(2138, 932, 'Ariel W.', 'lakedesire@gmail.com', 'http://democracyinsurgent.org', '128.95.87.80', '2010-05-09 13:06:34', '2010-05-09 21:06:34', 'I am an anarcho-syndaclist who organizes against budget cuts at UW with Student Worker Coalition.  While I agree fighting budget cuts is a reform, I think it is an important opportunity to politicize campus and fight for direct democracy in the workplace and the classroom.  I don''t think there will be a place for the university in an anarchist society, but in the mean time I will fight for democratic control of my workplace.\r\n\r\nI was at May 3 the whole time--I am the young white woman in red who was often on the bullhorn.  Nobody gave me this pamphlet while I was there or approached me to discuss.  I would have liked to discuss tactics on May 3 rather than after the fact on the passive aggressive medium of the internet.  I mostly want to ask what the authors of this statement advocate in terms of organizing.  This statement is pretty abstract (and I''m an English grad student so abstract isn''t foreign to me) and don''t know how I can translate a document like this into the organizing and agitating I do with my fellow grad students &amp; the other campus workers I organize with.  "Destroy work" doesn''t seem that doable to my immigrant comrades with two or three jobs and families to support.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10_6_3; en-us) AppleWebKit/531.22.7 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0.5 Safari/531.22.7', '', 0, 0),
