(1893, 856, 'A Known E-Moose', 'aknownemoose@hotmail.com', '', '67.161.121.205', '2010-04-09 15:37:07', '2010-04-09 23:37:07', 'I feel like there''s clearly people in the DIY community who favor fighting back and self-defense. There''s an important critique of capitalism that goes something like this: anything that is not directly fighting capitalism is absorbed into it. Once upon a time, everything was an alternative, but capitalism is global today precisely because it has the ability, in fact the need, hardwired into it, to conquer, colonize, and absorb all alternatives. Thus, the principles of DIY and the broader anti-authoritarian scene it emerged from, come into a conflict with reality, and have to answer the question: attack the system, or be absorbed back into it, just like all our predecessors.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9.1.9) Gecko/20100315 Firefox/3.5.9 (.NET CLR 3.5.30729)', '', 0, 0),
