(1920, 887, 'bex', 'lionsbirthday@hotmail.com', '', '96.26.240.201', '2010-04-12 09:34:45', '2010-04-12 17:34:45', 'something happened on april 9th. people were in the streets (and sidewalks), people were beat up and kidnapped by police, people were confused/angry/afraid/supported/surprised/inspired. \r\n\r\ni can easily see benji''s editorial about these events on the seattlediy website leading to ideological and personal fall-out and division in the seattle anarchist/anti-authoritarian/ diy community. debate about (dis)organization, stances on (non)violence, and what counts as more or less creative strategies of resistance/attack are all necessary. how else can we learn from our experiences and hear the voices of our communities?\r\n\r\nthe internet is notorious for fostering ill-will, misunderstandings, and division. i see it as a form of passive and indirect communication - helpful for deepening rifts, unhelpful for understanding their causes.\r\n\r\ni believe that these conversations may be more effective and productive if held in person - for example, in a community forum or discussion group specifically gathered to make a space for everyone''s thoughts.\r\nthis would not be a space for a bully pulpit or a gang-up, but rather a honest attempt of all involved to fully hear one another out. \r\n\r\nin our own ways we are all seeking to make manifest an ideal world. for my part, i would like to believe this is an opportunity not for further division or ostracism, but to strengthen the seattle anarchist community by broadening the scope of relationships and interactions which we feel we can constructively engage in. \r\n\r\nwe should all be willing (excited even!) to hold each other accountable and be held accountable ourselves. that''s fundamental. i would love to see this conversation continue in person. anyone else?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.19) Gecko/2010031218 Firefox/3.0.19', '', 0, 201),
(1921, 887, 'bex', 'lionsbirthday@hotmail.com', '', '96.26.240.201', '2010-04-12 09:56:21', '2010-04-12 17:56:21', 'and the internet is guaranteed to be 100% monitored. how annoying is THAT when it comes to freely and fully expressing ourselves?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.5; en-US; rv:1.9.0.19) Gecko/2010031218 Firefox/3.0.19', '', 0, 201),
