(455, 98, '2009-08-17 15:15:02', '2009-08-17 23:15:02', '<p style="text-align: center"><img class="aligncenter" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3064/2798485245_15a0d356e2.jpg" alt="Carousel Fest 2008 Love!" width="500" height="375" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hey Everybody!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Something wonderful is about to happen. It has nothing to do with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2010_Odyssey_Two" target="_blank"><em>2010 a Space Odyssey</em></a> (even though that would be <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jupiter" target="_blank">totally cool</a>!) but it has to do with <em>2009 a Seattle Odyssey</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Carousel Fest 2009!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And we need volunteers to help with whatever they can for the three days and six spaces that it will be taking place. As we have only two weeks left until the festival begins, we''re pressed to have individuals committed to helping out on this.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All proceeds this year go to the <a href="http://www.urbanreststop.org/" target="_blank">Urban Rest Stop</a> and <a href="http://www.hollowearthradio.com/" target="_blank">Hollow Earth Radio</a> so even if you are unsure or unable to volunteer for Carousel Fest this year, you can still come, see amazing musical acts, and help out two amazing organizations. For more updated information about the festival itself, visit Carousel Festival''s MySpace: <a href="http://www.myspace.com/carouselfestival" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/carouselfestival</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are interested in volunteering or have any questions about it, feel fine to e-mail me: <strong>kenneth.​m.​piekarski@​gmail.​com</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith Much Love (I mean it),<br />\r\n<br />\r\n-Kenneth-</p>', 'Carousel Festival Volunteering', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'carousel-festival-volunteering', '', '', '2009-08-17 15:15:02', '2009-08-17 23:15:02', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=455', 0, 'post', '', 1),
