equent events at various spaces\r\n<a href="http://www.seattlefreeschool.org/">http://www.seattlefreeschool.org</a>\r\nRegister for classes online!\r\n\r\n<strong>Squid &amp; Ink</strong>\r\nVegan restaurant, frequent shows\r\n<a href="http://www.myspace.com/squid_and_ink">www.myspace.com/squid_and_ink</a>\r\n1128 S. Albro Pl, in Georgetown\r\n\r\n<strong>20/20 Cycle</strong>\r\nBike shop, show and community event space\r\n2020 E. Union – Central District\r\n<a href="http://2020cycle.com">2020cycle.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>UmojaFest P.E.A.C.E. Center</strong>\r\n1107 24th Ave - Central District\r\n<a href="http://umojafestpeacecenter.com">http://umojafestpeacecenter.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Vera Project</strong>\r\nNon-profit venue, community space for meetings, workshops, art gallery, etc\r\nOn the corner of Warren Ave N\r\n&amp; Republican St @ Seattle Center\r\n<a href="http://theveraproject.org">theveraproject.org</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Wayward Café</strong>\r\nVegan cafe, occasional events\r\n9th and 55th - U-District\r\n<a href="http://myspace.com/waywardcafe">myspace.com/waywardcafe</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>West Seattle Legion Hall</strong>\r\nVenue for sporadic shows\r\n3618 SW Alaska St – West Seattle\r\n<a href="http://nwhardcore.com">nwhardcore.com</a>\r\n\r\nOther places to check for events:\r\nnwhardcore.com\r\nseattlepunk.org\r\nseattlefreeschool.org\r\nhttp://www.scn.org/activism/calendar\r\nhttp://www.seattleactivism.org\r\nhttp://sewupseattle.blogspot.com', 'Venues', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'venues', '', '', '2010-06-15 22:40:27', '2010-06-16 06:40:27', '', 11, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/new/?page_id=84', 1, 'page', '', 4),
(390, 99, '2009-07-30 12:23:26', '2009-07-30 20:23:26', '<p>In the basement of Arctic Circle...</p>\r\n<p>WORLD HISTORY (Seattle WA)<br />\r\nhttp://worldhistory.pirateandcowboy.com<br />\r\nhttp://www.myspace.com/worldworldhistoryhistory\\</p>\r\n<p>DEAD WESTERN (Sacramento CA)<br />\r\nDownload/Listen at http://www.snailonastick.com/downloads.htm<br />\r\nor they have a MySpace at http://www.myspace.com/50690003<br />\r\nI think they''re touring as a TRIO.<br />\r\n“In shadow, he appears neanderthal; in light, he waxes angelic. Who is<br />\r\nDead Western? He is a man of a gaping mouth, out of which pours — as readily as water from a faucet — a haunting, bewildering, beautiful voice, reminiscent of Scott Walker (circa Climate of Hunter). This bellowing voice, like an ancient reptile, slithers and wraps itself around the most tender acoustic melodies. Dead Western sounds like a forest growing (the throatless groaning of age-old trees); feels like a Victorian passage through limbo (grey, ominous); looks like a Grecian statue (as drawn by Robert Crumb). This is the sort of music one feels profoundly acquainted with — but not something generally found in record format. It is the shifting of rock, the scuttling of insects, the hissing of the wind: frightful, eternal.”</p>\r\n<p>WEBELOS (Seattle WA)<br />\r\nThey have a MySpace at www.myspace.com/thewebelosmusic<br />\r\nLiving Room Pop!</p>\r\n<p>-----</p>\r\n<p>at the Arctic Circle [Georgetown]<br />\r\nwww.arcticcirclehouse.info<br />\r\n6633 Ellis Ave S [98108]--------&gt; #60. 131. 174 buses</p>\r\n<p>Bring $ for the bands.<br />\r\n&amp; we''ll have some food for you to eat.<br />\r\nFood at 7:00PM<br />\r\nShow at 8:00PM</p>\r\n<p>IF YOU COME TO THE SHOW, Jamie (World History) will draw your portrait &amp; sign it &amp; give it to you.</p>\r\n', 'Get Your Portrait Drawn &amp; See Music TONIGHT.', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'get-your-portrait-drawn-see-music-tonight', '', '', '2009-07-30 12:24:24', '2009-07-30 20:24:24', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=390', 0, 'post', '', 0),
