(136, 3, '2008-08-16 23:03:42', '2008-08-17 07:03:42', 'Carousel Festival!!! The lovely Nathan from The Greenhouse and the SeattleDIY Collective have organized Carousel Fest''s third year of  awesomeness,  and this year is going to be a doozy!  Check myspace.com/carouselfestival for the  schedule.  This year we''re going to have some amazing artists to help us celebrate the local DIY community and raise money for Communities Against Rape And Abuse (CARA,  cara-seattle.org) and Home Alive (homealive.org),  including Kimya Dawson,  Bloodhag,  LP+BB,  Madeline,  and tons more!\r\n\r\nA shit storm has landed in Seattle following a violent exchange that occurred at the July Critical Mass ride.  Most media outlets are placing blame on bicyclists.  Let us first acknowledge that the actions of a few DO NOT represent the intentions of the whole.  Also,  it''s important to get accounts from witnesses of various perspectives – pedestrians,  drivers,  and bicyclists.  Critical Mass is still a  relevant expression of solidarity amongst bicyclists,  despite this incident,  and bicyclists deserve the right to safely express their desire to live in a bicycle-positive town.  Stay safe,  and keep riding.   \r\n\r\nA good friend of many people in the local DIY community has been arrested and is being charged with causing property damage. Please support Bryan LeFey!\r\nWe''re sad to say goodbye to a few DIY spaces! Dearborn on Woodland had their last show on July 5th.  The Ark is inhabited by new people and is now called Chilladelphia.  It saddens our hearts to let you know that Dog City is going to be torn down at the end of August.  Dog City will be hosting the first night of Carousel Festival,  which may be their last event.  \r\nDog City/Camp Nowhere has been an incredible place to meet people,  eat food,  and watch bands.  RIP.\r\n\r\nThere are a few new spaces popping up! The former inhabitants of the SS Marie Antoinette have begun a new space,  The Josephine (myspace.com/thejosephine).  There''s a house in South Seattle called The Jolly Roger (myspace.com/thejollyrogervenue) that hosts hardcore shows,  and House 2301 will apparently be hosting a show/month or so.  The Holy Mountain (myspace.com/holymountainvenue ) is still new on the scene,  and thus far has hosted some amazing events.  We''d like to welcome the House of Zanzibar (myspace.com/thehouseofzanzibar),  who have pledged to host some great events and pick up the slack left by the dearly departed houses.\r\n\r\nExciting event alert! The Spruce House (myspace.com/sprucehouse) is hosting a “DIY Happy Hour” on their stoop every other hursday \r\nfrom 6-9pm.  They''re hosting these events to help build community,  and they ask people to “BYO music,  food,  drinks,  shenanigans,  stories,  hidden talents,  skillshares and show and tells.” Email them at sprucehuset@gmail.com or message them for details.  The first one is on August 7th.\r\n\r\n', 'August 2008 News', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'august-2008-news', '', '', '2008-12-19 12:03:03', '2008-12-19 20:03:03', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=136', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(137, 1, '2008-12-16 23:03:45', '2008-12-17 07:03:45', '', 'Carousel Festival!!! The lovely Nathan from The Greenhouse and the SeattleDIY Collective have organized Carousel Fest''s third year of  awesomeness,  and this year is going to be a doozy!  Check myspace.com/carouselfestival for the  schedule.  This year we''re going to have some amazing artists to help us celebrate the local DIY community and raise money for Communities Against Rape And Abuse (CARA,  cara-seattle.org) and Home Alive (homealive.org),  including Kimya Dawson,  Bloodhag,  LP+BB,  Madeline,  and tons more!  A shit storm has landed in Seattle following a violent exchange that occurred at the July Critical Mass ride.  Most media outlets are placing blame on bicyclists.  Let us first acknowledge that the actions of a few DO NOT represent the intentions of the whole.  Also,  it''s important to get accounts from witnesses of various perspectives – pedestrians,  drivers,  and bicyclists.  Critical Mass is still a  relevant expression of solidarity amongst bicyclists,  despite this incident,  and bicyclists deserve the right to safely express their desire to live in a bicycle-positive town.  Stay safe,  and keep riding.     A good friend of many people in the local DIY community has been arrested and is being charged with causing property damage. Please support Bryan LeFey! We''re sad to say goodbye to a few DIY spaces! Dearborn on Woodland had their last show on July 5th.  The Ark is inhabited by new people and is now called Chilladelphia.  It saddens our hearts to let you know that Dog City is going to be torn down at the end of August.  Dog City will be hosting the first night of Carousel Festival,  which may be their last event.   Dog City/Camp Nowhere has been an incredible place to meet people,  eat food,  and watch bands.  RIP.  There are a few new spaces popping up! The former inhabitants of the SS Marie Antoinette have begun a new space,  The Josephine (myspace.com/thejosephine).  There''s a house in South Seattle called The Jolly Roger (myspace.com/thejollyrogervenue) that hosts hardcore shows,  and House 2301 will apparently be hosting a show/month or so.  The Holy Mountain (myspace.com/holymountainvenue ) is still new on the scene,  and thus far has hosted some amazing events.  We''d like to welcome the House of Zanzibar (myspace.com/thehouseofzanzibar),  who have pledged to host some great events and pick up the slack left by the dearly departed houses.  Exciting event alert! The Spruce House (myspace.com/sprucehouse) is hosting a “DIY Happy Hour” on their stoop every other hursday  from 6-9pm.  They''re hosting these events to help build community,  and they ask people to “BYO music,  food,  drinks,  shenanigans,  stories,  hidden talents,  skillshares and show and tells.” Email them at sprucehuset@gmail.com or message them for details.  The first one is on August 7th.  ', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '136-revision', '', '', '2008-12-16 23:03:45', '2008-12-17 07:03:45', '', 136, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=137', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
