(227, 1, '2009-02-06 17:54:05', '2009-02-07 01:54:05', 'We printed a bunch of newsletters and distributed some of them around town today! Also, for the first time we''ve included an insert in the newsletter - \nFor Crying Out Loud has given us some really exciting material with beautiful artwork and information about sexual violence survivor support, aggressor accountability, info about consent, and other valuable stuff. \nIt''s incredibly important info for everyone to have, and we feel honored to partner with For Crying Out Loud in distributing it around town. If you''d like to know more about what they''re doing, visit their webpage at http://www.myspace.com/forcryingoutloud206 and go to the Winter Skill Share and take some workshops with them! (http://www.myspace.com/seattleskillshare)\n\nRight now you can get newsletters at Singles Going Steady, The Vera Project, Left Bank Books, and Babeland, and soon we''ll get more to other places. If there''s other places you''d like to see them at let us know!\n\n- the SeattleDIY Collective', 'SeattleDIY February Newsletters out now', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '226-revision', '', '', '2009-02-06 17:54:05', '2009-02-07 01:54:05', '', 226, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=227', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
