(248, 91, '2009-03-23 13:49:17', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'It''s on!\n\nPunk Rock Flea Market returns to the Underground Events Center this summer! On June 6th, from 10:00 in the morning until 10:00 at night, the Punk Rock Flea will rock your world and fill the trunk of your car! The Underground is at 2407 1st Ave. in Belltown, Seattle. For those of you keeping track, this is PRFM #6!\n\nThis is a full on flea market selling everything you can imagine, including records, clothing, furniture, computers, stereo equipment, housewares, haircuts, toys, videos, bicycles, tacos, falafels, vegan treats, skateboards, political propaganda, information from non profit groups, books, art, bike repair, baby stuff, tarot readings &amp; whatever else we can fit into the space. Don''t let the name lead you to believe that we only welcome vendors selling punk records, clothes etc. The "Punk Rock" of the name refers as much to the DIY spirit of the event as it does to any particular music or lifestyle. ''Nuff said.\n\nSince it''s the height of summer, we''re gonna use the outside parking lot in addition to the Underground inside, so we''ve got 80 spaces for rent. The first 80 forms to come back with $25 will get those spaces. No exceptions. We have a few tables available, but if possible, bring your own. You should also plan to bring all of your own lighting and display equipment. Space at the PRFM always sells out, so I recommend reserving a space sooner rather than later. Send me an email to get the form – PRFleamarket@gmail.com. If you''ve done this before and know the drill it''s okay to just send your check and vendor info.\n\nAs always, the market opens to the public at 10:00 am and bands will begin to play at around 6:00 pm. Vendors are welcome to stay for the entire event, but it isn''t required. The 6:00 transition will be a natural moment for tired vendors to close up shop.\n\nOnce again, the space we are using has been generously loaned to us for the day by the Low Income Housing Institute, aka. LIHI. LIHI is a non-profit organization that builds homes for homeless and low-income people all around the Puget Sound. Your table fees and entry donations go toward paying insurance and advertising costs for this event. Once those expenses are covered, all additional proceeds will go to LIHI. You are most welcome to make additional donations to LIHI if you feel so inclined. More info about them at www.lihi.org.\n\nThe PRFM is put on by volunteers and amateurs, so you can help make it work by communicating your needs and by letting us know if we''re missing something important. We want this event to be successful, and we want to do it again!\n\nTo reserve a space or ask questions contact producer Joshua Okrent at PRFleamarket@gmail.com or (206) 957-8076. More info at http://www.myspace.com/punkrock_fleamarket. ', 'Punk Rock Flea Market', 0, '', 'pending', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2009-03-23 13:49:17', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=248', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(237, 72, '2009-02-28 23:51:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Hey all you bikey DIYers.\nThe Bike Shack has been hoping to have its annual brew fest this March 14th (Pi day!) but while we have several brewers, we''re still short on brew.\nMore importantly, we''re missing a venue!  We''re still hoping to do a brewfest as it brings in the vast majority of our rent (and due to the recent burglary, tool replacement) for the year.  Please let us know if you would like to donate a brew (you are compensated for ingredient cost) or know of a location which is willing/able to host the brew fest.  It generally pulls in 100-150 people and serves 40 gallons or so of brews.\nIf we can''t get something together the 14th, there''s still time to reschedule, but we have rent for sure out to the end of July assuming we don''t replace our tools (at least $150 wholesale) or any of our supplies (of which the Spring season will quickly wipe out many of them.)\nAgain, if you''ve never used us, the Bike Shack is a volunteer-run community bike shop dedicated to facilitating personal bike repair in allowing tool use, donated parts, and teaching hands-on bicycle repair.  We''re always in need of new volunteers.  Come during any of the hours posted on BikeShack.org [particularly 4-7 Thursdays, the only ones I guarantee!] and come check us out!\nBehind the Wayward Cafe on the corner of 9th and 55th NE in the U-District/Ravenna.', 'Last ditch effort:', 0, '', 'pending', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2009-02-28 23:51:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=237', 0, 'post', '', 0),
