(279, 1, '2009-04-30 12:16:20', '2009-04-30 20:16:20', 'Tonight (April 30th) in a garage/bike workshop/occasional DIY venue on Beacon Hill, will be a pretty amazing and diverse punk show. The four different bands playing could all be categorized under the catch all "pop punk," but each of the bands'' take on that cliche and mostly useless term are unique and appealing to largely different audiences. Slingshot Dakota, for example, are a two-piece band from the east coast who eschew the common formula ritualized since The Ramones, and instead focus their songs around the skillful and complex piano of Carly Commando (she''s classically trained) and soaring dual male/female vocals, but avoid any comparisons to pop groups like Mates of State by bringing a level of intensity that is clearly brought from a hardcore pedigree (take, for example, their <a href="http://www.ifyoumakeit.com/video/slingshot-dakota/waiting-room/">cover of "Waiting Room"</a>). \r\nThe other bands are equally impressive and distinct from one another. Be sure to show up on time at 7:30, cuz the show has to be over early to avoid troubles with neighbors and the noise ordinance.\r\n\r\nRVIVR (Amazing pop punk from Olympia!)\r\nSLINGSHOT DAKOTA (from Long Island)\r\nA MILLION YEARS AGO (Catchy, danceable and from Seattle!)\r\nAGATHA (Local punks! First Seattle Show!)\r\n\r\n7pm @ Montersorri House\r\n2317 14th ave. S. on Beacon Hill\r\nClose to 36 and 60 bus routes\r\n\r\n$3-5 Donation for touring folks\r\n\r\nWill start no later than 7:30pm. Must be done by 10:30. ', 'RVIVR/Slingshot Dakota/A Million Years Ago/Agatha', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rvivrslingshot-dakotaa-million-years-agoagatha', '', '', '2009-04-30 12:19:56', '2009-04-30 20:19:56', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=279', 0, 'post', '', 1),
