(282, 1, '2009-05-02 13:24:17', '2009-05-02 21:24:17', 'Tonight at Healthy Times Fun Club is a show with Why I Must Be Careful, who are a duo from Portland who skirt lines between noise, punk, and jazz in a way that doesn''t come off as pretentious, too high-minded, or too abstract. Their execution is oddly accessible, danceable even amid all its chaos - though you''ll be likely to watch with mouth agape when you witness their skill with their instruments. Like a lot of their contemporaries in the DIY noise/punk scene, they often take advantage of live shows as an opportunity to do something unexpected, making each night unique from the last, sometimes incorporating contact mics taped to their necks or other surprises into their set. Also at this show is Secret Mommy, from Vancouver CA, who in recent years have played live as an ensemble using acoustic instruments, though much of their recorded albums are digital.\r\n\r\n<object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/_XG6tojDE6A&hl=en&fs=1&rel=0"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/_XG6tojDE6A&hl=en&fs=1&rel=0" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object>', 'Why I Must Be Careful, Secret Mommy, Pillow Fight Fight!, Braidstorm', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-i-must-be-careful-secret-mommy-pillow-fight-fight-braidstorm', '', '', '2009-05-02 13:24:17', '2009-05-02 21:24:17', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=282', 0, 'post', '', 0),
