(298, 1, '2009-05-18 12:44:05', '2009-05-18 20:44:05', 'Monsterssori Microcinema Presents:\r\n\r\nLOST FILM FEST\r\nMAY 19TH 7pm!\r\npotluck at 7, films to promptly start at 8.\r\n2317 14th Ave S, Beacon Hill\r\n5-10 bux sliding scale for travelling Philidelphians\r\n\r\nSURPRISE!\r\n\r\nSurprise email!  Announcing a surprise show!\r\n\r\nMonstersorri Microcinema''s friends, West Philly''s own LOST FILM FEST is coming to Seattle for one night to present a special show at the MONSTERSSORI OBSERVATORY.  Lost Film Fest is a sort of hilarious, free-form short video festival where VJ Scotty Beibin sort of freeform-selects videos from his hard drive.  Scott works with some amazing people in his other life as part of Evil Twin Booking, so he''s often got otherwise unavailable videos from such favorites as the YES MEN and others.\r\nScott also promises a special sneek preview of his new show, SCIENTISTS ARE THE NEW ROCK STARS: "a live multimedia spectacle exploring the fuzzy and quarky lines between hard science, social science, and metaphysics with hands-on examples of environmentally sustainable art and technologies."\r\n\r\nhttp://www.lostfilmfest.com/\r\n\r\nBring a friend!  This is a surprise show, surprise us with a great audience and we''ll bring you more great stuff like this in the future!\r\n\r\n\r\nYours in Crime,\r\n\r\nAV Flaxoil\r\nMedia Monopolist', 'Lost Film Festival in Seattle!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lost-film-festival-in-seattle', '', '', '2009-05-18 12:44:05', '2009-05-18 20:44:05', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=298', 0, 'post', '', 0);
