(304, 11, '2009-05-31 20:44:23', '2009-06-01 04:44:23', '<p>Beacon Hill Community Festival is happening on June 6 at 11am at the Jefferson Community Center. There will be local food, carnival games, bouncy castle and so many local groups performing.</p>\r\n<p>Sacred Temple, a tantric healing community, was raided on Thursday May 21. This community of healers has been accused of prostitution and raided on that basis. The owner is under investigation for promoting prostitution and money laundering. The Seattle Police Department has on this occasion and several others overstepped their bounds and in so doing has trampled on the right of workers and sex workers in particular. While this story is not entirely clear as of this date the community should be kept aware. There is an unusually good article in The Stranger and you should check it out. </p>\r\n<p>Reclaim the Media and local community centers will be helping people find  and set up their DTV converter box. June 12 is the DTV conversion day. If you need help with this or further information look to reclaimthemedia.org. Speaking of this also look to www.scantv.org to get involved. </p>\r\n<p>The Bend-It Collective Extravaganza is coming Saturday 27-Monday 29! It is a rad arts festival led by and for queer young people and their friends. It will be all free, rad performers and also food. Check out the calendar at seattlediy.com for specifics. </p>\r\n<p>Fire Breathing Kangaroo House just started Plane Crash Theater in the backyard at their house. </p>\r\n', 'June News', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'june-news', '', '', '2009-06-02 19:23:14', '2009-06-03 03:23:14', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=304', 0, 'post', '', 0),
