(306, 11, '2009-05-31 20:44:23', '2009-06-01 04:44:23', 'Beacon Hill Community Festival is happening on June 6 at 11am at the Jefferson Community Center. There will be local food, carnival games, bouncy castle and so many local groups performing. Also, a member of our community will be there with his student from Maple Elementary doing the Lion Dance. \r\n\r\nSacred Temple, a tantric healing community, was raided on Thursday May 21. This community of healers has been accused of prostitution and raided on that basis. The owner is under investigation for promoting prostitution and money laundering. The Seattle Police Department has on this occasion and several others overstepped their bounds and in so doing has trampled on the right of workers and sex workers in particular. While this story is not entirely clear as of this date the community should be kept aware. There is an unusually good article in The Stranger and you should check it out. \r\n\r\nReclaim the Media and local community centers will be helping people find  and set up their DTV converter box. June 12 is the DTV conversion day. If you need help with this or further information look to reclaimthemedia.org. Speaking of this also look to www.scantv.org to get involved. \r\n\r\nThe Bend-It Collective Extravaganza is coming Saturday 27-Monday 29! It is a rad arts festival led by and for queer young people and their friends. It will be all free, rad performers and also food. Check out the calendar at seattlediy.com for specifics. \r\n\r\nFire Breathing Kangaroo House just started Plane Crash Theater in the backyard at their house. ', 'June News', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '304-revision-2', '', '', '2009-05-31 20:44:23', '2009-06-01 04:44:23', '', 304, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=306', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(308, 138, '2009-06-04 17:09:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<p>Hey SDIYers,</p>\n\n<p>We''re seeking a roommate for a 3br Wallingford house, starting on July 1st. Rent is $475/month plus utilities, with first/last/security deposit as well as a $35 credit check required by our landlord. The house is a block from Greenlake and close to bus routes, and in addition to your personal room there is a small shared office/studio space. <br />\n <br />\n Our ideal roommate is a student/artist/whatever who is creative, clean, and responsible. We''re a low-key couple who''re looking for a roommate who doesn''t come with any drama or pets. My girlfriend is an architecture student, and I work at a teen center on the Eastside.</p>\n\n<p>We''re omnivores but have no problem w/ Vegans/Veggies and aren''t obsessed w/ meat or anything.</p>', 'Roommate sought for 3br house in July', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2009-06-04 17:09:19', '2009-06-05 01:09:19', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=308', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(309, 99, '2009-06-05 00:14:28', '2009-06-05 08:14:28', '<p><br class="spacer_" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Food at 6:30 PM, presentation starts at 7 PM sharp, and bands follow. Sliding scale donations will be taken for tour costs and Eric’s legal fees.  Arctic Circle is a collective house in Georgetown.  Visit <a href="http://www.arcticcirclehouse.info">our website</a> for more details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Eric was arrested (along with Zachary Jenson and Lauren Weiner) on January 13, 2006, as part of the government’s ongoing Green Scare campaign. All three were charged with <a href="http://supporteric.org/indictment.pdf">“Conspiracy              to damage and destroy property by fire and an explosive.”</a> His arrest was the direct result of a government informant –              known only as “<a href="http://supporteric.org/pdfs/elleexhibit.pdf">Anna</a>”              – who spent a year and a half drawing him in and working with the              <span class="caps">FBI</span> to fabricate a crime and implicate Eric in it. Anna was paid over              $65,000 for her work with the <span class="caps">FBI</span>. Eric was imprisoned for what amounts to thought-crime – no actions were ever carried out, and Eric was charged with a single count of “conspiracy” – a powerful legal tool often used by the state to crush dissent. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">The tour consists of a workshop and musical performance.  First, friends of Eric will be presenting information about his case, which serves as a lens through which to study the basic concepts of entrapment, the use of informants, and government repression in general.  Unfortunately, the use of these tools by the state is becoming more and more prevalent, and it’s imperative that people understand how they work.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Following the presentation will be the beautiful musical catharsis of <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/Nora%2B%26%2BGnoll/Forward%2Bin%2BAll%2BDirections">Nora &amp; Gnoll </a>and              <a href="http://southwestmomusic.ning.com/profile/SpokePantsoftheFloweringSkillet">Spoke Pants of the Flowering Skillet</a>, from the Anarchozarkian MusicCollective, straight from the bowels of the midwest. We assure you, you won''t be disappointed.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">For more information on Eric and the Green Scare, please visit:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><a href="http://www.supporteric.org"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Support Eric</span></a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><a href="http://www.greenisthenewred.com">Green is the New Red</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><a href="http://www.arcticcirclehouse.info">Arctic Circle</a><br />\r\n </span></p>', 'Support Eric McDavid Tour at Arctic Circle Tuesday, June 16th', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'support-eric-mcdavid-tour-at-arctic-circle-tuesday-june-16th', '', '', '2009-06-05 00:14:28', '2009-06-05 08:14:28', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=309', 0, 'post', '', 0),
