(353, 99, '2009-06-30 16:32:11', '2009-07-01 00:32:11', '<p>..and the AETA 4 need your support!</p>\r\n<p>Come to the Arctic Circle on Friday, July 10th for a secret cafe to benefit the AETA 4! There will be delicious food, delectable company, and secret entertainment. Admission will be sliding scale ($1-10), and dinner starts promptly at 5:30.</p>\r\n<p>Who are the AETA 4?</p>\r\n<p>Nathan Pope, Adriana Stumpo, Joseph Buddenberg, and Maryam Khajavi were arrested in February of 2009 for public protest, and charged by the FBI for violating the Animal Enterprise Terrorism Act. The AETA 4 face an absurd maximum of ten years in prison for simply writing in chalk on the sidewalk of UCSC, wearing bandanas while protesting, and distributing flyers about animal research. </p>\r\n<p>What is the Animal Enterprise Terrorism Act (AETA)?</p>\r\n<p>The AETA was created to expand the Animal Enterprise Protection Act, used to convict the SHAC 7 (http://shac7.com), to further terrorize dissent and strip activists of First Amendment rights. Essentially, the AETA serves to protect corporations that participate in the many dimensions of animal cruelty and their business affiliates from public protest (http://www.greenisthenewred.com/blog/aeta-101/313/).</p>\r\n<p>The AETA is a part of a larger movement directed by the FBI that many environmental activists refer to as the “Green Scare” (http://greenscare.org), which is being used to crack down on environmental and animal rights organizing and actions. The Green Scare first appeared in 2002 after congressional hearings to discuss the Animal Liberation Front (ALF) as well as the Earth Liberation Front (ELF), in an effort to better understand how their actions threatened corporate profit and what the government could do to create a safety net for said corporations.</p>\r\n<p>Why does this matter?</p>\r\n<p>The Green Scare is being used to create a culture of fear in activist communities in order to uphold corporate “rights” to profit and nurture the free market economy, primarily through the use of infiltration (http://supporteric.org),  intimidation, manipulation, heavy surveillance, coercion, and blatant censorship. These themes are beginning to blur into a larger state of government oppression, in which people''s rights as well as the law are being openly violated.<br />\r\nCurrently, the government is investing tax dollars in acquiring corporations and banks and the line distinguishing the state''s powers from corporate power is a joke. Facing new laws and precedent setting prosecutions to protect companies from “terrorists,” activists face new difficulties in future attempts to hold “representatives” OR companies accountable. One tool available to anti-authoritarians and anarchists is to work at establishing a viable and supportive community that not only refuses to be silenced and intimidated, but reaches out to those being persecuted for the sake of profits. So, come join us if you can, and please bring money to benefit the AETA 4.</p>\r\n<p>For more information visit: www.aeta4.org</p>\r\n<p>You can also visit www.arcticcirclehouse.info<br />\r\nArctic Circle is at 6633 Ellis Ave. S. in Georgetown.</p>\r\nPLEASE RSVP! we@arcticcirclehouse.info', 'Shit''s gettin'' wacky...', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'shits-gettin-wacky', '', '', '2009-07-03 11:12:12', '2009-07-03 19:12:12', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=353', 0, 'post', '', 0),
