(405, 1, '2009-08-02 16:42:35', '2009-08-03 00:42:35', '<a href="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_Sd1mMUBlyRw/SnOYE7MCU5I/AAAAAAAAA6w/j94bIYZ0IOw/s1600-h/carouselsmall.jpg"><img src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_Sd1mMUBlyRw/SnOYE7MCU5I/AAAAAAAAA6w/j94bIYZ0IOw/s400/carouselsmall.jpg"/></a>\r\n(click the image for a bigger view!! poster by <a href="http://www.derekcharm.com/">Derek Charm</a>!)\r\n\r\nCarousel Festival is going to be awesome this year, as with every year. What is Carousel Fest? It''s a DIY celebration - regional artists and musicians will be performing at various houses and art spaces. Come and enjoy watching some amazing bands, join in on some workshops, watch some film, and hang out with a bunch of people who are similarly stoked about all the cool creative energy going on in the area!\r\n\r\nAll proceeds for Carousel Festival benefit Urban Rest Stop (<a href="http://urbanreststop.org">urbanreststop.org</a>) and Hollow Earth Radio (<a href="http://hollowearthradio.com">hollowearthradio.com</a>). Entry is a $5 donation at the door of each Carousel Festival location, or you can buy a full-festival ticket for $17 at the fest or at locations TBA (we''ll let you know asap!). ', 'CAROUSEL FESTIVAL 4!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'carousel-festival-4', '', '', '2009-08-02 17:51:04', '2009-08-03 01:51:04', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=405', 0, 'post', '', 0),
