quid_and_ink</a>\r\n1128 S. Albro Pl, in Georgetown\r\n\r\n<strong>20/20 Cycle</strong>\r\nBike shop, show and community event space\r\n2020 E. Union – Central District\r\n<a href="http://2020cycle.com">2020cycle.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Vera Project</strong>\r\nNon-profit venue, community space for meetings, workshops, art gallery, etc\r\nOn the corner of Warren Ave N\r\n& Republican St @ Seattle Center\r\n<a href="http://theveraproject.org">theveraproject.org</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Wayward Café</strong>\r\nVegan cafe, occasional events\r\n9th and 55th - U-District\r\n<a href="http://myspace.com/waywardcafe">myspace.com/waywardcafe</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>West Seattle Legion Hall</strong>\r\nVenue for sporadic shows\r\n3618 SW Alaska St – West Seattle\r\n<a href="http://nwhardcore.com">nwhardcore.com</a>', 'Venues', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '84-revision-10', '', '', '2009-08-02 20:56:41', '2009-08-03 04:56:41', '', 84, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=424', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(425, 98, '2009-08-02 18:04:58', '2009-08-03 02:04:58', '<p><img style="vertical-align: middle" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2559/3676619431_80bfbab3c9.jpg" alt="Bash Brothere (Photo by Sarah Anne Lloyd" width="500" height="333" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a very last-minute show <em>but</em> it is worth it if you go. It''s <strong>Monday, the 3rd of August</strong>, This upcoming Monday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Personally, I have only seen the Bash Brothers play but not the Apollo Ghosts or the Madonna Bangers. They''re on a small tour in the states from the fair country from above, Canadia.  It''s going to probably be punk-as-eff, so bring your earplugs so let''s welcome them with hugs and kisses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I met the Bash Brothers through Angelo Spencer at an inversely sold out show at the Comet Tavern. I was upset but, you know... the Comet. It was a great show though! Desolation Wilderness and Generifus were also playing so it was kind of upsetting that no one was there. I mean, I guess it made sense because the academy awards were <em>that night</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tangent</strong>: Do you ever notice about how there are a lot of actors that are <em>incredibly</em> poor at presenting themselves at the AA''s? They''re actors... I mean, come on! They should be good at <em>acting</em> excited about getting an award!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Anyway</em>, Kristjanne and Lindsay (the Bash Brothers), Angelo  and I were chumming it up, like we do. Then when were were talking about how much we really like Angelo''s music after he was done, the BB''s went to set up and as they started playing... I pooped myself.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Not</em> the bad pooping either, the good kind that your heart does when it falls in love with something unexpectedly. A metaphorical poop, I guess.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apollo Ghosts:<br />\r\n <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.myspace.com/adrianteacher" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/adrianteacher</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bash Brothers:<br />\r\n <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.myspace.com/bashbashbash" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/bashbashbash</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madonna Bangers:<br />\r\n <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.myspace.com/themadonnabangers" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/themadonnabangers</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hermit Thrushes (A awesome band from Phillie)<br />\r\n <a href="http://www.myspace.com/hermitthrushes"> http://www.myspace.com/hermitthrushes</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Love,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Kenneth-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px"> </p>\r\n\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">"THESE MIGHT VERY WELL BE THE BEST BANDS YOU SEE THIS SUMMER.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>seriously. I cannot recommend them highly enough. also, RAD DUDES."</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px">-Jenn H.-</p>', 'Apollo Ghosts, Bash Brothers, Madonna Bangers, Hermit Thrushes @ New Crompton', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '395-revision-15', '', '', '2009-08-02 18:04:58', '2009-08-03 02:04:58', '', 395, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=425', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
