(427, 1, '2009-08-03 16:52:19', '2009-08-04 00:52:19', '7:30pm\r\n\r\nCascade People''s Center\r\n309 Pontius Ave. North\r\nSeattle, WA 98109\r\n\r\nCommon Action Seattle invites you to a screening of <a href="http://www.terrorizingdissent.org">Terrorizing Dissent</a>, a film documenting the criminalization of dissent at the Republican National Convention in Saint Paul, Minnesota during September 2008.\r\n\r\nThe film features unforgettable historical footage, interviews with the RNC8 protest organizers who are now facing conspiracy charges, and footage from more than 40 cameras and journalists on the streets during the convention. See what really happened, see who ordered police violence and see how ordinary people were brutalized by riot cops.\r\n\r\n The event will also feature a fun door prize raffle bonanza. All proceeds benefit the RNC 8 defense fund. Following the film, stay for a Q & A session with RNC 8 member Luce Guillen-Givins on anarchist organizing, arrestee and prisoner support work and much more.\r\n\r\nBus Routes: 8, 25, 70-73, 74, 77, 79, 304, 317, 355, 377.\r\n\r\nCascade People''s Center is wheelchair accessible.\r\n\r\nFor more information on the RNC 8, visit http://www.rnc8.org.\r\n\r\nFor more info or to request on-site childcare, please call David at 206-909-1024', 'benefit film screening tonight!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'benefit-film-screening-tonight', '', '', '2009-08-03 16:52:19', '2009-08-04 00:52:19', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=427', 0, 'post', '', 0),
