(430, 1, '2009-08-13 13:37:08', '2009-08-13 21:37:08', '<img src="http://seattlediy.com/images/zinerelease.jpg" alt="zine release party" width="550"/>\r\n\r\nThe SeattleDIY Collective has been working on a zine with some other fine folks which will be a listing of places and projects in town that people can become engaged in, and have it be a guide to the city that isn''t just a list of cool places to go, but places where you can become an active participant. All sorts of places like The Bikery and projects like Food Not Bombs will be described, with information about how you can check them out and get more involved. The cover is beautifully printed via lino-cut by Team Nerd/Recession Proof Press, and there is a pull-out insert poster with a list of all sorts of great stuff going on. \r\n\r\nThe zine release party will be on August 16th at The Vera Project at 6pm, and for $5 entry you''ll get a copy of the zine and some amazingly delicious vegan food cooked by none other than The Asian Cajun (TM!), and music spun by Hollow Earth Radio DJ David Newman. You should definitely come and hang out with other exciting people who share similar passions and who do cool stuff, or if you''re part of a project you can come and bring info to give to peeps. For more info, email us at sdiycollective@gmail.com!\r\n', 'DIY Directory zine release party!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'diy-directory-zine-release-party', '', '', '2009-08-17 16:54:26', '2009-08-18 00:54:26', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=430', 0, 'post', '', 2),
