(443, 1, '2009-08-07 15:27:31', '2009-08-07 23:27:31', 'Saturday, August 8\r\n3pm at <a href="http://www.pilotbooksseattle.com/">Pilot Books</a> (219 Broadway E)\r\nFREE\r\n\r\nIf you''ve been curious how to formulate calendula hand cream or decoct burdock root, here''s your chance. Raleigh Briggs will be in the store tomorrow to demonstrate a few of those sweet sustainable nesting skills she writes about in <a href="http://microcosmpublishing.com/catalog/books/2333/">Make Your Place</a>. Herbal first aid, non-toxic cleaning supplies, organic garden boosters - she could whip out a recipe for any one of these or more. And she can answer questions on the rest.\r\n\r\nCome prepared to learn, discuss, and take back a few skills we''ve lost to the nasties (P&G, Clorox, I''m looking at you).\r\n\r\n<img src="http://microcosmpublishing.com/catimages/image_2333.jpg" alt="" />\r\n', 'Sustainable nesting skillz workshop!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sustainable-nesting-skillz-workshop', '', '', '2009-08-07 15:34:43', '2009-08-07 23:34:43', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=443', 0, 'post', '', 0),
