(498, 1, '2009-09-17 11:17:46', '2009-09-17 19:17:46', 'Here''s a message from our dear friends at the <a href="http://www.hugohouse.org/house/zapp/">Zine Archive and Publishing Project</a> (ZAPP!)\r\n\r\n"Dear Friends,\r\n\r\nOne year ago, on September 17, 2008, ZAPP reopened after a perversity of perils, including the great flood of 2007 that nearly drowned the zines in that persistent precipitation that perspires from the gray fogged body of the sky. \r\n\r\nThe re-opening would not have been possible without the help of dozens and dozens of wonderful people from all over the community.  Because of you, visiting, donating zines, reading zines, participating in events and spreading word of our existence, ZAPP would not  be able to grow and thrive.  Together, we have accomplished some remarkable things.   \r\n\r\nThanks to wonderful people like yourself, we’ve...\r\n    * Cataloged roughly 1000 zines\r\n    * Taken in roughly 800 newly donated zines\r\n    * Hosted the 1st national Zine Librarian “Unconference”\r\n    * Submitted six grant proposals\r\n    * Received the 4Culture Preservation Award\r\n    * Tabled at the Portland Zine Symposium\r\n    * Created a gallery space within ZAPP\r\n    * Formed a new partnership with the Vera Project\r\n    * Given tours and held classes for all ages\r\n    * Hosted a 24 Hour Zine Challenge\r\n    * Supported the enjoyment and creation of zines\r\n\r\nZAPP thanks everyone who has contributed to and supported zines, creative self-expression, DIY culture.  The artistic and literary outsiders, the marginalized and the radical, the crafty and the disenchanted, the brilliant and the odd, ZAPP owes it to you. \r\n\r\nThanks, you freaks.  We will not surrender….\r\n\r\n And with that, we bring you the book release party for Greg Hofmann’s debut illustrated novel, NO SURRENDER. \r\n\r\nA local artist, writer, and zinester, Mr. Hofmann is a good friend of ours and we would love it if you could come, Wednesday, September 30th at  7 PM.  Incorporating a spoken word performance, a slide show, and paintings, the event promises to be a multimedia extravaganza.  Also featuring a performance by author Isaac Marion and musical acts Begheera and Josh Powell.\r\n\r\n Come witness the excitement and help us celebrate the continuing vitality and importance of, oh you know, zines and performances and self publishing and art and all that insanity we for some reason think helps make the world livable and beautiful.\r\n\r\nLove,\r\nZAPP"\r\n<a href="http://www.hugohouse.org/house/zapp"><img src="http://www.owencurtsinger.com/linkpics/zapp.jpg" alt="" /></a>', 'We <3 ZAPP', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'we', '', '', '2009-09-17 11:17:46', '2009-09-17 19:17:46', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=498', 0, 'post', '', 0),
