(500, 1, '2009-09-17 14:42:44', '2009-09-17 22:42:44', 'One of the incredible things about having shows at DIY spaces like houses is that you can end up with an exciting mix of different kinds of art. Just as you may expect to see a crusty hardcore band or a cutesy lo-fi ukulele artist, you may also end up with cool performances by people that won''t be restricted to typical norms about what is sometimes expected or predictable in DIY spaces. This particular event is definitely along these lines, featuring a couple performers from Wisconsin who go to amazing places with their art. <a href="http://www.myspace.com/ShaneShaneBangedYourMom">Shane Shane</a> busts out absolutely ranchy and hyper-sexualizes queer dance jams, while <a href="http://www.myspace.com/wilhelminabaker">Wilhemina Baker</a> does a blend of performance art and arias sung through vocoders, often ending up partially naked, with the result being both at times scary and hilarious. Local marathon runner <a href="http://www.myspace.com/mchuggyb">MC Huggy B</a> will be bringing hip hop jams that celebrate having mad crushes, farmers markets, being poor, and being hooked on the internet. \r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.myspace.com/ShaneShaneBangedYourMom">Shane Shane</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.myspace.com/wilhelminabaker">Wilhemina Baker</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.myspace.com/mchuggyb">MC Huggy B</a>\r\nFriday September 18th, 7pm @ Dancylvania (110 Harvard Ave E, Capitol Hill)', 'rad show at Dancylvania!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rad-show-at-dancylvania', '', '', '2009-09-17 14:43:37', '2009-09-17 22:43:37', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=500', 0, 'post', '', 0);
