(517, 1, '2009-09-27 10:36:15', '2009-09-27 18:36:15', 'In towns with vibrant artist communities, it is inevitable that people will book events on the same night, even when the separate events consist of artists who are peers or roommates with one another. Tonight is a good example of this - two shows, both with bands who are excellent friends with the bands playing at the other show. This of course means that mutual friends of these performers will have a difficult choice as far as who to see. Will people choose one over the other based on convenience, or a preference for a particular band, or because they''re more excited about the general style of the music at one of the shows? \r\nThe choice for tonight is indeed difficult. At Monstersorri Observatory on Beacon Hill, there is a show with raucous and dancey punk bands who thrive on the audience singing along and thrashing about. One of the bands there tonight, Agatha, is just returning from a month-long tour, and will likely perform like a well-oiled machine. At Healthy Times Fun Club, the music will be more subdued, but definitely no less fun - Iji will play fun and danceable pop songs, while the others will likely play quiet songs that are both light hearted and beautiful. The pleasant surprise of tonight will likely be Little Teeth, who use atypical instrumentation and a range of percussion to craft their noise. \r\nSunday, September 27th:\r\n<strong>little teeth, iji, your heart breaks, world history</strong> @ <a href="http://www.myspace.com/healthytimesfunclub">healthy times fun club</a>\r\n<strong>Agatha, my parade, a million years ago</strong> @ monstersorri observatory (2317 14th Ave S, – Beacon Hill)\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.seattlediy.com/images/9-27-09.jpg" alt="" /><img src="http://hotlink.myspacecdn.com/images02/2/b771de45d2894bfa9d395e52b32c0938/m.jpg" alt="" />\r\n', 'nights of difficult decisions', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nights-of-difficult-decisions', '', '', '2009-09-27 10:40:42', '2009-09-27 18:40:42', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=517', 0, 'post', '', 1),
