(541, 1, '2009-10-19 12:18:50', '2009-10-19 20:18:50', 'No Olympics on Stolen Native Land Speaking Tour\r\nNovember 10th 7 PM\r\nCascade People''s Center\r\n(309 Pontius Ave N)\r\n\r\n<object width="400" height="267"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="movie" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=4869353&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1" /><embed src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=4869353&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" width="400" height="267"></embed></object><p><a href="http://vimeo.com/4869353">Resist 2010: Eight Reasons to Oppose the 2010 Winter Olympics. (LOW RES)</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user1798982">BurningFist Media</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>\r\n\r\nAs you may be aware, in February 2010, Vancouver (Canada) will be host\r\ncity for the 2010 Winter Olympics. Due to the negative impacts of the\r\nOlympics, including homelessness, ecological destruction, huge public\r\ndebt, and a greatly expanded police state, a movement has arisen to\r\nchallenge the Olympic industry & expose to the world its true nature.\r\n\r\nBeginning in mid-November, 2009, organizers from No2010, an Indigenous\r\nanti-Olympics organization, will travel down the West Coast of the US\r\nto conduct a speaking tour on the resistance to the 2010 Olympics, to\r\nshare their experiences, and to promote an anti-colonial & anti-\r\ncapitalist convergence that will coincide with the opening days of the\r\nGames in February, 2010 (Feb. 10-15, the Olympic Games begin Feb. 12).\r\n\r\nSince 2007, No2010 has been a primary source of information on the\r\nanti-Olympic struggle, publishing almost daily news accounts, reports\r\n& updates. They have published several PDF/magazines, leaflets,\r\nposters, stickers, and t-shirts as well. In 2009, they produced a 15\r\nminute video entitled Resist 2010. They  are also part of the Olympic\r\nResistance Network (ORN), which was established in 2008 and is\r\ncomprised of numerous grassroots autonomous groups & individuals.\r\n\r\nThe event will feature 1-2 speakers from No2010 and the Olympic\r\nResistance Network, a short video, with time for questions and\r\ndiscussion.\r\n\r\nSpeakers will also be available to do presentations at schools,\r\nuniversities, radio shows, etc., and to answer any inquiries from\r\nlocal media (corporate or alternative).\r\n\r\nFor more info: www.No2010.com, www.OlympicResistance.net\r\n\r\nEvent Sponsored by Common Action & Democracy Insurgent\r\n\r\nFlyer attached. Please post. Please Forward Widely!\r\n\r\nBus Routes: 8, 25, 70-73, 74, 77, 79, 304, 317, 355, 377.\r\n\r\nCascade People’s Center is wheelchair accessible. If you have any\r\nquestions about accessibility or require any other accommodations,\r\nplease call 206-612-2962 or E-mail lambert@riseup.net. If you require\r\nchildcare call or Email and we will work to arrange it upon request.', 'No Olympics on Stolen Native Land Speaking Tour - Nov. 10', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'no-olympics-on-stolen-native-land-speaking-tour-nov-10', '', '', '2009-10-19 12:18:50', '2009-10-19 20:18:50', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=541', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(542, 1, '2009-10-19 12:18:21', '2009-10-19 20:18:21', 'No Olympics on Stolen Native Land Speaking Tour\nNovember 10th 7 PM\nCascade People''s Center\n(309 Pontius Ave N)\n\n\n\nAs you may be aware, in February 2010, Vancouver (Canada) will be host\ncity for the 2010 Winter Olympics. Due to the negative impacts of the\nOlympics, including homelessness, ecological destruction, huge public\ndebt, and a greatly expanded police state, a movement has arisen to\nchallenge the Olympic industry & expose to the world its true nature.\n\nBeginning in mid-November, 2009, organizers from No2010, an Indigenous\nanti-Olympics organization, will travel down the West Coast of the US\nto conduct a speaking tour on the resistance to the 2010 Olympics, to\nshare their experiences, and to promote an anti-colonial & anti-\ncapitalist convergence that will coincide with the opening days of the\nGames in February, 2010 (Feb. 10-15, the Olympic Games begin Feb. 12).\n\nSince 2007, No2010 has been a primary source of information on the\nanti-Olympic struggle, publishing almost daily news accounts, reports\n& updates. They have published several PDF/magazines, leaflets,\nposters, stickers, and t-shirts as well. In 2009, they produced a 15\nminute video entitled Resist 2010. They  are also part of the Olympic\nResistance Network (ORN), which was established in 2008 and is\ncomprised of numerous grassroots autonomous groups & individuals.\n\nThe event will feature 1-2 speakers from No2010 and the Olympic\nResistance Network, a short video, with time for questions and\ndiscussion.\n\nSpeakers will also be available to do presentations at schools,\nuniversities, radio shows, etc., and to answer any inquiries from\nlocal media (corporate or alternative).\n\nFor more info: www.No2010.com, www.OlympicResistance.net\n\nEvent Sponsored by Common Action & Democracy Insurgent\n\nFlyer attached. Please post. Please Forward Widely!\n\nBus Routes: 8, 25, 70-73, 74, 77, 79, 304, 317, 355, 377.\n\nCascade People’s Center is wheelchair accessible. If you have any\nquestions about accessibility or require any other accommodations,\nplease call 206-612-2962 or E-mail lambert@riseup.net. If you require\nchildcare call or Email and we will work to arrange it upon request.', '', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '541-revision', '', '', '2009-10-19 12:18:21', '2009-10-19 20:18:21', '', 541, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=542', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(543, 1, '2009-10-19 15:15:16', '2009-10-19 23:15:16', 'Hey dear friends,\r\nWe''re looking to have more people writing on this blog about all the amazing events and projects that are going on in this fabulous city. Would you perhaps like to join in the fun?\r\nWhat we''re looking for is people to write with some journalistic flair about events, activities, and projects in town that give more detail than the usual "time/location/cause" that we get on a calendar. We want to uncover the background, context, and detail that make up the DIY community. Specifically, we''d like to see more on this blog from different aspects of the movement - news about & from the DIY community, local sellers and craft community, underground hiphop, noise and improvisation, activism (especially of the anti-authoritarian kind), workshops and skill-shares, youth-led organizations and movements, reviews of past events, etc. \r\nIf you''re interested, register and make an account on this website (upper right side of the page, "register" link), and send us an email describing what you''d like to write about. Email us at sdiycollective at gmail dot com.', 'Bloggers wanted!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bloggers-wanted', '', '', '2009-11-09 10:52:25', '2009-11-09 18:52:25', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=543', 0, 'post', '', 0),
