(552, 240, '2009-10-31 12:19:51', '2009-10-31 20:19:51', 'Couch Fest Films is a shorts film fest hosted in strangers'' houses all in one day in Seattle.  We are currently still looking for a few more host houses for Nov 7th, 2009. \r\n\r\nDo you like where you live?    Do you like film?    Do you like strangers?\r\n\r\nWell, why not open your residence to film loving strangers for couch fest films 2009?\r\n\r\nShare your unshakable fever for film with other compulsive cinephiles! Couch Fest Films is currently looking for Seattleites who are willing to open their home to host a short film program for this one day community film event.\r\n\r\nYou could be an honored host of a 30-minute shorts film program that will play every hour from 11am to 7pm.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested, email us: propaganda@couchfestfilms.com\r\n\r\nhttp://www.couchfestfilms.com/\r\n\r\n<object width="400" height="225"><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="movie" value="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=7154508&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1" /><embed src="http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=7154508&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=1&amp;show_byline=1&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" width="400" height="225"></embed></object><p><a href="http://vimeo.com/7154508">couch fest films promo 1</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/couchfestfilms">couch fest films</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>', 'couch fest films is still looking for host houses', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'couch-fest-films-is-still-looking-for-host-houses', '', '', '2009-10-31 12:21:43', '2009-10-31 20:21:43', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=552', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(553, 11, '2009-10-28 20:31:39', '2009-10-29 04:31:39', 'Seattle has a new infoshop opening mid-November. The L@s Quixotes Infoshop and Lending Library will carry radical books and zines for check-out. They will be located at 219 Broadway, upstairs inside of Pilot Books. Check out www.losquixotesinfoshop.wordpress.com for updates and more information. \r\n\r\nThanksgiving is celebrated in the United States this year on November 26. While many people in the United States will be celebrating with friends and family, indigenous people throughout the country will gather in protest. Many travel to Alcatraz island for Unthanksgiving Day to honor indigenous peoples of the Americas and fight for their rights or participate in the New England National Day of Mourning to honor indigenous ancestors and the struggles of indigenous peoples today. So, on this day remember the land that you are on and how you got here. \r\n\r\nNovember 11 is Veteran''s Day. Right now the United States is involved in two major wars and has military deployed in more the 150 countries around the world. Some great work is being done by veterans against war at Coffee Strong, a G.I coffee house just outside the gates of Fort Lewis in Lakewood, WA. Their goal is to provide soldiers, their families and recent vets a place where they can learn about their rights, receive non-military counseling, access alternative information and learn about resources available to them. Check it out! www.myspace.com/coffeestrong\r\n\r\nLast month SO many people came out for the Anarchist Bookfair. Thanks to the organizers so much working their asses off. The vendors were great but the workshops were amazing. Cannot wait for next year!\r\n\r\nThe Really, Really Free Market Festival will be held on Black Friday or Buy Nothing Day on November 27. On this day instead of buying all your presents for the holidays maybe you could come hang out with some folks downtown and pick up some free stuff. Free zines, workshops, buttons, theater and so much more. What is also great about this is that it falls so close to the 10th anniversary of the World Trade Organization (WTO) protests. \r\n\r\nSpeaking of the 10th anniversary of the WTO protests there will be a lot going. There will be a Week of Action from November 27-December 5. Look them up at seattleplus10.org for more information about the events of this week. \r\n\r\nWorld Vegan Day is November 1. Get together and make a vegan meal with your friends, start a garden, do whatever you want to support this lifestyle of non-oppressive dining. Today is all about good food and good friends!\r\n\r\nDo not forget to vote! Local elections actually matter, like for real. So, remember to mail-in your ballot. Approve Referendum 71 to keep the domestic partnership law that provides legal protections for lesbian and gay couples and seniors in committed relationships. Everyone deserves healthcare! \r\n', 'November News', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'november-news', '', '', '2009-10-28 20:31:39', '2009-10-29 04:31:39', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=553', 0, 'post', '', 0),
