(557, 1, '2009-11-04 22:25:30', '2009-11-05 06:25:30', 'The venerable and crusty punk house FBK (originally "the Fire Breathing Kangaroo" - just to be annoying and poke fun at the long history of dumb punk house names that everyone''s lived at) has been hosting shows for a long time, and this is going to be a great cross section of some of the stuff that''s gone on there. RVIVR is a rad pop punk band that blends east-coast style anthems with west coast sentimental sensibilities (think early Hot Water Music meets Jawbreaker) and also clearly rep their back-woods Olympia home in a way that makes it so I can''t help but think about permaculture farms and home brew. Shamefully I''m not too familiar with Filth Matress, who I hear rule, but I''m also excited about The Witches Of, a two-piece that combines Bratmobile style guitar and singing with technical and dancey druming. This show will be all over the place, but definitely totally awesome.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://i42.photobucket.com/albums/e311/karlisyourfriend/rvivrflier2.jpg" border="0" alt="Rvivr Nov 6th!">', 'show at fbk', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'show-at-fbk', '', '', '2009-11-04 22:25:30', '2009-11-05 06:25:30', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=557', 0, 'post', '', 0),
