(560, 1, '2009-10-19 15:15:16', '2009-10-19 23:15:16', 'Hey dear friends,\r\nWe''re looking to have more people writing on this blog about all the amazing events and projects that are going on in this fabulous city. Would you perhaps like to join in the fun?\r\nWhat we''re looking for is people to write with some journalistic flair about events, activities, and projects in town that give more detail than the usual "time/location/cause" that we get on a calendar. We want to uncover the background, context, and detail that make up the DIY community. Specifically, we''d like to see more on this blog from different aspects of the movement - news about & from the DIY community, local sellers and craft community, underground hiphop, noise and improvisation, activism (especially of the anti-authoritarian kind), workshops and skill-shares, youth-led organizations and movements, reviews of past events, etc. \r\nIf you''re interested, register and make an account on this website (upper right side of the page, "register" link), and send us an email describing what you''re like to write about. Email us at sdiycollective at gmail dot com.', 'Bloggers wanted!', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '543-revision-2', '', '', '2009-10-19 15:15:16', '2009-10-19 23:15:16', '', 543, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=560', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(561, 1, '2009-11-09 12:50:21', '2009-11-09 20:50:21', '<a href="http://olyladiyfest.wordpress.com/"><img src="http://olyladiyfest.files.wordpress.com/2009/10/gj-header.jpg" width="400" height="150"alt="GenderJam!" /></a>\r\n\r\nGender Jam: LAD.I.Y. & TRANS FEST OLYMPIA 2009\r\nNovember 20th-22nd Downtown Olympia\r\n\r\nWe don''t normally post about things going on outside of Seattle, but maybe we should start giving some shout-outs to some regional DIY fun? Here''s a great one: a festival in celebration of efforts to create a supportive and safer community for women, transfolks, and generqueer people, with workshops and performances by regional notables! If you plan on attending or participating you should be sure to read about their values and how you can support them in ways that they want to be supported, or just come to the evening shows at the Studio on November 20th (8 PM) and 21st (9 PM) and at Rainy Day Records on the 21st (1:30-4:30 PM). Visit their website for more info: <a href="http://olyladiyfest.wordpress.com">http://olyladiyfest.wordpress.com</a>', 'Just around the corner, and not in Seattle (but close!): GenderJam!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'just-around-the-corner-and-not-in-seattle-but-close-genderjam', '', '', '2009-11-09 12:50:52', '2009-11-09 20:50:52', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=561', 0, 'post', '', 2),
