partnering with Central District businesses, residents, churches and schools to advocate for safety, in all its forms, within our community. The anonymous T-shirts will be made at Central District community hubs all week long. To find a location to make a shirt visit www.hidmo.org or stop by Hidmo (2000 S. Jackson Street) where we will be making shirts Dec 1st – 4th from 5:30 to 7:00pm. This neighborhood-wide effort is unique in that it seeks to bring together a community stratified, and often fragmented, by our differences. The overall goal of the forum is to continue the work that we are all doing to get to know each other better, to feel safer in our neighborhood and to empower our community.\r\n \r\nFor more information or questions about the upcoming forum or the Hidmo Community Empowerment Project please contact Jason Davison at jason@hidmo.org or 206-328-7088 ', 'repost: Three days of community events at Hidmo', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '588-revision-4', '', '', '2009-12-05 16:00:04', '2009-12-06 00:00:04', '', 588, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=593', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
