"0">\r\n\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 0, 51); font-size: 10pt;" rowspan="1" colspan="1" align="left">\r\n<div style="border-color: rgb(153, 0, 0); border-bottom: 1px dotted rgb(153, 0, 0); color: rgb(102, 0, 0); font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;" align="center"><font style="color: rgb(102, 0, 0); font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;" color="#660000" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" size="3"><b>S.O.S : Safety for Our Streets</b></font></div>\r\n<div align="center">Monday December 7th</div>\r\n<div align="center">6:00pm to 8:00pm</div>\r\n<div align="center">at Garfield Community Center </div>\r\n<div align="center">(2323 East Cherry Street)</div>\r\n<div align="center">open to all ages / free</div>\r\n<div align="center">childcare &amp; appetizers&nbsp;provided&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><img name="ACCOUNT.IMAGE.29" alt="Clothesline Project" src="http://origin.ih.constantcontact.com/fs006/1101970789218/img/29.jpg?a=1102859858659" width="200" align="left" border="0" height="215">Greetings Hidmo Friends, Family, and Community Partners:</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>We have been steadily planning the next Hidmo Community Empowerment Project Forum and would like to invite everyone in the community to take part!</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div></div>\r\n<div>SOS will be an interactive discussion designed to engage individuals in various ways about safety in the Central District. The forum will be the culmination of Hidmo CEP''s "The Central District Clothesline Project". Historically, the Clothesline Project was a way for women to use t-shirts and a clothesline to testify about violence that happens to them and their community, or that of someone they knew. You can find out more history at http://www.clotheslineproject.org/History.html. We are expanding this concept to all residents and members of the community, and are partnering with Central District businesses, residents, churches and schools to advocate for safety, in all its forms, within our community. The anonymous T-shirts will be made at Central District community hubs all week long. To find a location to make a shirt visit www.hidmo.org or stop by Hidmo (2000 S. Jackson Street) where we will be making shirts Dec 1st - 4th from 5:30 to 7:00pm. This neighborhood-wide effort is unique in that it seeks to bring together a community stratified, and often fragmented, by our differences. The overall goal of the forum is to continue the work that we are all doing to get to know each other better, to feel safer in our neighborhood and to empower our community.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>For more information or questions about the upcoming forum or the Hidmo Community Empowerment Project please contact Jason Davison at jason@hidmo.org or 206-328-7088', 'repost: Three days of community events at Hidmo', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '588-revision-2', '', '', '2009-12-05 15:52:34', '2009-12-05 23:52:34', '', 588, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=590', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
