(638, 98, '2010-01-14 15:06:01', '2010-01-14 23:06:01', '<p>\r\n<object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="400" height="300" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="data" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf?v=71377" /><param name="flashvars" value="intl_lang=en-us&amp;photo_secret=c65472370c&amp;photo_id=4273522760" /><param name="bgcolor" value="#000000" /><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="src" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf?v=71377" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="400" height="300" src="http://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf?v=71377" allowfullscreen="true" bgcolor="#000000" flashvars="intl_lang=en-us&amp;photo_secret=c65472370c&amp;photo_id=4273522760" data="http://www.flickr.com/apps/video/stewart.swf?v=71377"></embed></object>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tonight, at the New Crompton, we have some fine acts to present you with:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/iji" target="_blank">iji</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/jasonclackley" target="_blank">Jason Clackly</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/lordtaroth" target="_blank">Jehova''s Fitness</a> (san diego)</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/koalacaust" target="_blank">Koalacaust</a> (san-town bay)</li>\r\n	<li>Cowlick (0.5 of <a href="http://www.myspace.com/junkbones" target="_blank">Junk Bones</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Jason Clackly! You know, the fellow with the huge beard, punk-as-fuck, never needs a mic, who is also a gentlemanly scholar and sweetheart? That fellow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here''s what I''ve heard: Jason Clackly has a full band. That it''s brilliant and amplifies everything great about Jason''s songwriting, complimenting the emotional intensity of each song. This is what I''ve heard and what I''m going to see tonight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I''ve never seen iji perform before but from what I''ve listened to, it''s brilliant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come over this evening; have fun, see your friends, make new friends, and for the love of your ears- <em><strong>bring earplugs</strong></em>. This is going to be a very loud three hours. Please, bring money to support our touring friends from California- Jehova''s Fitness and Koalacaust.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?client=safari&amp;q=4711+12th+Ave+NE+Seattle,++WA++98105&amp;oe=UTF-8&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=4711+12th+Ave+NE,+Seattle,+King,+Washington+98105&amp;gl=us&amp;ei=36NPS4uaNoWGNtmC5Y8J&amp;ved=0CAgQ8gEwAA&amp;z=16" target="_blank">New Crompton<br />\r\n 4711 12th Ave NE<br />\r\n Seattle,  WA  98105</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Love,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-Kenneth-</p>', 'Tonight at New Crompton (01-14-2010)', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'iji-jason-clackly-jehovas-fitness-san-diego-koalacaust-bay-cowlick', '', '', '2010-01-14 15:09:29', '2010-01-14 23:09:29', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=638', 0, 'post', '', 0),
