(644, 98, '2010-01-16 17:56:33', '2010-01-17 01:56:33', '<p style="text-align: left;">This Tuesday (January, 19th) will be a very fantastic show at the <a href="http://www.theveraproject.org/" target="_blank">Vera Project</a> featuring these stellar acts:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/nanagrizol" target="_blank">Nana Grizol</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://tmle.terrorware.com/" target="_blank">The Max Levine Ensemble</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/iji" target="_blank">iji</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.myspace.com/amillionyearsago" target="_blank">A Million Years ago</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="425" height="344" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/QCINFfAvb6o&amp;color1=0xb1b1b1&amp;color2=0xcfcfcf&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feature=player_embedded&amp;fs=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="425" height="344" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/QCINFfAvb6o&amp;color1=0xb1b1b1&amp;color2=0xcfcfcf&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feature=player_embedded&amp;fs=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object>\r\n\r\nLast time Nana Grizol was in town (if I recall correctly), it was done as a small Pacific Northwest tour with backing band and tour partners <a href="http://www.myspace.com/yourheartbreaks" target="_blank">Your Heart Breaks</a>. These shows were played mostly in houses. <em>The time before that</em> Nana Grizol was on tour with a fabulous band called <a type="&quot;application/x-shockwave-flash&quot;" href="&lt;object width=&quot;425&quot; height=&quot;344&quot;&gt;&lt;param name=&quot;movie&quot; value=&quot;http://www.youtube.com/v/QCINFfAvb6o&amp;color1=0xb1b1b1&amp;color2=0xcfcfcf&amp;hl=en_US&amp;feature=player_embedded&amp;fs=1&quot;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name=&quot;allowFullScreen&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name=&quot;allowScriptAccess&quot; value=&quot;always&quot;&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;embed src=" target=" mce_src=">The Music Tapes</a>. That time The Music Tapes were his backing band and it was glorious. This time I''m just assuming that whoever is in The Max Levine Ensemble / Nana Grizol are each others backing bands and so on...\r\n\r\nComing from many years of being a part of concert band (in my more youthful days) I always feel like it''s a pleasure and rare experience a full band incorporated with horns. More so, I feel that incredibly strong lyrical emotions coupled with an emphasizing horn line is even more of a rare sight.\r\n\r\nYou don''t want to show up late for this show- each band is absolutely fantastic.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Also...</strong></em>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thekennethfoundation/4272767885/"><img class="aligncenter" title="Arts &amp; Crafts" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2701/4272767885_8d1b5afe50.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="338" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thekennethfoundation/4272767885/"></a>Before this show from 12:00 - 7:00 we will be having an arts &amp; crafts baking gathering / assembly / party / whatever you call it... We call it "Get Hella Baked with Quality Papers." It''s a baking, stationary, arts and crafts group.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Last Sunday when we did this there was band practice and jamming out upstairs and mega crafts downstairs. We also found a videotape of a funeral taken in the Philippines at the Goodwill Bins that we put on in the background.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If the weather''s fine, the plan is to assemble a bike posse to trek to the Vera in time for the show. We have an art closet with a some supplies but it''s encouraged to bring your own in case we don''t have it. We have a kitchen with spices, sugar, flour, and fluids but we''re not sure if our ingredients will meet your baking needs. We do have cupcake pans though.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?client=safari&amp;q=4531+5th+Ave+NE+Seattle,+WA+98105&amp;oe=UTF-8&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=4531+5th+Ave+NE,+Seattle,+King,+Washington+98105&amp;gl=us&amp;ei=QG5SS-vBCoOeswOR48CNCA&amp;ved=0CAgQ8gEwAA&amp;z=16" target="_blank">Pet Seminary\r\n4531 5th Ave NE\r\nSeattle, WA 98105</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Love,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">-Kenneth-</p>', 'Nana Grizol / Pre-Show Arts, Crafts, Baking', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nana-grizol-pre-show-arts-crafts-baking', '', '', '2010-01-16 18:07:46', '2010-01-17 02:07:46', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=644', 0, 'post', '', 0),
