(658, 99, '2010-01-17 14:05:07', '2010-01-17 22:05:07', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://akpress.org/images/cms/5481_popup.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" />\r\n\r\nShon Meckfessel, (local) author of <em><a href="http://akpress.org/2009/items/suffledhowitgushakpress">Suffled How It Gush: A North American Anarchist in the Balkans</a> </em>will be speaking and reading at <a href="http://www.leftbankbooks.com/store/History">Left Bank Books</a>, your local anarchist collective bookstore, on <strong>Saturday, January 23rd at 7 PM</strong>.  Come out and learn about the Balkans and anarchism!\r\n\r\nLeft Bank Books is located at <strong>92 Pike Street</strong> on the corner of First and Pike, right at the entrance of the Pike Place Market.\r\n\r\n"Shon Meckfessel bathes in undercurrent discourses and points us to Balkan dynamics contradicting the nationalist loyalties that distort people''s lives. Rather than making ethnic claims or endorsing any hierarchy, he clarifies existing struggles against states and points toward a region free of domination." —George Katsiaficas, activist and author of <em>Subversion of Politics: European Autonomous Social Movements and the Decolonization of Everyday Life</em>\r\n\r\nSEE YOU SATURDAY!', 'Author Shon Meckfessel this Saturday (1-23) at Left Bank Books!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fourth-hiker-and-author-shon-meckfessel-this-saturday-1-23-at-left-bank-books', '', '', '2010-01-19 13:28:15', '2010-01-19 21:28:15', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=658', 0, 'post', '', 0),
