(662, 99, '2010-01-17 14:04:11', '2010-01-17 22:04:11', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://akpress.org/images/cms/5481_popup.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" />\n\nShon Meckfessel, (local) author of <em><a href="http://akpress.org/2009/items/suffledhowitgushakpress">Suffled How It Gush: A North American Anarchist in the Balkans</a> </em>and the <a href="http://news.newamericamedia.org/news/view_article.html?article_id=05fd43739c3af58af94000fd7909eb45">"fourth hiker"</a> will be speaking and reading at <a href="http://www.leftbankbooks.com/store/History">Left Bank Books</a>, your local anarchist collective bookstore, on <strong>Saturday, January 23rd at 7 PM</strong>.  Come out and learn about the Balkans, anarchism, and the three hikers still being held by the Iranian government.\n\n"Shon Meckfessel bathes in undercurrent discourses and points us to Balkan dynamics contradicting the nationalist loyalties that distort people''s lives. Rather than making ethnic claims or endorsing any hierarchy, he clarifies existing struggles against states and points toward a region free of domination." —George Katsiaficas, activist and author of <em>Subversion of Politics: European Autonomous Social Movements and the Decolonization of Everyday Life</em>\n\n"Shon traveled with Shane Bauer, Sarah Shourd and Joshua Fattal from Damascus, Syria to Iraqi Kurdistan for a short vacation this summer. Shon stayed behind at the hotel nursing a cold, while his three friends left for a hike. On the morning of July 31st, he set out to join them near a waterfall, when Shane telephoned him to say that they had been detained.  [Shon has urged the Iranian president] to release his friends and to consider that each of them has a, quote, ''long and public record of contesting injustice in the world.''" -Amy Goodman, from <a href="http://www.democracynow.org/2009/11/2/exclusive_friend_of_american_hikers_detained">her interview with Shon on Democracy Now</a>', '"Fourth Hiker" and Author Shon Meckfessel this Saturday (1-23) at Left Bank Books', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '658-revision-3', '', '', '2010-01-17 14:04:11', '2010-01-17 22:04:11', '', 658, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=662', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(666, 243, '2010-01-19 16:38:03', '2010-01-20 00:38:03', 'Nana Grizol is playing the Vera tonight. If you''re reading this, drop everything and get over there! Mastermind Theo Zumm writes lyrics entwined with melody, thrashed by raw power. They''ll uplift, get your ass dancing, and leave you euphoric. Don''t miss this chance to see what life will be like in the future perfect. Plus they''re touring with the Max Levigne Ensemble.. They also play with iji and A Mllion Years Ago. Iji is the perfect band to play with the Griz tonite, they''re basically the local version, in Nana Grizol''s own words: "Just a bunch of friends having the most fun possible", plus they keep it horny...\r\n\r\nI really can''t stress enough the importance of realizing the scope of vision in the way that these kids bring it alive. Okay, enough words: NOW, PEOPLE, MOVE!', 'Tonite: Nana Grizol, iji, Max Levigne Ens, A Million Yrs Ago @ Vera: Just GO!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tonite-nana-grizol-iji-max-levigne-ens-a-million-yrs-ago-vera-just-go', '', '', '2010-01-19 16:38:03', '2010-01-20 00:38:03', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=666', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(663, 99, '2010-01-17 14:05:07', '2010-01-17 22:05:07', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://akpress.org/images/cms/5481_popup.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" />\r\n\r\nShon Meckfessel, (local) author of <em><a href="http://akpress.org/2009/items/suffledhowitgushakpress">Suffled How It Gush: A North American Anarchist in the Balkans</a> </em>and the <a href="http://news.newamericamedia.org/news/view_article.html?article_id=05fd43739c3af58af94000fd7909eb45">"fourth hiker"</a> will be speaking and reading at <a href="http://www.leftbankbooks.com/store/History">Left Bank Books</a>, your local anarchist collective bookstore, on <strong>Saturday, January 23rd at 7 PM</strong>.  Come out and learn about the Balkans, anarchism, and the three hikers still being held by the Iranian government.\r\n\r\nLeft Bank Books is located at <strong>92 Pike Street</strong> on the corner of First and Pike, right at the entrance of the Pike Place Market.\r\n\r\n"Shon Meckfessel bathes in undercurrent discourses and points us to Balkan dynamics contradicting the nationalist loyalties that distort people''s lives. Rather than making ethnic claims or endorsing any hierarchy, he clarifies existing struggles against states and points toward a region free of domination." —George Katsiaficas, activist and author of <em>Subversion of Politics: European Autonomous Social Movements and the Decolonization of Everyday Life</em>\r\n\r\n"Shon traveled with Shane Bauer, Sarah Shourd and Joshua Fattal from Damascus, Syria to Iraqi Kurdistan for a short vacation this summer. Shon stayed behind at the hotel nursing a cold, while his three friends left for a hike. On the morning of July 31st, he set out to join them near a waterfall, when Shane telephoned him to say that they had been detained.  [Shon has urged the Iranian president] to release his friends and to consider that each of them has a, quote, ''long and public record of contesting injustice in the world.''" -Amy Goodman, from <a href="http://