(665, 99, '2010-01-19 10:42:04', '2010-01-19 18:42:04', '<img class="alignnone" src="http://akpress.org/images/cms/5481_popup.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="600" />\r\n\r\nShon Meckfessel, (local) author of <em><a href="http://akpress.org/2009/items/suffledhowitgushakpress">Suffled How It Gush: A North American Anarchist in the Balkans</a> </em>and the <a href="http://news.newamericamedia.org/news/view_article.html?article_id=05fd43739c3af58af94000fd7909eb45">"fourth hiker"</a> will be speaking and reading at <a href="http://www.leftbankbooks.com/store/History">Left Bank Books</a>, your local anarchist collective bookstore, on <strong>Saturday, January 23rd at 7 PM</strong>.  Come out and learn about the Balkans, anarchism, and the three hikers still being held by the Iranian government.\r\n\r\nLeft Bank Books is located at <strong>92 Pike Street</strong> on the corner of First and Pike, right at the entrance of the Pike Place Market.\r\n\r\n"Shon Meckfessel bathes in undercurrent discourses and points us to Balkan dynamics contradicting the nationalist loyalties that distort people''s lives. Rather than making ethnic claims or endorsing any hierarchy, he clarifies existing struggles against states and points toward a region free of domination." —George Katsiaficas, activist and author of <em>Subversion of Politics: European Autonomous Social Movements and the Decolonization of Everyday Life</em>\r\n\r\n"Shon traveled with Shane Bauer, Sarah Shourd and Joshua Fattal from Damascus, Syria to Iraqi Kurdistan for a short vacation this summer. Shon stayed behind at the hotel nursing a cold, while his three friends left for a hike. On the morning of July 31st, he set out to join them near a waterfall, when Shane telephoned him to say that they had been detained.  [Shon has urged the Iranian president] to release his friends and to consider that each of them has a, quote, ''long and public record of contesting injustice in the world.''" -Amy Goodman, from <a href="http://www.democracynow.org/2009/11/2/exclusive_friend_of_american_hikers_detained">her interview with Shon on Democracy Now</a>', 'Author Shon Meckfessel this Saturday (1-23) at Left Bank Books', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '658-revision-5', '', '', '2010-01-19 10:42:04', '2010-01-19 18:42:04', '', 658, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=665', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(667, 243, '2010-01-19 16:37:50', '2010-01-20 00:37:50', 'Nana Grizol is playing the Vera tonight. If you''re reading this, drop everything and get over there! Mastermind Theo Zumm writes lyrics entwined with melody, thrashed by raw power. They''ll uplift, get your ass dancing, and leave you euphoric. Don''t miss this chance to see what life will be like in the future perfect. Plus they''re touring with the Max Levigne Ensemble.. They also play with iji and A Mllion Years Ago. Iji is the perfect band to play with the Griz tonite, they''re basically the local version, in Nana Grizol''s own words: "Just a bunch of friends having the most fun possible", plus they keep it horny...\n\nI really can''t stress enough the importance of realizing the scope of vision in the way that these kids bring it alive. Okay, enough words: NOW, PEOPLE!', 'Tonite: Nana Grizol, iji, Max Levigne Ens, A Million Yrs Ago @ Vera: Just GO!', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '666-revision', '', '', '2010-01-19 16:37:50', '2010-01-20 00:37:50', '', 666, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=667', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(668, 279, '2010-01-24 12:43:36', '2010-01-24 20:43:36', 'The Honk Fest West Benefit!\r\n\r\nFor the last two years, Honk Fest West has put marching bands, samba lines, horn players, drum corps,\r\nand every manner of rhythmic and melodic noisemaker we could find right where they belong: in the\r\nSeattle streets. And in 2010, we’re doing it again and bigger, as we bring the lively sounds of 23 bands\r\nfrom across the United States here for the third annual HONK! FEST! WEST!\r\nOur upcoming Benefit on Saturday, January 30 helps raise funds to offset these bands’ travel expenses.\r\n\r\nWhen: 8pm‐2am, Saturday January 30, 2010\r\n\r\nWhere: Underground Events Center, 2407 1st Ave\r\n\r\n(between Battery St &amp; Wall St), Seattle, WA\r\n\r\nCost: $10‐20 (sliding scale donation)\r\n\r\nThe following bands will be working their magic throughout the evening:\r\n\r\n<strong>Orkestar Zirkonium </strong>(http://www.orkestarzirkonium.com/) is a mobile fourteen‐piece brass‐punk band\r\n\r\nthat borrows the performative style and Balkan/klezmer‐influenced sounds from the greats of the Roma\r\n\r\ntradition, plunging into crowds and galvanizing joyous derangement in every time signature.\r\n\r\n<strong>Reptet</strong> (http://www.reptet.com/) is a genre bending band consisting of drums, bass and four horns,\r\n\r\nperforming original compositions that incorporate reggae, rock, ska, punk, modern classical, avant\r\n\r\ngarde, eastern European folk influences and more.\r\n\r\n<strong>Titanium Sporkestra</strong> (http://titaniumsporkestra.com/) features ex‐members of the Infernal Noise\r\n\r\nBrigade and legendary Seattle band TchKunG!, and delivers a blend of heavy world drumming and\r\n\r\ntraditional drum line music, tweaked just a little and turned up to 11.\r\n\r\n<strong>Tubaluba</strong> (http://www.myspace.com/tubalubabrassband) mixes New Orleans jazz, funky times, blues\r\n\r\nfor the soul, and groovy world sounds into beautiful music that makes you shake your booty and clap\r\n\r\nyour hands.\r\n\r\n<strong>Yellow Hat Band</strong> (http://www.yellowhatband.org) plays loud, fun music from all over the world, turning\r\n\r\nany room they occupy into an irresistible dance party.\r\n\r\nIn addition to our full band line‐up, we’ll also be holding an auction, accepting donations, and running a\r\n\r\ncash bar.\r\n\r\nThis year''s HonkFestWest will occur across the city from Friday April 9, 2010 through Sunday April 11,\r\n\r\n2010. Stay tuned for more details. For more information, and pictures and videos from previous years, please visit honkfestwest.com\r\n\r\nFor press inquiries, please contact Tyson Lynn at tyson.lynn@gmail.com or 425.879.6391.', 'Bring Out Your Brass!  A benefit concert and auction for Honk Fest West', 0, 'Orkestar Zirkonium, Reptet, Titanium Sporkestra, Tubaluba, and Yellow Hat Band play the HonkFestWest \r\nBenefit show at the Underground Events Center on Saturday, January 30.  \r\n', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bring-out-your-brass-a-benefit-concert-and-auction-for-honk-fest-west', '', '', '2010-01-24 12:43:36', '2010-01-24 20:43:36', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=668', 0, 'post', '', 0),
