(722, 272, '2010-02-24 18:05:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<em>Seattle Solidarity is a volunteer network of working people who believe in standing up for our rights. Our goal is to support our fellow workers'' strikes and struggles, build solidarity, and organize to deal with specific job, housing, and other problems caused by the greed of the rich and powerful.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Seattle Solidarity Network has been battling with a local real estate company (Lorig &amp; Associates) and, as a result, Lorig has filed a lawsuit.  They are attempting to silence the network, so they can continue "enhancing communities" (read "catering to rich, white people, while pushing around anyone who gets in their way"). </strong>\r\n\r\nHelp them raise some cash for legal fees!  They''re a completely volunteer-run group &amp; could really use your support.\r\n\r\n<strong>Saturday, February 27\r\nThe Big House</strong>\r\n(a large house in Capitol Hill - email bighouse@dodiy.org &amp; ask for the address)\r\n\r\n<strong>8:00PM</strong>\r\n\r\nMUSIC BY:\r\nThe Pica Beats\r\nThousands\r\nJoe Martin\r\nWet Paint\r\nThe Greatest Place To\r\n\r\n$8 at the door goes directly to Seattle Solidarity.\r\n\r\nNOTE FOR EVERYONE: Everyone will enter through the back door &amp; it is wheelchair accessible.  Only the basement (where most of the music will happen) is wheelchair accessible.  Please be kind to people with chemical &amp; scent sensitivies - Please Don''t Wear Scented Deodorant or Perfumes &amp; Don''t Smoke Near The Non-Smokers.  We''re trying to make this event accessible to as many people as we can, so please send an email to bighouse@dodiy.org if you need any accommodations.  Also Read This: <a href="http://www.scn.org/activism/calendar/disabilities.html">www.scn.org/activism/calendar/disabilities.html</a>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.dodiy.org/feb27benefit_web400px.jpg" alt="Poster for SeaSol Benefit">\r\n\r\n', 'Solidarity is FUN.', 0, '', 'pending', 'open', 'open', '', '', ''