(730, 201, '2010-02-26 18:15:36', '2010-02-27 02:15:36', '<strong><em>We''re baaaack!</em></strong>\r\n\r\n<a title="MySpace HTML Codes, Generators and more at ALLHTMLCODES.COM!" href="http://www.allhtmlcodes.com"><img src="http://www.benchmarkinstitute.org/t_by_t/free_stuff/free.jpg" alt="http://www.benchmarkinstitute.org/t_by_t/free_stuff/free.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\nYou thought the <strong>Really Really Free Market</strong> was lost and gone forever, didn''t you? You thought it had been washed away by the cold winter rains (er, mild winter sun) of Seattle''s most brutal season?\r\n\r\nWell, think again! <strong>The Really Really Free Market is actually REALLY really happening tomorrow!</strong>\r\n\r\nrain or freaking shine.\r\n\r\n<em><strong>the details:</strong></em>\r\n\r\nCome join us at <strong>Pratt Park</strong> (on 20th between Yesler and Jackson in the Central Area)! RRFM organizers will be there from <strong>noon to 4pm</strong>, but really it all depends on YOUR participation.\r\n\r\nThis is how it works: <strong>bring your freebox!</strong> Clothes, movies, music, house goods, snacks, shoes, whatever else that you no longer need and think someone might be able to use. Why buy new things when there is so much extra <em>stuff</em> just floating around our community? Everything is totally free, bring what you don''t want anymore, take away new finds. At the end of the day someone will scoop up everything left over and take it down to be donated to Lifelong AIDS Alliance.\r\n\r\nIt''s like the biggest free box of your dreams! Look for us tomorrow, you''ll see picnic tables covered with stuff (or if it''s raining, look for us under the covered area.\r\n\r\nSee you there!', 'Really Really Free Market, Saturday Feb. 27th!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'really-really-free-market-saturday-feb-27th', '', '', '2010-02-26 18:15:36', '2010-02-27 02:15:36', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=730', 0, 'post', '', 1),
