(741, 295, '2010-02-27 16:26:42', '2010-02-28 00:26:42', '<strong><em>Through This Window</em></strong> is a new quarterly collaborative web-based multimedia project created by a small group of artist friends here in Seattle. Every three months they aim to release a new installment around a unique and interesting theme or subject, exploring it from/through a wide range of points of view, mediums, and medias. <!--more-->\r\n\r\nThere are three main components to the website and project:  1) A significant video component, which might be compared to a short visual version of This American Life with a Northwest bent. Each theme/subject will be treated with multiple stories or angles in a variety of mediums or medias: interviews, poetry, fictional narrative shorts, music, animation, audio collages, etc.  2) The next essential aspect of each month''s release is the webzine portion. It''s aim is to complement and provide context for the video portion while providing an opportunity to post photographs, writing, paintings and/or other art in a standalone way, while contributing to a fuller story around the installment''s theme/subject.  3) The interactive component: There will be an open online gallery of submitted work for anybody to participate in the exploration of that installment''s theme/subject. It will remain open for submissions of all kinds indefinitely. You might compare this part of <em>TTW</em> to Miranda July''s "<a href="http://www.learningtoloveyoumore.com">Learning To Love You More</a>" project/website (that''s now, unfortunately, done.)\r\n\r\nOn March 1st, the first installment will be released to the world via <a href="http://www.ThroughThisWindow.com">the project website</a>. It is called "Unemployed!" and features a wide range of writing and art, including a short story from Ryan Boudinot, author of "Misconception" and "The Littlest Hitler," a video interview/documentary with/about Aaron Heideman of the "<a href="http://www.themaninavanproject.com">Man In A Van Project</a>"<a href="http://www.themaninavanproject.com/"></a>, animation, paintings, poetry, a comic, an interactive game, and more.\r\n\r\n<em>TTW</em> is currently accepting submissions of all kinds for the next installment, titled “Unrequited Love.” The deadline is May 15, 2010 and it will be released officially on June 1<sup>st</sup>.\r\n\r\nCheck out the official site at <a href="http://www.ThroughThisWindow.com">http://www.ThroughThisWindow.com</a> ... it''ll be changing pretty drastically on the 1st.\r\n\r\nBecome a fan on facebook: <a href="http://www.facebook.com/throughthiswindow">http://www.facebook.com/throughthiswindow</a>', '“Through This Window,” A Quarterly Webzine, Is Launching', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%e2%80%9cthrough-this-window%e2%80%9d-a-quarterly-webzine-is-launching', '', '', '2010-02-27 16:43:46', '2010-02-28 00:43:46', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=741', 0, 'post', '', 0),
