(772, 99, '2010-03-14 22:16:00', '2010-03-15 06:16:00', '<img src="http://www.akpress.org/images/cms/5734_popup.jpg" alt="Book Cover" />\r\nHey Seattle DIYers!\r\nIf you''ve got the time, head down to your favorite anarchist bookshop of horrors tomorrow, 3/15, to hear Matt Hern talk about his newest book, Common Ground In A Liquid City: Essays In Defense of an Urban Future.  Matt lives up in Vancouver, B.C., and is super-rad. He''s the author of the amazing Everywhere All The Time: A New Deschooling Reader, and the founder of the Purple Thistle Center up in Vancouver.  Besides being on the forefront of the deschooling movement and having radical politics, he''s also a professor at UBC, teaching about urban sustainability and city design.  Come hang with us tomorrow to talk about the scariness of corporate control, the promise of grassroots organizing, and the way to bring funky back. Also, Left Bank needs your love, so come hang out with us anyways. \r\n\r\nIt''s going to be SO GOOD. \r\n7:30PM @ LEFT BANK BOOKS\r\n92 Pike St.\r\n(1st &amp; Pike, next to the flower shop!)\r\n', 'Deschool Pioneer Matt Hern @ Left Bank 3/15!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'deschool-pioneer-matt-hern-at-left-bank-books-315', '', '', '2010-03-14 22:17:15', '2010-03-15 06:17:15', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=772', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(773, 99, '2010-03-14 22:16:00', '2010-03-15 06:16:00', 'Hey Seattle DIYers!\r\n<img src="http://www.akpress.org/images/cms/5734_popup.jpg" alt="Book Cover" />\r\nIf you''ve got the time, head down to your favorite anarchist bookshop of horrors tomorrow, 3/15, to hear Matt Hern talk about his newest book, Common Ground In A Liquid City: Essays In Defense of an Urban Future.  Matt lives up in Vancouver, B.C., and is super-rad. He''s the author of the amazing Everywhere All The Time: A New Deschooling Reader, and the founder of the Purple Thistle Center up in Vancouver.  Besides being on the forefront of the deschooling movement and having radical politics, he''s also a professor at UBC, teaching about urban sustainability and city design.  Come hang with us tomorrow to talk about the scariness of corporate control, the promise of grassroots organizing, and the way to bring funky back. Also, Left Bank needs your love, so come hang out with us anyways. \r\n\r\nIt''s going to be SO GOOD. \r\n7:30PM @ LEFT BANK BOOKS\r\n92 Pike St.\r\n(1st &amp; Pike, next to the flower shop!)\r\n', 'Deschool Pioneer Matt Hern at Left Bank Books 3/15', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '772-revision', '', '', '2010-03-14 22:16:00', '2010-03-15 06:16:00', '', 772, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=773', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(774, 302, '2010-03-16 20:27:04', '2010-03-17 04:27:04', '<img src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_Lgt_6u86SVg/S4cO10lVhjI/AAAAAAAAA-Q/b-L0ej-8WHE/s320/Maria+Talks+Tarot_edited-1_1024.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">Hi Everyone, </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">It''s time again for Report Night, this month March 26 starting at 6:30 at 936 20th Ave (up the porch and through the door on the left).</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">Of course the basic premise of Report Night is that you pick a topic of your choosing, have some type of learning aid to go with it (visual, audio, food, etc) and then you spend 5-10 minutes presenting on it. And really it can be anything. </span> \r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">Check out our blog at: </span><a href="http://seattlereportnight.blogspot.com/" target="_blank"><span style="font-family: Calibri;color: #0000ff;font-size: small"><span style="text-decoration: underline">http://seattlereportnight.blogspot.com/</span></span></a><span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small"> </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">If interested in reporting shoot me an e-mail back so I can add you to the list.</span> \r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">I usually write here that "you can''t come if you''re an asshole." And yes, please keep the ass-holery at home, but also we trying to promote a Safer Space (i.e. checking racist, homophobic, sexist, etc. comments) while also assuming positive intent. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">Shoot a response back for the head count, and feel free to pass the word along to anyone who''d be interested.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">Cheers!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small">Rebecca</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Calibri;font-size: small"> </span>', 'Report Night March 26', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'report-night-march-26', '', '', '2010-03-16 20:31:45', '2010-03-17 04:31:45', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=774', 0, 'post', '', 0),
