(779, 1, '2010-03-16 20:37:34', '2010-03-17 04:37:34', '<a href="http://www.thebikery.org">The Bikery</a> is hosting a forum - how does gender affect the bike community? \r\nSunday the 21st of March at 11am. Brunch provided! Bring a bowl and a fork. \r\n\r\nThis will be a really great event, and will certainly be a lively discussion. Come ready to engage in a conversation full of respect and candor. \r\n\r\nLocated at <a href="http://www.thebikery.org">The Bikery</a>: 1265 Main Street, #104, Seattle, WA 98144. This forum will occur in the conference rooms above The Bikery.\r\n\r\nAlso, this event is occuring at the the same time as a workshop at the Bikery about "<strong>Getting Back In The Saddle</strong>"\r\n"Haven''t ridden a bike since you were a kid, but looking to get "back in the saddle"? This is the class for you! We''ll go over information helpful to new cyclists like which bikes are best for which purpose, good places to buy bikes, what other equipment you need to get started, how to ride on streets, and we''ll have time to answer questions that you bring as well. The Bikery requests a $5-15 donation for class attendance, work trade accepted, but no one will be refused for lack of funds. For more information, visit www.thebikery.org or call us at (206) 568-3535."', 'Bike community gender forum', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bike-community-gender-forum', '', '', '2010-03-16 20:37:34', '2010-03-17 04:37:34', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=779', 0, 'post', '', 0),
