(784, 1, '2010-03-19 10:05:41', '2010-03-19 18:05:41', 'There are way too many things going on tonight. Here''s a preview of a few:\r\n\r\nHollow Earth Radio''s Magma Festiva - Radio8Ball Show!\r\n<blockquote>Karl Blau will performing songs chosen at random to answer your questions on the <strong>Radio8Ball Show</strong>!!\r\nHollow Earth Radio and the Henry Art Gallery present The Radio8Ball Show hosted by Andras Jones. With musical guest Karl Blau and a celebrity skype-in with a very special guest, amazing San Fran. author and performer, Michelle Tea.\r\nRadio8Ball: The Pop Oracle is a musical divination format where questions are answered by picking songs at random and interpreting the randomly chosen song as the answer to the question, like picking musical tarot cards.\r\nHenry Auditorium - $12 General | $6 for Henry Members | Included with Magma Fest Pass</blockquote>\r\n\r\nBirthDIYfest at the Vera Project:\r\n<blockquote>BirthDIYfest is an annual one-night all-ages concert & party which celebrates everyone who has a passion to help the NW DIY (do-it-yourself) creative community thrive. This year the date is Friday March 19th 2010 and the place is The Vera Project. There will be live performances by BOAT, Kay Kay & His Weathered Underground, Feral Children, Kids and Animals, and the Nextdoor Neighbors, as well as promotional tables for local DIY organizations, artists, venues, record labels, and more!\r\nw/\r\nBOAT | http://myspace.com/boatmusic\r\nKAY KAY & HIS WEATHERED UNDERGROUND | http://myspace.com/kaykayunderground\r\nFERAL CHILDREN | http://myspace.com/feralchildrenseattle\r\nKIDS AND ANIMALS | http://myspace.com/kidsandanimalsband\r\nTHE NEXTDOOR NEIGHBORS | http://myspace.com/theenextdoorneighbors</blockquote>\r\n\r\nAnd there''s a great show at the<a href="http://www.myspace.com/blacklodgemountain"> Black Lodge</a>:\r\n<blockquote>ALASKAS (Seattle)\r\nButts (Seattle)\r\nASSS (Portland)\r\nBrainstorm (Portland)\r\nStarskate (Santa Rosa, CA)\r\nALL AWESOME, ALL AGES.\r\n9ishpm, Cheapishdonations.\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nAnd late tonight is the 2nd ever Seattle Midnight Mystery Ride!\r\n<blockquote>For more info visit<a href="http://seattlemidnightmysteryride.wordpress.com"> http://seattlemidnightmysteryride.wordpress.com</a>\r\nMeet at 11pm at the Cantebury (15th and Mercer on Cap Hill)\r\nRide leaves PROMPTLY at Midnight. Sam is the leader this month- he will take us somewhere fun and mysterious!\r\nPlease remember this is a social ride- so please don''t go too fast. The Mystery Ride is for bike jocks and bike novices alike.\r\nSee you in the dark!</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'SO MUCH going on tonight', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'so-much-going-on-tonight', '', '', '2010-03-19 10:05:41', '2010-03-19 18:05:41', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=784', 0, 'post', '', 0);
