(802, 201, '2010-03-27 10:53:12', '2010-03-27 18:53:12', '<img alt="" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_E8BpJEni77I/SDcBqteUVNI/AAAAAAAACUk/q12u30WMUlY/s400/free-stuff.jpg.gif" class="aligncenter" width="400" height="286" />\n\nIs your freebox overflowing with recently unburied treasure? Are you doing your spring cleaning and have some weird/wonderful things you need to get off your hands? Are you in desperate need of some totally free clothes, movies, books, CDs, household goods, instruments, etc etc?\n\nJust as I suspected! \n\nWell, the Really Really Free Market (aka the answer to all your prayers) is really really happening today!\n\nthe details:\n\nCome join us at Pratt Park (on 20th between Yesler and Jackson in the Central Area)! RRFM organizers will be there from noon to 4pm, but really it all depends on YOUR participation.\n\nThis is how it works: bring your freebox! Clothes, movies, music, house goods, snacks, shoes, whatever else that you no longer need and think someone might be able to use. Why buy new things when there is so much extra stuff just floating around our community? Everything is totally free, bring what you don’t want anymore, take away new finds. At the end of the day someone will scoop up everything left over and take it down to be donated to Lifelong AIDS Alliance.\n\nIt’s like the biggest free box of your dreams! Look for us tomorrow, you’ll see picnic tables covered with stuff (or if it’s raining, look for us under the covered area.\n\nSee you there!', 'Really Really Free Market at Pratt Park, TODAY!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'really-really-free-market-at-pratt-park-today', '', '', '2010-03-27 10:53:12', '2010-03-27 18:53:12', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=802', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(803, 99, '2010-03-30 12:34:31', '2010-03-30 20:34:31', '<strong>Wednesday, April 7th at 7:30 PM\r\nAt <a href="http://www.leftbankbooks.com">Left Bank Books</a>\r\n92 Pike Street</strong>\r\n\r\n<img alt="" src="http://farm1.static.flickr.com/33/54901206_cabedd151f.jpg" class="alignnone" width="500" height="375" />\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.lasthours.org.uk/archive/interviews/peter-gelderloos/">Peter Gelderloos</a>--author of <a href="http://www.akpress.org/2005/items/hownonviolenceprotectsthestate">How Non-Violence Protects the State</a>, <a href="http://www.akpress.org/2006/items/consensusanewhandbookforgrassrootspolitical">Consensus</a>, and the newly published <a href="http://littleblackcart.com/index.php?main_page=product_book_info&amp;products_id=527">Anarchy Works</a>--will be speaking at Left Bank Books on Democracy as Totalitarianism.  Peter will analyze democracy as a creation of the elite and an evolution from obviously authoritarian forms of governance that allows for greater control of people''s beliefs and lives.  We will explore the anarchist proposition that all government--including democracy--is authoritarian and a force for domination and thought-control.\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Democracy as Totalitarianism: Peter Gelderloos Speaks at Left Bank Books', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'democracy-as-totalitarianism-peter-gelderloos-speaks-at-left-bank-books', '', '', '2010-03-30 12:34:31', '2010-03-30 20:34:31', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=803', 0, 'post', '', 1),
