(835, 96, '2010-04-01 16:31:12', '2010-04-02 00:31:12', '<img src="http://profile.ak.fbcdn.net/object2/1327/22/n104000282971116_405.jpg" alt="" />\r\nMost of us would agree that the D.I.Y. music community is alive and thriving, but what about other art forms. A space like Healthy Times Fun Club has potential much further then only doing concerts and I am so excited that this friday they will be hosting a new musical by Shelby Turner (recent seattle transplant from Olympia and member of Sundance Kids, Megabog and iji).\r\nThe Truly Magnificent Bob Story follows the worlds most optimistic pizza delivery guy as he overcomes problems at home, black magic, and severe world wide environmental disasters. Could this be the worlds first Posi-Pizza Performance? I had the pleasure of seeing the play  when it was performed in Idaho last month and it blew my mind. I offered this quote for the flyer "The best play I have ever seen." For real.\r\n\r\nFri April 2nd\r\nHealthy Times Fun Club\r\n8:00 $5\r\n\r\nThe half hour play featuring Derek Ryan-Hain and Emily Popp will be followed by Music from An Earth-Like World-Like Earth, Christopher Francis and Son (olympia) and Slow Trucks (san fransisco).\r\n\r\nDon''t miss this one dudez', 'The Truly Magnificent Bob Story', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-truly-magnificent-bob-story', '', '', '2010-04-01 16:38:40', '2010-04-02 00:38:40', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=835', 0, 'post', '', 1),
