(839, 1, '2010-04-03 09:55:19', '2010-04-03 17:55:19', 'I love going to shows at nontraditional venues. Tonight is a tough decision, though. First, there''s the very awesome looking <a href="http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=816">MakeShift Reclamation event</a> (a multi-media event exploring feminist ideas around gender oppression and current events). But also tonight are shows featuring lo-fi young performers at <a href="http://2020cycle.com/">20/20 Cycle</a> - one of the best bike shops and performance spaces around - and a show at "<a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/Seattle-WA/The-Bread-Factory-Seattle-WA/10150133182495332">The Bread Factory</a>", on 20th and Jackson near Moonlight Cafe and Hidmo. Is this actually a bread factory? Is the show taking place in the Franz warehouse, or is it just inspired by their neighbors. Only one way to find out!\r\nOf course, if getting brutal is more your thing, you can always check out Ludicra at <a href="http://www.myspace.com/themorgueseattle">The Morgue</a>. Fuck dude, Srsly brtl.\r\n\r\n--------------------------\r\nRelease show for HY006 `The Water From the Well` - by Generifus\r\nwith Generifus, Cap Lori and Alaskas performing\r\nAll Half Yogurt releases will be available including Generifus, Cap Lori, Alaskas, Half Yogurt, Spencer Moody, Ed Askew, Dennis Driscoll and more.\r\n<a href="http://www.halfyogurt.com/">http://www.halfyogurt.com/</a>\r\n<a href="http://www.generifus.com/">http://www.generifus.com/</a>\r\nSaturday april 3, 8pm @ <a href="http://2020cycle.com/">20/20 Cycle</a> - 2020 east union, seattle, wa\r\n\r\n---------------------\r\n<img src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4063/4423050171_136e24442c_m.jpg" alt="" />\r\nORIGAMI GHOSTS\r\nW E B E L O S\r\niji\r\nSLASHED TIRES\r\n1985\r\n\r\nFirst Saturday Music Night @ The Bread Factory.\r\nBring some food or drinks or money or all three.\r\nFun City: Population YOU!\r\n\r\nWe will feed you veggie chili till you fart a 6.0 on the Rictor Scale. ', 'Events on Saturday night, 4/3/10!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'events-on-saturday-night-4310', '', '\nhttp://www.seattlediy.com/?p=816', '2010-04-03 09:55:19', '2010-04-03 17:55:19', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=839', 0, 'post', '', 0),
