(845, 1, '2010-04-05 21:42:15', '2010-04-06 05:42:15', 'A local writer for the website Examiner.com has been <a href="http://www.examiner.com/x-42204-Seattle-DIY-Examiner~y2010m3d23-What-is-DIY-Getting-started-with-the-Seattle-DIY-and-craft-community">profiling a number of great DIY projects and activities</a> lately, and I dug the most <a href="http://www.examiner.com/x-42204-Seattle-DIY-Examiner~y2010m4d5-Do-it-together-Using-your-skills-to-give-back">recent post</a> especially. Part of what I really love about the DIY community is not just the part where someone decides to "do it yourself", but when people encourage the community to work collaboratively and "Do It Together"! In the spirit of "D.I.T.", Audrey, the author of these posts, has <a href="http://www.examiner.com/x-42204-Seattle-DIY-Examiner~y2010m4d5-Do-it-together-Using-your-skills-to-give-back">suggested a number of projects</a> like <a href="http://www.scn.org/foodnotbombs">Food Not Bombs</a> or <a href="http://www.thebikery.org/">The Bikery</a> or <a href="http://www.seattlefreeschool.org/">Seattle Free School</a> that are great to get involved in that empower whole communities. \r\n\r\nI would suggest a number of other cool projects that people can get involved in, like <a href="http://bikeworks.org/">Bike Works</a>, <a href="http://www.alleycatacres.com/">Alleycat Acres</a>, <a href="http://justiceworks.info/">Justice Works!</a>, or <a href="http://bookstoprisoners.net/">Books To Prisoners</a>. ', 'Do It Together projects in Seattle!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'do-it-together-projects-in-seattle', '', '', '2010-04-05 21:42:15', '2010-04-06 05:42:15', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=845', 0, 'post', '', 0),
