(900, 1, '2010-04-16 11:53:13', '2010-04-16 19:53:13', 'Some great people have organized an incredible looking event on April 24th on Capitol Hill. They''re calling it Earth Day Free Day, which is looking to be a great mix of elements, ranging from a Really Really Free Market, a convergence of noisemakers (bring drums and instruments!), a potluck, and a trading-post of sorts. This will be taking place at the "parking lot" on Pine & Belmont, the empty gravel yard where numerous small businesses once thrived until local developers decided to bulldoze the entire block, then back out on replacing it with anything.\r\nI, for one, will be there with bells on. Here''s the relevant info:\r\n\r\n<img src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_rMyJ-IxaNe8/S8ZQzwXSlbI/AAAAAAAAANg/blKycjUhqBU/s1600/edfd+ppl.jpg" alt="" />\r\nhttp://peoplesparkinglot.blogspot.com/\r\n"Earth Day Free Day: A community celebration, potluck style\r\n\r\nOn April 24, Capitol Hillsters will be able to do something they''re not usually allowed to do: take over the vacant space on East Pine. The empty gravel lot, lodged between Belmont and Summit, is typically off limits. No trespassing allowed. It’s a hard reality for some to swallow, as this block used to be home of some of the neighborhood’s best bars and nightlife. But on April 24th we get to take this space back. People''s Parking Lot has been granted permission to throw a huge public gathering there.\r\n\r\nIn honor of Earth Day, I propose that we come together as a community to celebrate being here. Getting together, meeting your neighbors and celebrating as a community is greatly beneficial to our world. So come dance, sing, create and communicate with us in the gravel lot on Sat. April, 24.\r\n\r\nWe’ll be loosely organizing, but the main goal here is to make it an event we create together, just by showing up and sharing. If you’re a musician, bring your instrument. If you’re an artist, consider the lot your outdoor studio for the day, if you’re a baker or chef, bring us a taste of your latest creation, if you’re a dancer, think of the lot as your studio, if you love to talk and speak your mind, come find someone to chat with.\r\n\r\nWe’ll be trying to invite barter and really, really free market folks so that there is an element of free stuff as well as free service.\r\n\r\nPlease save the date! Come help celebrate your community and your place in the world. If you can help in any way, have an idea, or just want to get in touch, please let me know.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nSarah Kuck"\r\n\r\n(Here''s the <a href="http://www.facebook.com/event.php?eid=10150140364840317">facebook invite page</a>, and here''s <a href="http://peoplesparkinglot.blogspot.com/">their website</a>!)', 'April 24th - Earth Day Free Day!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'april-24th-earth-day-free-day', '', '', '2010-04-16 11:53:13', '2010-04-16 19:53:13', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=900', 0, 'post', '', 0);
