(932, 99, '2010-05-05 14:15:33', '2010-05-05 22:15:33', '<em>The following text is from a leaflet distributed at the <a href="http://nobudgetcutsuw.blogspot.com/p/may-3-strike-pledge.html">May 3rd Campus Strike Against Budget Cuts at the University of Washington.</a> Following the text are few links for further readings and resources for getting involved.</em>\r\n\r\nOur bones shift as the professor begins a lecture as stiff and common as this molded plastic seat. We just woke up for class but are already bored. This is routine. This morning’s class is as bitter and over-priced as our burnt coffee. We’ve swallowed this so many mornings that we have forgotten a life beyond daily schedule. This morning’s class, a meeting, another class, and then ‘free’ time. We once held the illusions of higher education; now we hold iphones. We are resigned to facebook profiles to check in with friends that we are actually too busy to meet. We chat with our friends about how much longer we will endure this regime. How many more quarters until we receive the brand name stamp, the university graduate insignia, next to our name? We’ve become utterly disillusioned. Recently there’s been some momentum behind a student and working movement with a specific set of demands aimed at reforming a system we would rather seek to abolish: the university as an institution that integrates us into the spectacle—that is, our lives as separated from and presented to us for our passive consumption. We do not want to reform and improve it; death by any other name has the same stench.\r\n\r\n<em><a href="http://arcticcirclecollective.info/articles/8/what-we-demand-instead-is-life">Continue Reading...</a>\r\n</em>', 'What We Demand, Instead, Is Life', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-we-demand-instead-is-life', '', '', '2010-05-05 14:16:42', '2010-05-05 22:16:42', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=932', 0, 'post', '', 5),
