(952, 1, '2010-05-22 14:46:23', '2010-05-22 22:46:23', 'Tonight there''s several amazing shows at cool DIY spaces. First, The Greenhouse is doing their final shows series, and tonight is going to be a great event celebrating an end to a long tradition of putting on incredible shows at that house. Tonight''s show features a few artists who have been a strong part of both The Greenhouse and the broader DIY community, and it''s a perfect opportunity to join in and see a fitting end to a long tradition of amazing events. The bands tonight are:\r\nOrca Team (http://www.myspace.com/orcateamband)\r\nPWRFL Power (http://www.myspace.com/pwrflpower)\r\nPill Wonder (http://www.myspace.com/pillwonder)\r\nBryan Appleby (http://www.myspace.com/bryanjohnappleby)\r\n\r\nAll-ages! Doors @ 8pm. Show @ 9pm. $5 suggested donation.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://c2.ac-images.myspacecdn.com/images02/114/l_8f76a3db5cb9427eb49acb45bb1c0051.jpg" width="350" alt="" />\r\n\r\n\r\nThe other undoubtedly amazing event tonight is at Healthy Times Fun Club, featuring the band Good Luck! from Bloomington, Indiana. They''re a rare creature - full of technical skill and incredible musicianship, but still filled to the brim with earnestness and heart, making them one of the most exciting and captivating bands around right now. The other bands playing this show are also some of the finest that Seattle has to offer, so this show is really one not to miss. The lineup is: \r\nGood Luck: http://www.myspace.com/wearegoodluck or http://www.facebook.com/wearegoodluck\r\nAgatha: http://www.myspace.com/agatha206\r\nA Million Years Ago: http://www.myspace.com/amillionyearsago\r\nMega Bog: http://www.myspace.com/megabog\r\nNeed directions? email healthytimesfunclub at gmail dot com.\r\n\r\n<img src="http://seattlediy.com/images/goodluckshow.jpg" alt="Good Luck at Healthy Times Fun Club" />\r\n\r\n', 'Several great shows tonight!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'several-great-shows-tonight', '', '', '2010-05-22 1