(970, 1, '2010-05-24 10:53:49', '2010-05-24 18:53:49', '<img src="http://img341.imageshack.us/img341/5163/img5715w.jpg" alt="" />\r\n\r\nWe are not always a party.  But we do live, grow, dance, eat, laugh and play together every day in defiance of a society that moves continually towards isolation and fragmentation.  Come live with us!\r\n\r\nWe are a 14 person collective living in a big blue house in the University District.\r\n\r\nWe live cooperatively, sharing the work, cost, and care of living together.\r\n\r\nWe try to make our home a safe space, and to minimize the presence of transphobia, racism, ableism, sexism, homophobia and other oppressive language and actions.  We are striving to create an autonomous space free from oppression and fear!\r\n\r\nWe value:\r\n\r\n-       sharing skills and knowledge\r\n\r\n-       critical discourse and discovery\r\n\r\n-       an awareness of one’s own privilege\r\n\r\n-       consensus-based decision making\r\n\r\n-       art and reclamation of public spaces\r\n\r\n-       breaking down hierarchies\r\n\r\n-       sharing vegan meals\r\n\r\n-       listening to and playing music\r\n\r\n-       bicycles\r\n\r\n-       growing our own food\r\n\r\n-       having monthly community potlucks\r\n\r\n-       activism\r\n\r\nWe share nightly dinners (each member is required to cook twice a month).  Members contribute to our chore and house work system, attend two house meetings a month, and go on retreats twice a year.\r\n\r\nOur average base rent is around $450/month, with cost varying according to room size and location. There is a deposit of $700 (payment options are available). We share the costs of vegetarian and mostly organic food, mortgage, property tax, maintenance, utilities, local phone, and DSL. In total this costs around $150 in addition to the base room cost.  Total membership dues at this time range from $593-654.\r\n\r\nWe have open spaces beginning in July and continuing through summer and fall!\r\n\r\nIf you are curious about membershipping, please contact us at sherwoodcooperative@gmail.com. We ask that all interested members come to three house dinners, write a letter of intent, have a one-on-one conversation with a house member, and then attend a membership meeting.  Please only contact us if you are willing to fully participate in our labor and expense sharing system and if you are looking to stay for at least a year.\r\n\r\nWe would love to meet you!\r\n\r\n- the Sherwood Coop\r\n\r\nFor more information, check out our website: http://sherwoodcooperative.org/\r\n\r\n*POTLUCK this Thursday at 7PM at 4746 18th ave NE.  Come hang out!*﻿', 'Live cooperatively!  Sherwood seeks new roomates!', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '960-revision-5', '', '', '2010-05-24 10:53:49', '2010-05-24 18:53:49', '', 960, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=970', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(971, 1, '2010-05-27 12:29:43', '2010-05-27 20:29:43', 'The fine local blog <a href="http://www.veganscore.com/">Vegan Score</a> has posted this week about an excellent looking film that''s going to be screened at the <a href="http://www.nwfilmforum.org/">Northwest Film Forum</a> in late June. Be sure to watch the trailer, attend the screening, and support these great activist filmmakers.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.veganscore.com/2010/05/vegan-activism-on-big-screen-in-seattle.html">See there original post here!</a>\r\n\r\n"Ladies and Gentleman, another vegan-friendly event is headed our way: the Seattle premier screening of <a href="http://boldnative.com/">Bold Native</a>, a film <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">about </span>animal activism in multiple forms, but made for <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">everyone  </span>- activists, pacifists, vegans, animal abolitionists, omnivores, vegetarians, politicians, cyclists, Sumarians (ok, well, maybe not that many Sumarians). Everyone. All of us.<br><br>Those of us who avoid eating animals for the animals'' sake are used to good documentaries on the topic: <a href="http://www.earthlings.com/">Earthlings</a>, <a href="http://peaceablekingdomfilm.org/">Peaceable Kingdom</a>, Meet your Meat,  <a href="http://www.witnessfilm.org/">The Witness</a>, A Cow at My Table, etc. but this time it is different: Bold Native is a <span style="font-style: italic; font-weight: bold;">full length fictional dramatic film</span>.<br><br><object width="425" height="340"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/EB0ITQfWjfk&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x006699&amp;color2=0x54abd6"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/EB0ITQfWjfk&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x006699&amp;color2=0x54abd6" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="340"></object><br><br>The topic of activists who are labeled terrorists by the US Government couldn''t be more important, timely, or relevant to Seattle. Intrepid speaker and Seattle resident, Josh Harper, (who was himself sentenced to 3 years in prison for animal activism under the Animal Enterprise Terrorism Act), will hopefully speak or be available for Q&amp;A after the film. Here is Josh talking about his experience before his imprisonment.<br><br><object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/0KkC3oFccXM&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x006699&amp;color2=0x54abd6"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/0KkC3oFccXM&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x006699&amp;color2=0x54abd6" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></object><br><br>There will be an early screening at 7:00 pm and a later screening at 9:00 pm on Tuesday June 29, 2010. Each screening will include some Q&amp;A with special guests. This is a rare opportunity to participate in dialog about activism, direct action, and the persecution (and prosecution) of activists by our government.<br><br>I like anything that brings together good art, thoughtful purpose, and real stories about people walking the walk.<br><br>You don''t have to be an activist yourself to appreciate the courage and fortitude that men and women have shown by speaking out to change national and global opinions (and occasionally even change the law). You also don''t have to be into direct action to enjoy a well made independent film, so invite you friends and lovers. There may be some other activities before and after the screenings, so  stay tuned. We''ll all have a good time.<br><br>Tickets are already on sale, so <a href="http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1422">mosey your mouse here</a> to buy some. Really. See you there.<br><br>Where: <a href="http://www.nwfilmforum.org/live/page/calendar/1422">Northwest Film Forum</a><br>1515 12th Ave, Seattle, (between Pike &amp; Pine)<br>Date: Tuesday, June 29, 2010<br>Time: 7:00 pm or 9:00 pm"', 'Bold Native screening in June @ NWFF', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bold-native-screening-in-june-nwff', '', '', '2010-05-27 12:29:43', '2010-05-27 20:29:43', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=971', 0, 'post', '', 1),
