(976, 201, '2010-05-29 08:51:00', '2010-05-29 16:51:00', '<img alt="" src="http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/4/a/highres_8733354.jpeg" title="FREEE!" class="aligncenter" width="500" height="375" />\n\nIs your freebox overflowing with recently unburied treasure? Are you doing your spring cleaning and have some weird/wonderful things you need to get off your hands? Are you in desperate need of some totally free clothes, movies, books, CDs, household goods, instruments, etc etc?\n\nJust as I suspected!\n\nWell, the Really Really Free Market (aka the answer to all your prayers) is really really happening today!\n\nthe details:\n\nCome join us at Pratt Park (on 20th between Yesler and Jackson in the Central Area)! RRFM organizers will be there from noon to 4pm, but really it all depends on YOUR participation.\n\nThis is how it works: bring your freebox! Clothes, movies, music, house goods, snacks, shoes, whatever else that you no longer need and think someone might be able to use. Why buy new things when there is so much extra stuff just floating around our community? Everything is totally free, bring what you don’t want anymore, take away new finds. At the end of the day someone will scoop up everything left over and take it down to be donated to Lifelong AIDS Alliance.\n\nIt’s like the biggest free box of your dreams! Look for us tomorrow, you’ll see picnic tables covered with stuff (or if it’s raining, look for us under the covered area.\n\nSee you there!', 'Really Really Free Market TODAY at Pratt Park, 12-4pm! Wheeeee!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'really-really-free-market-today-at-pratt-park-12-4pm-wheeeee', '', '', '2010-05-29 08:51:00', '2010-05-29 16:51:00', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=976', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(977, 14, '2010-05-30 14:29:45', '2010-05-30 22:29:45', '<img src="http://homegrown.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/02/dscn1698.jpg" height="50%" width="50%">\n\nonce upon a time, we hosted a weekly craft night at dancylvania. eventually it turned into "craft &amp; conspiracy", which was mostly just a couple of folks watching the x-files from the beginning. with many other projects and meetings and work and life, the gathering died out. \n\nwe''d like to start it up again, but with more of a focus on skillsharing, and less of scully''s delicious power pant-suits. (well, maybe we''ll keep those.) maybe you''ve got fixing old electronics down, brew ginger beer, have some sexy spanish skills, want to spread wheatpasting tactics, or you make a mean risotto -- so share it! \n\nthe first gathering will be <b>monday, june 7th at dancylvania from 7-9pm</b>. from there, we can pick a regular time that works for most folks, and decide how often it will happen, and the structure. if you want to know more, you can comment here or email dancylvania [at] gmail [dot] com!', 'skillshare at dancylvania', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'skillshare-at-dancylvania', '', '', '2010-05-30 14:29:45', '2010-05-30 22:29:45', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=977', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(978, 1, '2010-06-01 11:19:32', '2010-06-01 19:19:32', '<img src="http://c2.ac-images.myspacecdn.com/images02/30/l_272a440666d04f318748222cc0601545.jpg" width="300" alt="" />\r\n\r\nThe mighty-awesome folks at <a href="http://www.myspace.com/blacklodgemountain">The Black Lodge</a>, a really great DIY warehouse space, have just recently worked out a new deal with continuing their lease. However, this also means that they''ll be responsible for fronting a sizable amount of cash to pay for structural work on their space. Please attend their shows coming up, especially any benefit shows. We''ll keep you all up to date with any other ways of supporting them in the near future.\r\n\r\nHere''s their statement from their blog:\r\n\r\n"Fellow Black Lodgers, Seattle musicians, and other counter culture patrons,\r\n\r\nAs many of you know The Black Lodge has been in a state of uncertainty for many months. We have been unorganized, under stress, and most noticeably unwilling to book future shows. The reason for all of this is because our old landlord was trying to sell his lease, or as we call it, The Black Lodge. Why? Amongst other reasons we believe it is because there are some structural issues in this space that he wasn’t prepared to resolve.\r\n\r\nSo began a long process of determining if we could, should, would take the lease. We were definitely not the only people considered for taking the space. We sat through several tours of other people coming through the space considering what they would do with it once they had it. Every day for months we had no idea whether we were going to be booted out or if we were going to be allowed to stay. After a long and stressful process we have obtained the lease for The Black Lodge, outright. Now we have to deal with these structural issues!\r\n\r\nWith no middle man complicating the process you can expect a different attitude here at The Black Lodge. Over the next three years we will be renovating the space. We will also be seeking support from the community to help us in these efforts. We are in the beginning stages of creating a series of Black Lodge benefit shows. We are looking for bands and individuals to volunteer at these to keep the renovations on track.\r\n\r\nThanks for all the continued support,\r\n\r\n-The Black Lodge-"', 'To the future of The Black Lodge!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'to-the-future-of-the-black-lodge', '', '', '2010-06-01 11:19:32', '2010-06-01 19:19:32', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=978', 0, 'post', '', 0),
