(1133, 98, '2010-07-20 21:08:30', '2010-07-21 05:08:30', 'There''s this great fellow who has the name of Ed Halliday. He has been wanting to receive submissions for a spoken word tape compilation for a few months now but so far only has one. He''d like more.\r\n\r\nIn a nutshell, this compilation will be predominantly spoken word pieces that can have any assortment of accompaniment with it. Has anyone ever heard of a band called <strong>Kicking Giant</strong>? There''s this absolutely brilliant spoken word song called <em>The Town Idiot</em> that is pretty much my favorite spoken word song / piece ever (aside from everything that I''ve seen <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/thekennethfoundation/4719213931/" target="_blank">Elissa Ball</a> present as of lately).\r\n\r\nYou don''t have to be a band, established or recognized artist to do this. If you are thinking about submitting anything, you should probably just do it.\r\n\r\nThis is a good thing.\r\n\r\nYou can converse with Ed about this and submit material via his email <a href="mailto:zebrajones01@gmail.com" target="_blank">zebrajones01@gmail.com</a>', 'Submit Spoken Word Pieces for a Compilation!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'submit-spoken-word-pieces-for-a-compilation', '', '', '2010-07-20 21:08:30', '2010-07-21 05:08:30', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1133', 0, 'post', '', 1),
