(1053, 201, '2010-06-21 09:41:55', '2010-06-21 17:41:55', ' Is June 24th- June 27th\n\n________________________________________\n\n \n\nThis year of Seattle’s favorite radical free, queer and all-ages festival in June is more exciting than ever! On Thursday the 24th at Black Lodge (Eastlake & Republican) at 8pm we are partnering with the amazing femmes of F.U.S.S (Femme Unity + Support Seattle) for aQueer Carnival and Dance Party. On Friday the 25th in Cal Anderson Park on Capitol Hill we will have a “Queer Garden: Bands in the Park” with music starting at 3pm, followed by a screening of Travel Queeries at Dusk with local shorts. Friday music featuring The Redwood Plan, Hail Seizures, Black Letter Edition, Junk Bones, Cloudbustr, Council of Lions, Emma, and Christian Mailloux. Saturday the 26th will also be held in Cal Anderson Park starting with Big Gay Field Day at noon featuring personalized rubber ducky races, giant twister, hula hoops, and other fun favorites. Saturday evening we will have our Variety Showstarting at 6pm featuring ArtStar, queerbait!, Scarlett Vain, Dominique Eyesli D’Amour and more! And finally Sunday the evening of the 27th we will wind it down with“Unaccessorized: ‘Acoustic’ and Spoken Word” at 7pm at the Richard Hugo Housefeaturing S (Jenn Ghetto), charliesque, Heart Behavior, Shanay Salas, Henry Luke, young stay young (formerly overcome by the power of love), and more! The Hugo House is on 11thbetween Olive and Pine across the back-in parking from Cal Anderson. Don’t miss this festival of a lifetime!\n\n \n\nAll events are free of charge with free vegan meals.\n\n \n\nIf you have time to help out before or during the festival, contact us!!! We need lots of help for fliering and other outreach, food preparation during the festival, set up/break down, and other jobs. Come make it happen!\n\n \n\nBend-It is a queer artist activist collective that makes the world a more fabulous place by building welcoming, liberated spaces, strengthening community, and creating meaningful alternatives for queer people of all ages and their friends.', 'Bend-It Extravaganza 2010 ', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bend-it-extravaganza-2010', '', '', '2010-06-21 09:41:55', '2010-06-21 17:41:55', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1053', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1054, 327, '2010-06-22 13:48:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'The members of Casa Luna are searching for a new housemate and co-op member, and have an opening now. Casa Luna is an artists'' cooperative house, organized by creative and unique individuals. We seek a person who will be excited to participate in the not so mundane daily goings-ons here at Luna, and have a life of their own that can be enhanced by involvement in a supportive home.\r\n\r\nPlease contact us if you''re interested in the following:\r\n\r\nCooking and enjoying vegetarian, ''freegan'' and vegan meals\r\nTaking long bike rides around the city and surroundings\r\nCreating art, music, and performance\r\nShedding layers of pre-established behavioral conditioning\r\nSharing duties of cleaning and organizing\r\nGardening, reading in the hammock, building campfires\r\nDumpster diving for fun and profit\r\n\r\nWe have twice-monthly house meetings, and a regular monthly potluck for our friends and extended community. Occasional parties too, with music, food, and not a small amount of revelry!\r\n\r\nFor rent is a downstairs, daylight basement room with a large window and modest closet. As much as we love kids and animals, we are not looking for any at this time. Two fabulous cats currently reside here, and though our house is kid friendly for short visits, we generally cultivate a more adult environment.\r\n\r\nWe are excited to meet somebody who is interested in taking a part in our community -- If you''re a busy student or professional -- and you''re still reading -- this might not be the best place for you to focus -- there''s usually something fun and distracting going on at the casa. That said, we''re also uninterested in substance abuse and anti-intellectualism... but we''ll talk.\r\n\r\nIf you''re interested, please respond to this ad with brief responses to the following questions:\r\n-Hi! Who are you?\r\n-What kind of place do you actually want to live in?\r\n-What might you contribute?\r\n-How long do you plan on sticking around when you find a home?\r\nAnd of course, anything else you''d like for us to know.\r\n\r\nMoving in requires a payment of first and last months rent + a 200 dollar deposit (150 of which is refundable), and co-op dues (currently $50, which covers bills, lightbulbs, cooking oil, etc)\r\nWe can be flexible on the move-in sum for the right candidate- so be sure to let us know how serious your interest is. Write to us if this is clearly someplace you ought to check out.\r\n\r\nThanks for reading!\r\nCasa Luna\r\n<!-- START CLTAGS -->', 'Casa Luna Seeking Housemates', 0, '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-06-22 13:48:38', '2010-06-22 21:48:38', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1054', 0, 'post', '', 0),
