(1057, 201, '2010-06-24 13:09:03', '2010-06-24 21:09:03', '<a title="IMG_3199 by bexamillion, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/bexamillion/4730806923/"><img src="http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1410/4730806923_6e312cb67b.jpg" alt="IMG_3199" width="375" height="500" /></a>\r\n\r\npride weekend descends upon seattle. businesses bust out their rainbow flags and queers converge in bars, clubs, and beer gardens across capital hill. corporations trot out their special pride products, eager to stuff their pockets with money from another niche market. is this what queerness looks like - spending money and getting wasted? wouldn''t you rather be celebrating with creation, rather than consumption? the bend-it festival is a fabulous example of this, with all ages music and more happening all weekend, but why stop there? people of all ages and identifications are welcome to join together this saturday night at midnight (that''s saturday going into sunday) for a roving dance party in the streets! we don''t need bars, booze, money, or ID cards to have fun. we are young, old, powerful, shy, sexy, smart, silly, and prepared to take what''s ours. these are our streets and we''ll play in them if we want to! wear your dancing shoes and bring your friends. see you at midnight!\r\n\r\ndown with corporate pride!\r\n\r\nup with "queers fucking queers" dance party!\r\n\r\nsaturday 6/26 at midnight!\r\n\r\nall ages and totally totally free!\r\n\r\nmeet up at madison and union, on the sidewalk <em>by</em> of pony (not in the bar itself)!\r\n\r\ncome and dance!', 'queers fucking queers dance party!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'queers-fucking-queers-dance-party', '', '', '2010-06-25 00:56:41', '2010-06-25 08:56:41', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1057', 0, 'post', '', 0),
