(1105, 1, '2010-07-09 11:46:03', '2010-07-09 19:46:03', 'The Capitol Hill Seattle blog <a href="http://www.capitolhillseattle.com/2010/07/09/capitol-hill-pirate-radio-station-aims-to-give-back-to-community-not-steal-airwaves">posted today</a> about a pirate radio station on Capitol Hill called "101.9 The Whore" (apparently named after a male prostitute? Read the story for more details about this if-y name, which will soon change to "Spunk FM"), with the intent to play dance music and local community PSA''s, especially focusing on the queer community here. It''s cool to see a pirate radio station start to go "above ground," and although it looks like the FCC is already aware of them, there does not appear to currently be an imminent risk of the station being shut down. For more info, visit this <a href="http://boards.radio-info.com/smf/index.php?topic=158613.0">message board thread</a>.\r\n\r\nThis brings to mind some work done by a collective in Philadelphia, the <a href="http://prometheusradio.org/">Prometheus Radio Project</a>, who help disenfranchised communities start their own radio projects, and have been working on passing <a href="http://prometheusradio.org/node/835">The Local Community Radio Act</a>, which would allow communities to start their own low power FM stations much more easily. This bill needs only pass the US senate before going to Obama''s desk! If this passes, this would be a huge boon to projects like "101.9 The Whore," any other pirate radio stations that would want to go above-ground, as well as projects like <a href="http://www.hollowearthradio.org/">Hollow Earth Radio</a>.\r\n\r\nSpeaking of <a href="http://www.hollowearthradio.org/">Hollow Earth Radio</a>, they just met and surpassed their recent fund raising goal, and will now have more than $4,500 in their coffers to help them move into their new public community space next door to <a href="http://www.2020cycle.com/">20/20 Cycle</a> in the Central District!! Huzzah!\r\n\r\n', 'Radio! Radio!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'radio-radio', '', '', '2010-07-09 11:49:35', '2010-07-09 19:49:35', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1105', 0, 'post', '', 1),
