(1218, 3, '2010-08-20 15:47:10', '2010-08-20 23:47:10', 'While you''re waiting in anticipation for the unofficial kick-off with the <a href="http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1197">Conspiracy Tour</a>, have a look at the awesome <a href="http://seattleanarchist.org/?page_id=45">workshop schedule</a>!\n\nSaturday, August 21st\n\n    * 10:30 am Cristien Storm, co-founder of Home Alive and author of Living In Liberation: Boundary Setting, Self-Care and Social Change\n    * 11:00 am Towards Queer Anarchist Theory\n    * 11:30 am The Beehive Collective\n    * 12:00 pm Anarchism &amp; Science\n    * 1:00 pm Squat Birth Journal\n    * 1:30 pm Common Action: Recentering on People’s Movements: Especifismo in Action\n    * 2:00 pm My Baby Rides the Short Bus Book Talk\n    * 2:30 pm Uses of a Whirlwind Book Talk\n    * 3:00 pm For Crying Out Loud: Survivor Support\n    * 4:00 pm Social War: the beginning of a Stratagem of Conflict\n\nSunday, August 22nd\n\n    * 11:30 am Emma Goldman Finishing School\n    * 1:00 pm Identity Politics: Tactically Inefficient\n    * 1:30 pm NW APOC on Racism, Sexism, Homophobia Now in Anarcho-Radical Movements\n    * 2:00 pm SeaSol strategy, tactics and movement building – How workers and tenants can defeat employers and landlords\n    * 2:30 pm Common Action: Transformative Justice Skillshare\n    * 3:00 pm George Jackson Brigade Discussion\n    * 3:30 pm Seattle Street Medic Training\n    * 4:00 pm One Big Union Book Talk\n\n The 2010 Seattle Anarchist Book Fair is August 21-22 at our partnered space, <a href="http://www.theveraproject.org">the Vera Project</a> (Warren Ave N &amp; Republican, at Seattle Center). Public hours are 10-5 on Saturday the 21st and 11-5 on Sunday the 22nd. We hope that our workshops and panels will be packed with folks from our communities engaging in discourse about things directly affecting our lives, whether it be strategies or tactics for resistance for putting theory into practice, or how to celebrate our creative passions. We think it is important to be cultivating our own ideas and art, projects and relationships, so that we aren’t lulled into complacency by Anarchist “experts” who have answers for us.', 'Seattle Anarchist Book Fair - it''s here!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'seattle-anarchist-book-fair-its-here', '', 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1197\nhttp://seattleanarchist.org/?page_id=45', '2010-08-20 15:47:10', '2010-08-20 23:47:10', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1218', 0, 'post', '', 0);
