(1225, 99, '2010-08-19 12:07:36', '2010-08-19 20:07:36', 'G20 Arrestee Benefit show, August 21st 8 pm. All Ages $5-10. At the FBK 6272 Ellis South Avenue, Seattle, Wa 98108\r\n\r\nIn June of 2010 G20 leaders met in Toronto. Seventeen people where  arrested who are now facing trumped up and politically motivated  allegations including conspiracy. Many were targeted in the streets and  for organizing events surrounding the G20, some arrested at gun point  and pre-emptive raids.  Some of the seventeen people were infiltrated by  two undercovers who had been organizing with them for the past year and  a half.  These attempts by the state to control and deem certain  individuals as terrorists by openly organizing, is to criminalize  dissent and weaken our courage of acting as a community. Solidarity is a  continuation of acts before and after arrests. We need to keep  organizing and draw strength even in the face of repression.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://portland.indymedia.org/media/images/2010/08/401636.jpg"><img class="alignnone" src="http://portland.indymedia.org/icon/2010/08/401636.jpg" alt="" width="129" height="200" /></a>', 'G20 Arrestee Benefit Show', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'g20-arrestee-benefit-show', '', '', '2010-08-19 12:09:07', '2010-08-19 20:09:07', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1225', 0, 'post', '', 0),
