(1232, 98, '2010-08-21 12:34:09', '2010-08-21 20:34:09', '<p style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter" title="HOLY CRAP!" src="http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4119/4905229335_2eae8dfdb1.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="390" /></p>\nOf my favorite bands in the Pacific Northwest, two of them are playing tonight. Of my favorite bands from Vancouver, BC, there is also one of those playing tonight.\n\nThis is Council of Lions'' last show possibly ever. They played at Friendship City (RIP 2008-2009) in Bellingham with Knot Knocked up and another band that I can''t recall at the moment. If my memory serves me right, either one or a combination of Jenn, Davy, Claire mentioned that they had been working on some songs. Everyone was all, like, "yeah, play for us" and they did. It was so great. It was the best. In about a year and a half they''ve become progressively more badass and still my favorite queercore / rock n'' roll band in the Northwest. Seriously. I''m going to miss their unity and inspiration.\n\nCold Lake''s cassette EP release is also happening at that same show. WOW! They''ve been working on this thing since early this month and one of those days I got a call asking if I could download some software to recover a hard drive that crashed (after they already recorded 5 songs)! There''s 9 songs on this cute-puppy, it''s red, and it''s rocked my face off since I listened to it whilst making breakfast both today and yesterday. The internet says that they''re "cleaner than Prince''s bathroom" and I hope and imagine that Prince has more than one bathroom (where would his guests #2?).\n\nMadonna Bangers is from Vancouver, BC. They''re the fucking best. Last time they played in Seattle it was about a year ago at the Chai House (that RIP''n café in Ballard) and at the New Crompton. The New Crompton PA couldn''t handle The King''s (vocals) words and ramblins''. The Chai House PA could but that''s not important. Imagine a bunch of "kids" in their early to mid 20''s going on a "rock ''n road" trip to America, getting stoked on beer (which is very expensive in Canada), and totally rip dippin'' the Chai House, then at some point before the show (or the next day) pooping in Lake Union and screaming "Corn Shark".\n\nI know barely anything about Imperial Can the than it''s Ghost Mice Chris''s new band on Plan-It-X and it''s probably fucking rad.\n\nAlso there''s a puppet show, and it''s Clyde Petersen''s birthday party. Fuck yeah.\n\n5113 Russell Ave NW (ballard)\n\n8pm <em>SHARP</em>, $5-$10', 'Cold Lake, Council of Lions (last show), Madonna Bangers (V,B.C.), Imperial Can (B, IN) TONIGHT!', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1231-revision', '', '', '2010-08-21 12:34:09', '2010-08-21 20:34:09', '', 1231, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1232', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
