(1307, 330, '2010-09-17 12:34:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1133\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sharpteethandhairallover.tumblr.com/post/898797472/im-going-to-elaborate-on-my-spoken-word-project-4-yall">I’m going to elaborate on my spoken word project 4 yall</a>\r\n\r\n-I posted a post that Kenneth posted about it but now I’m  posting about it so I can re-post it in other places so I don’t have to  post so many posts.-\r\n\r\n<strong>“the long and short of it”:</strong> I’m working on a spoken  word compilation cd/tape, you should record yourself reading a spoken  word piece with accompaniment and send it in Mp3 format to  Zebrajones01@gmail.com\r\n\r\n<strong>I’ll elaborate a bit:</strong> This is a project with very  few guidelines, it doesn’t even have a deadline, because I will just  always accept submissions for spoken word comps because I plan on always  making spoken word comps. This is vol. 1.\r\n\r\nThere are two really broad guidelines\r\n\r\n1) Record a spoken word piece. It doesn’t have to be a poem, it can  be a story or a conversation or just like, I dunno, anything I guess.\r\n\r\n2) It needs to have accompaniment. This is also pretty open, it  doesn’t have to be instrumental, it can honestly be anything. I mean I  guess it has to get my stamp of approval but don’t let that sway you  from trying anything and everything from noise loops to field recordings  to sound effects to guitar chords to drumming to whatever. “think  outside the box”\r\n\r\nOnce vol. 1 is all put together there will be more ways for you to help out but we’ll get to that when the time comes.', 'Spoken Word Compilation Project', 0, '', 'pending', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2010-09-17 12:34:38', '2010-09-17 20:34:38', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1307', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1268, 99, '2010-08-31 17:14:52', '2010-09-01 01:14:52', 'you may have heard about the brutal murders that happened yesterday\nand today by police in washington state (http://arcticcirclecollective.info/articles/51/seattle-cops-kill-again). with all of the work being done to quell anti-cop sentiment, a\nquick response to this news is appropriate.\n\nfolks will gather for literature distribution regarding these two specific murders this FRIDAY 9/3 from NOON to 2 pm in front of seattle central community college, on the corner of broadway and pine. people are encouraged to make banners, signs, their\nown handouts/pamphlets, and respect a diversity of tactics regarding\npeople''s public response to these tragedies.\n\nthis is a perfect opportunity to continue conversations regarding strategies for further timely community or individual responses to cop killings, as well as to find each other while addressing our rage at the police/state.', 'friday anti-cop demonstration', 0, '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1255-revision-2', '', '', '2010-08-31 17:14:52', '2010-09-01 01:14:52', '', 1255, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1268', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1281, 98, '2010-09-09 17:11:58', '2010-09-10 01:11:58', '<p style="text-align: center;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.seattlediy.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tarantula6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1285" title="tarantula6" src="http://www.seattlediy.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/tarantula6-300x204.jpg" alt="" width="0" height="0" /></a></p>\r\n<img class="alignnone" title="Cairo" src="http://i191.photobucket.com/albums/z43/sevenarts/cinema/tarantula.jpg" alt="" width="507" height="381" />\r\n\r\nThis fair Saturday of <strong>September 11th, 2010</strong> Cairo will have the fortune of presenting an outstanding multi-media performance presentation with enough pie to push plotted connections and flow yr bar chart.\r\n\r\nShow will start at <strong>8:00 SHARP</strong> because Cairo''s neighbors eat it raw. Be there at 7:30\r\n\r\n<strong>Slide 1</strong>:\r\n\r\nJustin Clifford Rhody of (Friends and Relatives Records) transversed across multiple states from Bloomington, Indiana. He may throw matches, feces, hearts but rumor has it that he''s just showing us a found film or soundtracked somethings.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://friendsandrelativesrecords.com" target="_blank">http://friendsandrelativesrecords.com</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Slide 2<span style="font-weight: normal;">:</span></strong>\r\n\r\nBrain Fruit will be tantalizing ears so much that your higher processes will desire more glucose and sucrose BUT stay away from high-fructose, and lactose (provided y''r vegan or intolerant). During this time you will have already noticed that the room looks a bit different than most of your experiences at Cairo. That''s because the room was transformed (or "installed") into bullshit via Slashed Tires. What an asshole.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://myspace.com/brainfruitmusic" target="_blank">http://myspace.com/brainfruitmusic</a>\r\n<a href="http://slashedtires.com/" target="_blank"> http://slashedtires.com/</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Slide 3</strong>:\r\n\r\nAlexis Gideon puts devils into your brian. He conjures- ney- summons these devils to do his bidding though his warlockian guitar and "soundtracks" in a genre known as "witch-wave" (way cooler and more coherent than "chillwave". Sorry bros). These devils'' dance moves send chills in such a way that it seems to only affect ye then... but <em>beware</em> of the night terrors brought to your brain whilst asleep.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://alexisgideon.com" target="_blank">http://alexisgideon.com</a>\r\n\r\nThere will also be friends and hugs.', 'Sept 11th at Cairo: Alexis Gideon, Justin Clifford Rhody, Brain Fruit', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sept-11th-at-cairo-alexis-gideon-justin-clifford-rhody-brain-fruit', '', '', '2010-09-09 19:48:57', '2010-09-10 03:48:57', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1281', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1322, 201, '2010-09-24 23:27:02', '2010-09-25 07:27:02', '<p style="text-align: center"><strong>Reeeeaaaallly Really Free Market Tomorrow (er, technically TODAY!!!)</strong></p>\r\n<img class="aligncenter" src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_QIv6HjGGb8c/SYuT3PxVTpI/AAAAAAAAAJk/a054NaGE0cU/s400/octopus.gif" alt="" width="360" height="360" />\r\n\r\nCome over to <strong>Pratt Park</strong> (20th and Yesler in the Central District) <strong>between noon and 4pm</strong>. <strong>Bring what you got</strong> (clothes? shoes? furniture? books? food? anything re-usable!), and <strong>take what you want</strong>. No buying/selling/bartering. Just sharing resources and spreading the love. At 4, anything left will be donated to Lifelong AIDS Alliance.\r\n\r\nThe main organizers won''t be able to show up until 2 tomorrow, so <strong>it''s up to you to make the magic of the RRFM happen! </strong>You can do it!<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nSee you tomorrow!', '', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '1322', '', '', '2010-09-24 23:27:02', '2010-09-25 07:27:02', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1322', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1271, 341, '2010-09-13 11:32:43', '2010-09-13 19:32:43', 'We would like to invite you to a community event that The Environmental Outreach and Stewardship (EOS) Alliance, in conjunction with 350.org, is hosting on October 10<sup>th</sup> in the Beacon Hill neighborhood.  EOS Alliance and volunteers from other organizations such as: Landau Associates, Green Seattle Partnership, and Cascade Land Conservancy are planning a community event to celebrate the Maple School Natural Area and surrounding community.\r\n\r\nOur event will feature free food, music, art, speakers and the continued restoration of the Maple School Natural Area.  The Maple School Natural Area is a green space where EOS Alliance is currently conducting habitat restoration work on behalf of the Green Seattle Partnership.  We want to create a community involvement for lasting care of the natural area and greater appreciation for the importance of healthy green spaces in Seattle.\r\n\r\nWhere: The Maple School Natural Area is located on: S 20th Ave. and S. Lucille Street\r\n\r\nWhen: October 10th, 2010 10am-6pm', 'Habitat Restoration on Beacon Hill! Music, Trees, and Free Food!', 0, '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'habitat-restoration-on-beacon-hill-music-trees-and-free-food', '', '', '2010-09-13 11:32:43', '2010-09-13 19:32:43', '', 0, 'http://www.seattlediy.com/?p=1271', 0, 'post', '', 1),
