(8, '<p>Do you like lofi surf punk? <span class=\\"postbody\\">How about super lofi? <br /> <br /> The Beach Boys, The Kinks, Eric&#39;s Trip and caUSE co-MOTION are our inspiration. <br /> <br /> Want to listen? You can go here - <br /> <a href=\\"http://www.myspace.com/sandycitywa\\" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/sandycitywa</a> <br /> <br /> We plan on playing a few shows in Northern CA &amp; Oregon at the end of January. <br /> <br /> Inquire for more details if you can help!  <br /> <br /> Show at Dancylvania on January 31st w/ Bow + Arrow and The Witches Of.\r\n<div id=\\"sig\\"><br /></div>\r\n</span></p>', '2008-12-21 20:15:57', 8, 18, 2, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:11:"Jon Manning";s:2:"at";i:1229912224;}}', '67.168.90.5'),
(9, '<p>There&#39;s going to be a really cool show at the blood barn.&nbsp; the show is the last show for the band Puma Run, also playing are Degania, Jason Clackley, and Posiedon.</p>\r\n<p>If the snow is gone it would be real nice bike ride from the ferry. This should be a really fun time!</p>\r\n<p>the address is 4054 west blakley ave</p>\r\n<p>if anyone needs help getting to the show from the ferry you should email me at deganiadegania at gmail dot com.</p>\r\n<p>Oh yeah! And it&#39;s free!!!!!&nbsp; pizza party afterwards!!<img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /><img title=\\"Cool\\" src=\\"/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif\\" alt=\\"Cool\\" /></p>', '2008-12-25 16:23:54', 9, 23, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.212.90.238'),
(10, '<p>On January 1st, at 12:30 in the afternoon on 15th and 45th in the U-District at the Tent City:</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Local homeless residents of \\"Nickelsville\\" Tent City and activists are holding a rally and march on the 1st to bring attention to the housing rights of homeless people in our city. There will be music, speakers, and food for all to gather around and discuss.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>At 2:30, after the speakers, a march will begin towards an abandoned property in the U-District. We will re-open the house, and claim it for the community. It will be used as temporary housing and a community space for our neighborhood, and for the homeless.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>bring noise makers, banners pertaining to housing rights or anti-capitalism if you&#39;re so inclined. Bring all your friends and food donations for the Tent City and for the new squat.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Thanks,</p>\r\n<p>-Team Victory Collective</p>', '2008-12-29 10:31:15', 10, 26, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '151.200.13.147'),
(11, '<p>I almost forgot!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>contact info:</p>\r\n<p>for more information and (limited) help on getting a ride to the action, please call:</p>\r\n<p>(206) 850 9626</p>\r\n<p>or email us at:</p>\r\n<p><a href="mailto:team_victory_will_win@yahoo.com" target="_blank">team_victory_will_win@yahoo.com</a></p>', '2008-12-29 10:34:21', 10, 26, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 2, NULL, '151.200.13.147'),
(12, '<p>We are looking to start an all People of Color dancy punk band and need another member.&nbsp; Preferably a woman or trans person of color to balance out gender.&nbsp; Right now we have a keyboardist, singer and drummer.&nbsp; So, if you play something that would compliment this, please email me at asiancajunandy(at)gmail(dot)com.</p>', '2008-12-30 15:01:50', 11, 10, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '24.18.179.255'),
(13, '<p>It sounds soooo good! I&#39;m stoked.</p>', '2009-01-03 01:55:51', 8, 1, 2, '', '', 0, 0, 2, NULL, '67.170.107.229'),
(14, '<table style=\\"text-align: left;\\" border=\\"0\\" cellspacing=\\"0\\" cellpadding=\\"0\\" width=\\"600\\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;\\">\r\n<div>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</div>\r\n<span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: medium;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-weight: bold; color: #000066;\\"><big><em>Glacier Blockade Earns Great Media!</em></big><br />Now Join the Community Rally to: PROTECT PUGET SOUND - STOP GLACIER&#39;S DOCK</span></span>\r\n<div><span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small; color: #000000; font-weight: bold;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small; font-style: normal; font-weight: bold; color: #cc0000;\\">Rally &amp; <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_1\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\" style=\\"border-bottom: 1px dashed #0066cc; cursor: pointer;\\">Flotilla</span> TOMORROW! - Sunday, January 4, 2009 - 12 Noon</span></span></div>\r\n<span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small; color: #000000; font-weight: bold;\\"><br />On foot - Meet at <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_2\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">Gold Beach Community</span> Center at Noon<br />Power Boat rendezvous at Dockton at 10 AM<br />Small Craft Launch from Sandy Shores at 12:30 PM</span>\r\n<div>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</div>\r\n<p><span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; color: #000000;\\"><em>[NOTE: For all our friends around the country, it may seem that Backbone Campaign has been a little quite - but fear not.   We are as fiercely and joyfully active as ever, supporting our local community to stand up to a corrupt corporate-government attack on our local ecosystems.<span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\"> We will have the giant Preamble in DC celebrating We the People for Inauguration, and the Procession for the Future Spring Tour is coming together beautifully</span>!  Contact us asap if you&#39;d like to be involved with either of those efforts.  <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_3\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\" style=\\"border-bottom: 1px dashed #0066cc; cursor: pointer;\\">206-408-8058</span>.]</em></span></p>\r\n</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;\\"> <br /> <img src=\\"http://backbonecampaign.org/media/HardBlockadeEast500.jpg\\" border=\\"0\\" alt=\\"\\" hspace=\\"5\\" vspace=\\"5\\" align=\\"right\\" /> <span style=\\"font-family: Verdana,Geneva,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: x-small; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; color: #000000;\\">Many islanders braved early morning cold and some risked arrest to protect the <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_4\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\" style=\\"border-bottom: 1px dashed #0066cc; cursor: pointer;\\">Puget Sound</span> and <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_5\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\" style=\\"border-bottom: 1px dashed #0066cc; cursor: pointer;\\">Maury Island</span>.  They earned great attention in the press:<br /><a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD55yWsp15DO8MyPiQXgW6gO4vKBrsRdq4WxbWjLvmdp01yDN0P-HtuP7Pf1rZDsZTNgYsyr9BQ1AX47NDQE8acdxWNnLo-C0g5bW0lQKuE0nTRiip_ezvA9UK5bMYOvYeaR3BjaPSqAMMmmKSJsqZ_MPdKTXioRywLsEWsLv2qJasAVslIowRmeVFBdqehghiFu17ILrvMXL0Q==\\" target="_blank"> <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_6\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">King 5 TV coverage</span></a>,  <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD55rGN87yIBwrnTCqINP0xCyRJbKjecamrv7WaRSDBuQLUaSPEUbb1AiOpj8nVb44GtL_tT1u98gvb8dwYAw27lIueON3g4CM62kQRd9-j1POwPOZlYEmm1fcQnEx65FwKb7FAC9zo7_-ghUm7Md_9JBy6n2TlUmqw_acwbkykLuau4fxoUU_dS5\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1231039024_7\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">Seattle Times story</span></a>, <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD54DOmekDl30LSW9e0k6lGsugzX_evNicYxcruCvT7eWN0nsWImMe10uM7IH7GzpVT2MgmUf3qUpbCs8xAmFc95vffGA6T-49qJeEjzYI-VtkkvySxM5qVhD3OqCWd2Rr2IsrMjuqswC2Uy5-n-_lnx6sSjfYHf_cdY5TN16Y-p3kDhIGhLXbNaoyqclsp1OMSI3HSjeeSEzzAfpFhh3dxMeA6Ll_RxNH7pULFPXzxep3udEsJHQ3pUz8_Tu5iwQnRo=\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1231039024_8\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">Seattle PI Photo essay</span></a> by Mike Urban, <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD54-AyBQmctXOvrDRPXF2hmD2E35tWwdaEjwbs9d6IusaxpM3dunF_eVxmR3yFpzuaitFhbTDJowFs4tP-fCfJfA5cCQ-DLVwy_pFtrPdWDmA-jA4hr_8ilNh8Dbdqwc34r_a5UcYOsOe6VV5CUVNzNr0N46aTtC4vs=\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1231039024_9\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">The Beachcomber&#39;s online coverage</span></a>, <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD57s80GCJZv68GY8QkQDnMHmecIDYfycm6aPBbirjXr0ZS1xWJ7LC0dRKT87P-HxBvP_vIFnHM1SC2J-91tZ5u0WXYztH6YZBrohGRzfue66kNEMxGa5dC3YSeEX284ZK3g=\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1231039024_10\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">POI Boardmember Patrick Christie KUOW</span></a>, <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD56CFKyCw-qhhuKM3nK9hcLK0gaaf9GIvKW5xshGpu2pnyCE0jlhpI9Khri0TpkfNsvxK5qpQ8sXfybL1WtlDw3VE4ZwoeoX0ePxFpI0x5Y6btA5MG5rilMsmGQig10EUjbILFRhaKVWew==\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1231039024_11\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">Photos by Dan Schueler</span></a>.<br /><br /> Now Backbone Campaign and Preserve Our Islands are hosting a GIANT community Flotilla &amp; Rally on the on the water &amp; on the beach this Sunday, Jan. 4th. <br /> <br /> Make a New Year&#39;s Resolution to STOP GLACIER from building a barge-loading pier for exporting 2-7+ MILLION of tons of Maury Island PER YEAR.  Stop the spilling, shading and spoiling of the Maury Island Aquatic Reserve.  The system is broken and the process has failed to protect the people and the Puget Sound.  So now it is up to us. <br /> <br /> Receive an update on the issue, listen to people-power music, and hear from community members, experts in aquatic preservation, and seasoned community activists speak about how <span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\">together - we can still win this fight</span>.  Join us TOMORROW to MAKE SOME NOISE! Send the message from Vashon-Maury to the rest of Puget Sound, Olympia, and Washington State that we will not be silent. <br /> <br /> Be part of the Flotilla in power boat or kayak, or join the crowd on the beach. <span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\">Bring noise makers (<span id=\\"lw_1231039024_12\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">air horns</span>, drums, and trumpets), your friends, and get inspired for a community struggle to protect the Island and Sound we all love so dearly. </span><br /> <br /> <strong><span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\">On foot:</span></strong> Meet us at the <span id=\\"lw_1231039024_13\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\" style=\\"border-bottom: medium none; background: transparent none repeat scroll 0% 0%; cursor: pointer;\\">Gold Beach Community</span> Center (<strong><a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001h8T6SbULD57DeU9cc2O-0o6YQfeJDFax58VnXt6ar6wGzzSN4y1QZrQb5ASy6-8LXUyEUAc98JRM1UEg9u_W9OCLLQxa-Tmlvjj0Mfr-v8_bw5VRJarDd6vTPQX-oT0P4Dk6ljZtTgq7HI1Nt1hKojTnarTebnL74-M194U79b6U7wzjkKP-4WimZUMQ55SA_ut-QD_ESDtnc-QGQu8FwX39_GzRVzYZTyETCXRMZllfzLQkk-Hu5bvL_k9jDcEwfSPnV9LuSjSO7ndKe5swYNZem1gPFWtksKX7435gb3NZHzswFjZMFNXVutUy2hIemZ6JuCANdt86Zd0zVEVWOZt58EzotF0b9MOCzczxpFA7Ro2OqZO3ZtOJw5FuvaDT6BsbGzuCyIgJlW-r6jK33OvAKm8dpUgwdBUB9_0_yIzd6e4JR3u5KM95aggkixmbUWThVSdmjrE=\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1231039024_14\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">MAP HERE</span></a></strong>) at NOON<br /> <strong><span style=\\"text-decoration: underline;\\">Small craft:</span></strong> Meet at Sandy Shores launch at 12:30. (<a rel=\\"nofoll