(22, '<p>Hey Gang. I sell records on and off around th&#39; area, y&#39; might have seen me at th&#39; Punk&nbsp; Rock Flea Market or the record label sale at Healthy Times this past December. Anyhow, I&#39;ll be at the Fremont Sunday Market a whole lot coming up (calendar at myspace.com/motorandfamine ) and I&#39;m mainly posting this because I am down to trade whatever records folks wanna bring. If it&#39;s decent-ish, I&#39;m definately up fr more of a straight-across trade than what a lot of the record stores do. It keeps things interesting for me when I don&#39;t have money to buy more records :)</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Anyways, drop by, it&#39;s on Sundays (I should be there about EVERY Sunday starting in March) on 34th in Fremont, between Phinney Ave and the PCC. I&#39;m always somewhere on the South side of the street, with a head-of-Elvis that reads \\"Glitter Hut\\" hanging from my canopy.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Looking especially for punk, noise, no-wave, indie, oddball, eclectic, garage, psyche, but whatever y&#39; got, ya&#39;ll. Drop by, I get pretty bored at these things.</p>', '2009-02-06 15:28:13', 17, 12, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '146.129.243.131'),
(23, '<p>Hallo.<br /> My name is Herbert and I&#39;m interested in finding out more information<br /> about displaying art in seattttle. I&#39;m currently looking for a place willing to host a free art show.<br /> This is the second time I&#39;ve ever actually done this, so I&#39;m still<br /> pretty new and I don&#39;t really know everything about showing art.<br /> <br /> The first show I &nbsp;did was at the Wayward Cafe and it was a free art show. We (my friends and I) gathered and collected art for the show from various artists from around the world. Then we displayed the art at the Wayward for the month. We had an ending reception where we gave all the art away for free to all who came. The idea behind this show came from a group of street artists who would leave paintings on the street, so that anyone interested could pick it up and take it home. More artists became interested in free art and it unofficially became known as Free Art Friday. &nbsp;Similar shows have the same idea as our free art show, but the difference is that we would like to display the art for a longer period of time for everyone to enjoy. There is another project called \\"Its Yours, Take It,\\" where shows are just turned into a one day event in a public space, open to all.<br /> <br /> While everyone has their own reason for doing free art, personally, I just like to make art and give it away to people.<br /> <br /> I would like to do another similar show and wanted to know if anyone would be open to the idea a free art show.<br /> I&#39;ve already started collecting art for my next show and would like to<br /> do one in April, if that would be at all possible. (I&#39;m not sure how<br /> far people are booked.)<br /> <br /> Well, thank you for reading.<br /> My friend recommended me to check the DIY scene here in Seattle.<br /> If you would like to know more, have questions, or would like to see what we have collected so far, please send me a message back.<br /> I look forward to working with everyone!,</p>\r\n<p>-Herbertos</p>', '2009-02-09 12:04:44', 18, 54, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '128.208.95.133'),
(24, '<p>would anyone like to help? or would anyone like to join in making some free art?</p>', '2009-02-10 11:56:17', 18, 54, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 2, NULL, '128.208.35.203'),
(25, '<p>Attention Indie Market Vendors! <br /><br />Bumbershoot&reg;: Seattle&rsquo;s Music &amp; Arts Festival is accepting applications for Bumbershoot&rsquo;s Indie Market. <br /><br />Bumbershoot is North America&rsquo;s largest annual urban arts and music festival. Scheduled over Labor Day weekend in Seattle, Bumbershoot offers its 150,000 festival-goers an engaging mix of entertainment and spectacle with more than 250 scheduled events in 20 indoor and outdoor venues. Learn more about this internationally acclaimed festival at bumbershoot.org.&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;<br />The Indie Market is Bumbershoot&rsquo;s arena for independent artists, designers, crafters, and retailers who break the mold of the traditional craft fair. It&rsquo;s a distinctive marketplace that speaks to Bumbershoot&rsquo;s young, urban audience &ndash; a colorful and varied display of handmade crafts, original designs, everyday art, and inventive retail style.<br /><br />If you are a craftastic entrepreneur or an independent retailer who supports indie craft artists, we want you to apply! Don&rsquo;t miss this incredible opportunity to be involved in one of Seattle&rsquo;s biggest gathering of artists and tastemakers. We encourage artists working in either new or traditional forms to apply. All types of work will be considered, with the exception of pre-recorded music, food, and beverage. Please note that T-shirts may be sold at Bumbershoot only with specific pre-approval. <br /><br />Festival Dates: Saturday, September 5 &ndash; Monday, September 7, 2009<br />Application Deadline: Tuesday, March 31, 2009, but applications accepted until all spaces are filled. <br />Vendor Operating Hours: 11:00 AM &ndash; 9:00 PM (later in some cases) <br /><br />Get an application here: <a href="http://bumbershoot.org/_pdf/Indie_Market_App.pdf" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://bumbershoot.org/_pdf/In.....et_App.pdf</a> <br /></p>', '2009-02-13 11:25:17', 19, 57, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '64.81.167.213'),
(26, '<p>Hey everyone I&#39;m new to the board, you&#39;ve got some really</p>\r\n<p>cool stuff happening here and I hope I can contribute.</p>\r\n<p>I have organized a new style record show here in Seattle I hope ya&#39;ll</p>\r\n<p>can come.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><a href=\\"http://www.bigdigseattle.com/\\" target="_blank"><span id=\\"lw_1234634222_0\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\"><a href="http://www.bigdigseattle.com/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.bigdigseattle.com/</a></span></a></p>\r\n<p>The Big Dig Record Show<br />Sat. March 7th<br />4-9pm $3<br />3pm Early Entry $10<br />All Ages/Bar w/ ID<br /><br />@ Lo-Fi<br /><span id=\\"lw_1234634222_1\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">429 Eastlake<br />Seattle, WA</span><br />(1 Block West of I-5, 3 Blocks N of&nbsp;<span id=\\"lw_1234634222_2\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">REI</span>)<br /><br />New times call for new solutions, gone are the days of waking before dawn to wade through an endless sea of records that wouldn&#39;t&nbsp; even have a place in the local Goodwill.<br />We have the answer! The&nbsp;<span id=\\"lw_1234634222_3\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">Big Dig</span>,&nbsp;<span id=\\"lw_1234634222_4\\" class=\\"yshortcuts\\">quality records</span>&nbsp;sold by friendly, knowledgeable record dealers from the Northwest and beyond.<br />Accompanied by DJ&#39;s spinning their favorite vinyl treasures and a full bar to provide all the social lubricant you&#39;ll need.<br />It&#39;s gonna be a scene man!</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />', '2009-02-14 11:57:56', 20, 59, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.231.220.116'),
(27, '<p>As most of you know, our beloved <strong>Home Alive</strong> is leaving their 10th ave and Pike location due to financial difficulties.&nbsp; But...we all know <strong>they will PREVAIL</strong> and continue their bombastic mission in our community.</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, our awesome<strong> PUNK ROCK YOGA</strong>&nbsp;class ( <a href=\\"http://www.punkrockyoga.com\\" target="_blank">http://www.punkrockyoga.com</a> )&nbsp;that have met there for the past three years is about to become homeless.</p>\r\n<p>at our classes, we have live music--no, not usually punk, but good improvizational tunage.&nbsp; We practice in a circle, and the class is cool for all levels (unless you have gnarley injuries that need special attention, then we can schedule one-on-one practices)</p>\r\n<p>We need a place to practice on Tuesday nights on Capitol Hill between the hours of 5-7pm in order for the group to continue...space enough for up to ten folks to practice yoga.</p>\r\n<p>Facilitators get free classes, and the energy we contribute to any space is OFF THE CHARTS!!!&nbsp; Oh, by the way, I can also pay some rent. :)</p>\r\n<p>Homes, buisnesses, any space at all will do... we&#39;re punk!</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Can you help?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thanks so much,</p>\r\n<p>Janell (the yoga teacher)</p>', '2009-02-24 16:29:45', 21, 65, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '74.61.29.6'),
(28, '<p>Hey everyone,</p>\r\n<p>I play drums and am looking to start a fun summer band with some like-minded musicians. In my mind, the major influences would be groups like Gang Gang Dance, Abe Vigoda, No Age, Animal Collective, OOIOO, El Guincho, ESG . It would be super rhythmic (inspired by latin, afro-cuban, \\"world\\"-beats, house, etc) and uptempo, danceable but not aggressive. I don&#39;t want to get too unnecessarily complex musically. Having FUN is the key.Creativity with effects and loops is a plus.</p>\r\n<p>Anyone interested or know if any similar projects out there need a drummer?</p>\r\n<p>Thanks!<br />Benny</p>\r\n<p>throwing.up.ghosts &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; @ &nbsp; &nbsp; gmail.com</p>', '2009-03-05 13:54:51', 22, 75, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '74.94.73.118'),
