(41, '<p>i have to be out of the place i am staying at by july 16th so i am trying to find a room in a house, or apartment, with like minded people. i work at the wayward cafe so a desired location would be close to the university district but if not, i am willing to make the commute. 100$ to 350$ dollars a month is in my comfort zone but we can negotiate a price. i am friendly, i will clean up after myself, i will provide my own food ( wouldn&#39;t mind sharing either), and i am not a pyscho pathic murderer. contact me at <a href="mailto:freetacosfor99cents@hotmail.com" target="_blank">freetacosfor99cents@hotmail.com</a> or 206-719-2646 if you are interested in meeting up and talking about said topic. thank you for your time, hope to hear from you soon</p>\r\n<p>- chad</p>\r\n<p>p.s. closets, pantries, or studios will work too. i don&#39;t have a lot of stuff and i don&#39;t mind small living conditions.</p>', '2009-06-19 17:48:49', 33, 147, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.231.146.49'),
(34, '<p>I live in Sherwood Co-op. I am looking for a subletter. I think you want to live here.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Its a collective house. We share food, stories, skills, and a love for activism. We have an amazing organic garden out front, checkins, and run a collective antry project our o our basement. We help with FNB and a number of other programs. We support social justice. We love to make things (like beer, soda and essential oils), to ride bikes, to read books, to talk, to cook. We have community vegan dinners nearly every night and monthly potlucks. We live in the U.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>My room is pretty damn big and overlooks the garden on the 2nd floor.<br />It has 2 walls of crazy windows and gets tons of light. <br />I&#39;ll be gone from mid June - September. the room is furnished, but I don&#39;t have alot of stuff. Just a bed, couch, desk, and recored/tape player. You can use my stuff, hell if I like you&nbsp; you can borrow my bike.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Let me know if your interested. Come over for dinner and check it out.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>w hi t n e y&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 206-619-0873&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href="mailto:whitney@theemptyroom.org" target="_blank">whitney@theemptyroom.org</a></p>', '2009-04-29 10:47:50', 26, 110, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '76.22.99.22'),
(35, '<p>Hey,</p>\r\n<p>I am throwing a benefit fro Home Alive @ The Underground Events Center on July 4th. It&#39;s going to be an All Ages early show, and line up is looking pretty killer (I am keeping it on the DL until its confirmed but it&#39;s a very loud metal/grind/punk show).</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>I am calling out to Seattle DIY itself, as well as anyone who would like to volunteer at this event, and help promote it before hand. We will have an awesome flier ready in mid-May, and plan on coordinating fliering teams in all parts of town to get the word out about this awesome cause. As you may know, Home Alive is having a tough time and it is homeless itself. I am looking to get max capacity for this event, or at least the most I can for the kind of music it is.</p>\r\n<p>If ANYONE is down to help PLEASE contact me @&nbsp; <a href="mailto:aaronkennedypr@gmail.com" target="_blank">aaronkennedypr@gmail.com</a></p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Thank you for reading,</p>\r\n<p>Aaron</p>', '2009-04-29 12:47:46', 27, 114, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '209.91.40.108'),
(36, '<p>Hi - My band is trying to book our first tour out of San Francisco - and I need help!</p>\r\n<p>Here&#39;s our website: <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://prizehog.bravehost.com&amp;nbsp\\" target="_blank"></a><a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://prizehog.bravehost.com&amp;nbsp\\" target="_blank"><a href="http://prizehog.bravehost.com&nbsp" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://prizehog.bravehost.com&nbsp</a>;</a>;;;; . We have a show on the 2nd of July&nbsp; in Portland, we would like to book another Oregon show the 3rd and 6th and to play in Washington for July 4th and 5th - help?</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Thanks for your help.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>-Veronica</p>\r\n<p><a href="mailto:volcanodust@gmail.com" target="_blank">volcanodust@gmail.com</a></p>', '2009-05-04 17:56:32', 28, 116, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:4:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:11:"volcanodust";s:2:"at";i:1241478278;}i:1;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:11:"volcanodust";s:2:"at";i:1241484176;}i:2;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:11:"volcanodust";s:2:"at";i:1241484215;}i:3;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:11:"volcanodust";s:2:"at";i:1241484272;}}', '66.253.70.71'),
(37, '<p>Hi Everybody!</p>\r\n<p>I&#39;m in two bands that are touring from New York. Two bands consisting of five people.(Less people sleeping on your floor!)</p>\r\n<p>We&#39;re planning on being in the Washington area from July 31 to Aug 3 and Aug 6 &amp; 7, then the Oregon area on Aug 8 &amp; 9. We already have plans for Aug 4 &amp; 5.</p>\r\n<p>If you/anyone you know could help us out with a show we would love and appreciate it. If you&#39;re in/know someone in a band that could draw people and are of a similar D.I.Y. ethic please let me know or contact them (or both).<br /> Thanks so much.<br /> <span style=\\"color: #888888;\\"><br /> Kevin Yankou<br /> 914 564-1020<br /> <a href=\\"http://www.myspace.com/nooneandthesomebodies\\" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/noonean.....somebodies</a><br /> <a href=\\"http://www.myspace.com/turbosleaze\\" target="_blank">http://www.myspace.com/turbosleaze</a></span></p>\r\n<p>p.s.</p>\r\n<p>I&#39;d rather you didn&#39;t crank call me. Plus, it might be expensive.</p>', '2009-05-30 16:08:18', 29, 133, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '173.2.66.228'),
(38, '<p>We&#39;re seeking a roommate for a 3br Wallingford house, starting on July 1st. Rent is $475/month plus utilities, with first/last/security deposit as well as a $35 credit check required by our landlord. The house is a block from Greenlake and close to bus routes, and in addition to your personal room there is a small shared office/studio space. <br /> <br /> Our ideal roommate is a student/artist/whatever who is creative, clean, and responsible. We&#39;re both pretty busy between our jobs, school, and the various non-profits we volunteer with. We spend most of our time at home in the evening and are gone most of the day. We both have a variety of creative hobbies like playing music, drawing, writing, cooking, and are much more likely to spend an evening at home with a movie or reading than to be partying. We&#39;re looking for much the same from a roommate, someone who&#39;s low-key to live with but also active and interesting in their personal pursuits.</p>\r\n<p>We&#39;re omnivores but enjoy Vegan/Vegetarian food, good coffee, and riding our bikes around the lake.</p>\r\n<p>Email <a href="mailto:crshong@hotmail.com" target="_blank">crshong@hotmail.com</a>&nbsp; for more info and to set up a time to check out the space.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>word.</p>\r\n<p>chris hong</p>', '2009-06-04 20:15:42', 30, 138, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '72.11.69.174'),
(39, '<p>Hey Fellow diy&#39;ers. I wanted to let you know about a completley awesome diy festival going on in Missoula, MT this year. Total Fest is in it&#39;s 8th year of existence and is going to be at the Badlander/ Palace lounge this year. The shows are all ages and also alcohol will be available for the 21+ crowd. I don&#39;t know the ticket prices yet but an ever growing list of confirmed bands and other important details will be available at <a href="http://www.totalfest.org" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.totalfest.org</a> and myspace.com/totalfest Please keep checking the site and I hope you folks will make the 8 hour drive to come hand out and BBQ with us and enjoy some great bands. I&#39;ll post the entire lineup when they do. Thanks. Tyson</p>', '2009-06-07 00:35:11', 31, 139, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '72.174.39.150'),
(40, '<p>Hey.</p>\r\n<p>If you&#39;re in between leases/houses for part of the summer, my roommate and I are looking to fill two rooms in our house for the month of July. &nbsp;The house is in the U-District about 3 blocks from Wayward (yum) and half a block from the 71, 72, and 73 bus lines.</p>\r\n<p>One room is in the basement and it will cost $400 because it&#39;s a little dark down there. &nbsp;The other is upstairs on the ground floor and is going for $500. &nbsp;ALLLL Utilities/internet included! &nbsp;Also, you can move in as early as June 15th (whoa, a month and a half for the price of one!?).</p>\r\n<p>Let me know if you are interested. &nbsp;Move fast though, cause I&#39;m leaving town soon.</p>\r\n<p>(washer/dryer, dope porch-couch sitch).</p>\r\n<p>[1305 NE 55th Street]</p>', '2009-06-08 15:55:44', 32, 141, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '24.18.243.169'),
(42, '<p>our house is basically like this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2OJ8GSNC3zY" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v.....OJ8GSNC3zY</a><br /><br />we might have a room opening up this july. a shed in august if you&#39;re real ballsy. the july room could possibly be shared with male or female bodied crust punk bike mechanic (pending roommate shuffle). it&#39;s a really big room with a huge huge closet, possibly you could rent the closet for $150. or a closet that&#39;s not in someone&#39;s room for $200. please someone who gives a damn. i am vegan and like vegans. this house is basically at the epicenter of vegan seattle but also includes meat eaters. xvx also good. we have a back yard / garden / bike shop / wood shop / sweet kitchen / shared library. we are way into dumpstering and diy. we ride our bikes to the dumpstore. join us.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>no idiots</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>email bahutaccha at gmail</p>', '2009-06-30 00:49:02', 34, 67, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '67.160.38.140'),
(43, '<p>Hey Everyone,</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>How&#39;s it going? My name is Greg O&#39;Brien and I live in Dublin Ireland. I run a D.I.Y label here called Slow Loris. We mainly release folk, electronic, experimental pop stuff. I play in a band called <a title=\\"at last an atlas\\" href=\\"http://www.myspace.com/atlastanatlas\\" target="_blank">at last an atlas</a> and I release comics and Zines. I&#39;m coming to the states in October and i&#39;m looking to play some shows in and around seattle and was just wondering if anyone might be able to help me out. If anyone has any advice or help it&#39;d be hugely appreciated. I&#39;m travelling up from&nbsp; San Fransisco to Seattle and plan to be in and around Seattle from about the 24th of October to the 3rd of November.</p>\r\n<p>So if anyone knows of people running shows anywhere in Seattle or surround towns and citys, the help would be much appreciated. Thanks a million,</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Take care</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Greg</p>', '2009-07-16 16:46:32', 35, 168, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '89.100.41.117'),
