(54, '<p>We are Una and Nym and we are looking for a little room in a radical/collective-type house&nbsp;to live in hopefully for the long-term.</p>\r\n<p>We have been on a music/farm tour since July, and we both have jobs lined up for our Seattle return. We are both musicians but don&#39;t require loud practice sessions, tidy but not total neat freaks, non-smoking but don&#39;t care what you do. Nym can weld/fix/build just about anything, including bikes. If the house is interested, he knows how to keep and care for chickens. I would love to start a garden or help with one in the coming year and do art skill-share type stuff. I make music and zines (the kind that are actually on paper) and sew a lot. We also have a big-ass industrial sewing machine and a scary looking van and are dumpster enthusiasts.</p>\r\n<p>We are nice and stable and do dishes and are house-trained.</p>\r\n<p>In dreamy-dream land the house would be in Georgetown/Ballard/upper Cap-Hill/U-district but other places are great too.</p>\r\n<p>If you or anyone you know has an opening in an awesome house, please email me so that I can help make it awesomer and then we can all be awesomest together.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\\"mailto:orphanspace@hotmail.com\\" target="_blank">orphanspace@hotmail.com</a></p>\r\n<br />', '2009-10-31 18:27:59', 44, 241, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '76.164.37.19'),
(55, '<p>Gender Jam laDIY&amp;Trans Fest Olympia</p>\r\n<p>November 20th-22nd</p>\r\n<p>Processions Studio: 311 Capitol Way North, Olympia, WA.</p>\r\n<p>Totally free DIY event! Workshops, Music Shows, Dance Party, Housing, Food &amp; Childcare!</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Go to the website to see the schedule, register and volunteer!</p>\r\n<p><a href="http://olyladiyfest.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">http://olyladiyfest.wordpress.com/</a></p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>GenderJam is a not-for-profit radical community event. We recognize that we live in a society full of power imbalances along lines of race, class,gender, sex, sexuality, age, physical ability, size and other diverse identities. Though these differences can feel intimidating, we also affirm that we share common experience that inspires us to fight these norms. As we work towards ending sexism in our society, we feel it is essential to build community and experience each other in new ways, loving and supporting one another. GenderJam&rsquo;s intention is to build community and empower women,female-bodied or identified people, transfolk, queers, ladies, and genderqueer people. We hope to do this by sharing skills, listening to each other, performing for each other, working together, learning from one another, and affirming and lifting each other up. We hope to create spaces for dialogue, motivation and creativity, and to practice open communication and love for one another in the process.</p>\r\n<p>We welcome the greater Olympia community to join with us in this effort. While the GenderJam festival itself will occupy just one weekend, our intention is to make it an anuual event, and more importantly to re-create our community to be as safe, inclusive and supportive as possible for people who are woman, female, gender queer, and/or trans-identified. We hope to be a permanent visible, irrepressible and positive force now and in the future.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Confirmed Workshops Include:<br /><em>Book-binding, astronomy, comics, drag performance, massage techniques, self defense, acrobalancing, piercing and tattoos, radical mycology, portable stove making, ICE Resistance, how to pants the cops without them knowing, making earrings, square dancing, songwriting, screen printing, and more!</em></p>\r\n<p>Confirmed Performances By:<br /><em>Kimya Dawson, Eleanor Murray, Foxdye, Aba Cole, Council of Lions, Cumulus, Witch Kromosomes, Femme Uke, Black Guns, Party Thighs, Little Swamp, Purple Rhinestone Eagle, Pet Dander, Mika Mae, Margy Pepper, Violet, Briana Marela and Blood Bones. </em></p>\r\n<p><em><strong>Ready or not, here we come&hellip;</strong></em></p>', '2009-11-15 15:52:34', 45, 257, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.231.47.104'),
(56, '<p>Hey folks.</p>\r\n<p>We&#39;re a well established Seattle band in need of a competent, creative and committed keyboard player / multi-instrumentalist with some pretty solid vocal skills. We have a preference for a female in terms of the vocals, but a guy with a higher tenor voice and a nice falsetto (think Carl Wilson) could totally work. Keyboard should be your primary focus but it would be a big plus if you can play a little guitar / bass or, better yet, strings or brass. Experience or desire to learn live music software like Ableton will also definitely work in your favor. We&#39;re a bit all over the place stylistically but I guess we qualify as indie pop more than anything else. Major influences include the Beach Boys, Flaming Lips, Talking Heads, Built to Spill, Velvet Underground, Neutral Milk Hotel, Of Montreal, CSNY, Harry Nilsson, AnCo, Yes, loads of other stuff (like I said, we&#39;re pretty stylistically diverse). <br /> <br />We&#39;re by no means a huge band right now but we&#39;re definitely on the up and up, having been played a number of times on KEXP and in regular rotation on KFJC, KEXP, and SomaFM indiepoprocks. We&#39;ve played college shows with 1000+ in the audience in addition to venues like the Doug Fir in Portland and the Slowdown in Omaha. While you don&#39;t need to quit your day job, it is imperative that you&#39;d be able to take off ~2 weeks in March to tour to and from SxSW; we&#39;ve confirmed a tour to and from with another noteworthy Seattle band as well as several shows in Austin. We&#39;ll be releasing a record right before then as well. We have pretty serious aspirations for this band so we need someone willing to commit to that mindset. Not that we take ourselves overly seriously, but we definitely want to make every effort to succeed where we can. <br /> <br />It&#39;d be best if you&#39;re at least in your mid 20s and maybe not much older than mid 30s. If you&#39;re interested please send us an email describing your qualifications and, preferably, any recorded material you might have. If it looks like you might be a good candidate for us we&#39;ll send you our album and you can see what you think; we can go from there!</p>\r\n<p>ps.&nbsp; I guess we&#39;re not exactly a DIY band in the sense that we only play house shows and record on a talkboy, but we definitely still play these sorts of house shows and so forth.</p>', '2009-12-04 10:17:49', 46, 183, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '174.21.186.96'),
(57, '<p>please respond directly to <a href="mailto:casaluna@googlegroups.com">casaluna@googlegroups.com</a>.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Casa Luna Co-op is a seven bedroom artist/musician cooperative in Seattle&#39;s Roosevelt neighborhood. Situated on the 66 Metro line and near three large grocery stores, this is a great location and we love our home! We are currently all between the ages of twenty-five and thirty (2 gals, three guys) and are active, employed, literate, queer-friendly, critical thinkers. Our two kitchens are primarily vegetarian and we have a vested interest in maintaining that. We enjoy preparing and sharing meals. <br /> Two bedrooms are open for the month of February, with possible prorated January move-in. Rent for the available rooms is $360 and $270 for an upstairs and basement room, respectively. Utilities are included in our monthly co-op dues of $75, which includes bulk food staples, lightbulbs, soap, and other practical necessities. Our home has long been a hub of activity and we are seeking applicants who are interested in being around people, music, community, food, gardens, discussion, dance, snacks, bicycles, and feats of strength and contortion. We plan to have an art and fashion party in early March, so if you have artwork to contribute feel free to mention it. <br /> To apply, please write to us about yourself and your experience with cooperative living (or lack thereof, don&#39;t be shy)- If you don&#39;t receive a response from us immediately, please understand that we recieve too many inquiries to respond to all. Otherwise, we may have you over to see the house and meet collective members. Though we have a cat, you need not apply if you currently have pets. More may be possible in the future but new additions to the co-op are only allowed via consensus decision- this process helps us all remain accountable. House plants are more than welcome. <br /> Bereft the ravages of indirect communication! Viva grammar y punktuacion! Viva! <br /> <br /> Casa Luna Co-op thanks you.</p>', '2010-01-08 14:32:48', 47, 275, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.197.232.74'),
(58, '<p>The <strong>Starship Submarine</strong> presents:<br />Mouce Manouche (gypsy-folk, Seattle)<br />Trees Are Neurons (lysergic-nature-drone, Humboldt CA)<br />Harold Cisman (intense-awesomeness, Seattle)<br /><br />Please attend, beginning 8pm at 825 Lake Washington Blvd in Leschi on the date of January 16th, which is a Saturday evening. <br />Bring beverages and food to share, if you would like. <br /><br />Thank you kindly,<br />-profane stefane</p>\r\n<p><a rel="nofollow" href="http://honorificabilitudinitatibusrecordings.blogspot.com" target="_blank">http://honorificabilitudinitat.....ogspot.com</a></p>\r\n<a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/lh/photo/AhYiJj6WRCYY10ZZ9FMSQw?feat=directlink" rel="nofollow">http://picasaweb.google.com/lh.....directlink</a>', '2010-01-10 16:33:49', 48, 258, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:8:"effenvee";s:2:"at";i:1263170203;}}', '98.237.248.63'),
