(60, '<p>hello<br />we have a room that will be empty by the end of this month in our house. we are 5 minutes away from university avenue, many good dumpsters, the food bank, parks, waterfront, cool venues and co-ops. the rent is about 420 all utilities included and there is a deposit ( which makes a total of 540 to move in ). it&#39;s not cheap but on the other hand landlady doesnt care about the house and we can pretty much do anything we&#39;d like in here/with it. <br />the house has three stories, ground level, basement and an attic that needs work done but could eventually be turned into one or two rooms and make every one&#39;s rent cheaper. the room is on ground level, right by the bathroom (there is another full bathroom downstairs). it is about a 100 sq.ft. with a double window and an empty lot for a view. there is a little walk in closet with a window too.<br />7 people are living in the house right now but more often than not it&#39;s quiet and empty since about half of us are working full time or spend a lot of time out. someone who would be more interested in making this house an actual co-op and being actively involved in collective activities would be preferred!<br />we moved in just a few months ago and there is still a lot to be done to make the place alive. we have been trying to keep the commons clear of too many furniture and other useless crap so we always have space to jump around, dance, and work on various projects like making soap, home brewing, repairing stuff, painting etc&hellip; we are also planning on having public events soon. we are currently setting the basement space for house shows and a resource center where we can offer access to a free store, a zine and anarchist/diy publication library, internet access and washing machine/shower for kids passing thru. the house is huge and there are tons of possibilities!<br />a plus too if you are interested in gender issues and generally in redefining your relationships with others outside of the patriarchal and consumerist ideas of love/sex/friendship etc&hellip; <br />if you are interested in meeting us contact us and tell us a little bit about yourself and your interests. if you are playing music or painting or writing and have internet pages, send us some links!<br />danke</p>\r\n<p><a href="mailto:htilil.lilith@riseup.net">htilil.lilith@riseup.net</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="mailto:doppelgangerhaus@gmail.com">doppelgangerhaus@gmail.com</a></p>', '2010-01-24 21:07:18', 50, 238, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:13:"eatyourmakeup";s:2:"at";i:1264396810;}}', '76.28.255.137'),
(61, 'Hey gang-<br /><br />Okay, this message is a three-parter... First off, I wanna announce that I&#39;m opening up a new record shop in Ballard on March 13th! It&#39;s at 5459 Leary Ave NW, on the second floor of Resolution Audio (next door to where Mr. Spot&#39;s Chai House was until last week). You actually have to walk through the stereo shop to get upstairs, which might seem a little weird, but it&#39;s cool. They&#39;re renting out portions of their vacant second floor for really cheap; there are currently two other record shops and a clothing store there now.<br /><br />Part two: I need records to open up a record shop! I&#39;ve been getting stock from labels and bands around the world, but I also wanna have a good selection of local stuff (Seattle, Olympia, Bellingham, whatever...). I&#39;ve already hit up labels I know personally, like Lost Sound and MASA, but maybe I don&#39;t know you or just haven&#39;t seen you in the last few weeks. Check out the website below (it&#39;ll look cooler later, of course) and send me an email with what you&#39;ve got. I&#39;ll take cds, vinyl, tapes, cd-rs, whatever. I&#39;m also hoping to have a zine section, but I&#39;ve been detached from the zine culture for so long that I don&#39;t really know what&#39;s what anymore. Suggestions welcomed!<br /><br /><a href="http://jigsaw-records.com/" target="_blank">http://jigsaw-records.com/</a><br /><br />Part three! I&#39;ve been gathering the furniture/supplies I need, but there are a couple things that still elude me. If you see any of these items on your thrifting/dumpstering/etc quests, please snag it for me or let me know where to get it (Craigslist has been fruitless to date, but I&#39;m always checking).<br /><br />* <strong>cassette racks/shelves</strong>: probably either one big one (holding 100-ish tapes) or a couple mid-sized ones (holding 30-50 each) would be useful<br /><br />* <strong>cd display thingies</strong>: the kind that are tiered for new release displays, if you know what I mean...<br /><br />Everything else should be easy to find or build myself. Thanks!<br /><br />Chris', '2010-02-02 11:31:36', 51, 285, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '24.19.48.28'),
(62, '<p>Hey All,</p>\r\n<p>I live at a house called the Garden of Readen, and we&#39;re putting on a 3 night 2 day music festival on the 16th, 17th, and 18th of April.&nbsp; The idea is similar to Carosel Fest, and will be almost completely house shows.&nbsp; We&#39;re trying to bring people in from all different genres.&nbsp; Do a pop punk show here, a hardcore show there, an ambient nose set somewhere else, etc.&nbsp; Let me know if your band is into this, or if you know some people I should contact who would love to play/help out.&nbsp; Also, if you have any tips from one organizer to another, please let me know.&nbsp; My e-mail is <a href="mailto:nduncan@riseup.net">nduncan@riseup.net</a> .&nbsp; Thanks every body!</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>Nick Duncan</p>', '2010-02-08 19:04:13', 52, 286, 3, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '76.121.122.152'),
