(72, 'The members of Casa Luna are searching for a new housemate and co-op member, and have an opening now. Casa Luna is an artists&#39; cooperative house, organized by creative and unique individuals. We seek a person who will be excited to participate in the not so mundane daily goings-ons here at Luna, and have a life of their own that can be enhanced by involvement in a supportive home. <br /> <br /> Please contact us if you&#39;re interested in the following: <br /> <br /> Cooking and enjoying vegetarian, &#39;freegan&#39; and vegan meals <br /> Taking long bike rides around the city and surroundings <br /> Creating art, music, and performance <br /> Shedding layers of pre-established behavioral conditioning <br /> Sharing duties of cleaning and organizing <br /> Gardening, reading in the hammock, building campfires <br /> Dumpster diving for fun and profit <br /> <br /> We have twice-monthly house meetings, and a regular monthly potluck for our friends and extended community. Occasional parties too, with music, food, and not a small amount of revelry! <br /> <br /> For rent is a downstairs, daylight basement room with a large window and modest closet. As much as we love kids and animals, we are not looking for any at this time. Two fabulous cats currently reside here, and though our house is kid friendly for short visits, we generally cultivate a more adult environment. <br /> <br /> We are excited to meet somebody who is interested in taking a part in our community -- If you&#39;re a busy student or professional -- and you&#39;re still reading -- this might not be the best place for you to focus -- there&#39;s usually something fun and distracting going on at the casa. That said, we&#39;re also uninterested in substance abuse and anti-intellectualism... but we&#39;ll talk. <br /> <br /> If you&#39;re interested, please respond to this ad with brief responses to the following questions: <br /> -Hi! Who are you? <br /> -What kind of place do you actually want to live in? <br /> -What might you contribute? <br /> -How long do you plan on sticking around when you find a home? <br /> And of course, anything else you&#39;d like for us to know.  <br /> <br />Moving in requires a payment of first and last months rent + a 200 dollar deposit (150 of which is refundable), and co-op dues (currently $50, which covers bills, lightbulbs, cooking oil, etc) <br />We can be flexible on the move-in sum for the right candidate- so be sure to let us know how serious your interest is. Write to us if this is clearly someplace you ought to check out. <br /> <br /> Thanks for reading! <br /> Casa Luna <br /> <!-- START CLTAGS --><br />', '2010-06-22 13:49:44', 61, 327, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.231.104.150'),
(73, '<p><strong>HI HOW ARE YOU HELLO</strong></p>\r\n<p>i just found out yesterday that i got a job in seattle, so i&#39;m on the lookout for community-minded folks to live with!</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><strong>ABOUT ME</strong></p>\r\n<p>- a tiny queer woman of color, in her early-twenties;</p>\r\n<p>- current resident of baltimore;</p>\r\n<p>- vegetarian/aspiring vegan;</p>\r\n<p>- volunteer at a radical info/coffeeshop;</p>\r\n<p>- interested in food justice, feminist ethics, radical accountability, reading while walking, and animal documentaries&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><strong>HOUSING PREFERENCES</strong></p>\r\n<p>- first/foremost: though leftist/radical politics resonate strongly with me, i think revolutionary rhetoric is much less important than the way you create community</p>\r\n<p>- meaningful avenues of open, honest communication (e.g., house meetings, mutual respect, post-it notes taken seriously, however you do it, etc)</p>\r\n<p>- a collective commitment to understanding &amp; respecting each other&#39;s needs, boundaries, and positions, especially when it&#39;s inconvenient or uncomfortable</p>\r\n<p>- creaky houses without cable television</p>\r\n<p>- no indoor smoking, though i have nothing at all against smoking outdoors/in general!</p>\r\n<p>- animal housemates! i am so fuckingfond of large dogs, snugglemonster cats, and miscellaneous rodentia. &nbsp;have i mentioned chickens? please let me help you take care of yr chickens.</p>\r\n<p>- a certain degree of cleanliness; let&#39;s take care of our shared spaces together!</p>\r\n<p>- room for gardening, bike storage, dance parties, shared meals, DIY projects, and community events</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><strong>OTHER CON$IDERATIONS</strong></p>\r\n<p>probably not more than 400 (utilities included) a month, although that&#39;s somewhat negotiable. i&#39;ll be here for at least a year!</p>\r\n<p>my job begins on the first of september, so if i could move in mid-august, that would be tops.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p><strong>IF YOU</strong></p>\r\n<p>waded successfully through all these exclamation points and are STILL interested in living with me (or even just being friends! i&#39;m in that market for that, too!), reply here with your email address and LET THE GREAT EXPERIMENT BEGIN. making sure we&#39;re the right fit for each other is important to me, too, so let&#39;s talk it out. thanks for your time/thoughts/feelings!</p>', '2010-07-18 09:47:51', 62, 328, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:2:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:4:"bean";s:2:"at";i:1279635356;}i:1;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:3:"bug";s:2:"at";i:1279646320;}}', '96.234.189.62'),
(74, '<p>hi. i&#39;m moving to seattle and trying to get a sense of where i might best seek housing among responsible, community-building, DIY-minded folks. i&#39;ve been living in washington, DC for about 9 years and grew up outside the city, and as much as I love and have been deeply inspired by my time here, I&#39;m sorta yearnin&#39; for a change in surroundings. I&#39;ve lived in radical collective housing for the better part of my adult life, and i&#39;m hoping to dig a few a roots in a similar space in y&#39;all&#39;s fascinating town.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>i&#39;m 27, cis-male, small and weird and determinedly gender-deviant. i am a white person strongly committed to anti-racist, radical feminist, and anti-authoritarian politics. i spent a good chunk of my teens absorbed by urban punk culture, and while i don&#39;t feel nearly as comfortable within the limits of that "scene" as i once did, i encountered a lot of positive ideas that have carried over into my life since. i am a grubby scavenger; i love to scour for busted parts and abandoned machines and dismember components and rebuild things and repair things and remake things. i &#39;ve done a lot of music-related projects in DC - most recently, I recorded a whole slew of rad crust/metal/folk/punk projects in a homebuilt studio behind my house! I am on the quiet side socially, but it&#39;s super important to me to maintain healthy, trusting, communicative relationships with people i&#39;m close to or becoming closer to! i make a lot of bad jokes and sing blind guardian guitar solos whilst bombing massive hills on my trusty bike and get unreasonably excited about garden herbs. i would like very much to live in a world that seamlessly incorporates medieval times and snow crash into a thrilling, unpredictable whole.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>i&#39;m hoping to find a group house on the small side (4-7 folks vs 15-20) with a single room rent in the $400 range &ndash; preferably something with windows to the outside world &ndash; and housemates who love to cook and enjoy keeping a reasonably tidy space. workshops, gardens, studios, the occasional carefully organized house-show, etc would all be a huge plus. despite my enthusiasm about moving, i am sad to leave behind the tiny, wonderfully diverse family i&#39;ve been a part of in DC, and i&#39;m really hoping to find a group of folks with whom i can try to build a similar sense of community and momentum, and who are committed to developing lasting, sustainable worlds outside of apocalyptic capitalist monoculture.</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>i&#39;m hoping to find a place to move into on 1 september or a few days after..any ideas, room openings, pointers, advice, criticism, etc would be greatly appreciated.. i don&#39;t really have any close friends in the NW, so i&#39;m kinda on my own trying to figure everything out! i found this site during a housing search and it really resonated with me, so i figured i&#39;d give this a shot! thanks so much for any / all help!</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>bryan</p>\r\n<br />', '2010-07-20 07:01:43', 63, 329, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:3:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:5:"bryin";s:2:"at";i:1279609347;}i:1;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:5:"bryin";s:2:"at";i:1279609698;}i:2;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:5:"bryin";s:2:"at";i:1279611388;}}', '69.250.148.94'),
(75, '<p>My house at 20th and Dearborn in the CD(bordering the ID) is looking for a roomate for August 1st and two for Sept. 1st.&nbsp; Two rooms are medium-sized and $365/mo. and one is large and $450/mo.&nbsp; We are in a nice neighborhood close to tons of bus lines, $2 Vietnamese sandwiches, Goodwill and The Greenhouse.</p>\r\n<p>We are 27-35, have two cats, are relatively clean and bands practice in the basement 2-3 times per week.&nbsp; Veg/aquatarians preferred but it&#39;s negotiable.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please have a job, decent rental/credit history and clean up after yourself.&nbsp; We are very chill and just looking for mature, problem-free roommates.&nbsp; This would fill the remainder of our lease through Jan. 4th.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Get in touch at <a href="mailto:flophaus@hotmail.com" target="_blank">flophaus@hotmail.com</a>&nbsp;or 206-933-5708</p>\r\n<p>Thanks!&nbsp; Justin</p>', '2010-07-21 23:30:55', 64, 331, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '184.77.100.150'),
(76, '<p>The Office of Dr Glorious is looking for a lovely new roommate!&nbsp; We are a Central District house with four bedrooms, typically housing four people.&nbsp; The room you would be living in is a large forest green dwelling with high ceilings and three windows.&nbsp; We have a basement space suitable for musical projects, art projects and anything else you think you may want to use it for. &nbsp; We have some quiet house shows from time to time as well.&nbsp; The three roommates that are staying are in their mid twenties and early thirties and all work with children.&nbsp; All you really need in order to fit in here is the ability to wash a few dishes now and then and generally be a friendly, open, un-turdlike human. &nbsp; Ideally looking for a female-ish person to take the room in order to keep things balanced but any and all who apply will be considered.&nbsp; As noted in the title this room is available anywhere between the 1st and 15th of August, utilities are not included in the rent price but tend to stay low, usually the put the rent for the place up to a whopping $360 a month. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please call or email to set up a time to view the room, and meet and greet the roommates. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Best Wishes,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Amanda</p>\r\n<p>360 888 9514</p>', '2010-07-22 09:01:31', 65, 305, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '71.217.82.115'),
(77, '<p>hi amanda! I sent you a PM about the room -- it&#39;d be rad to chat with y&#39;all !</p>\r\n<p>thanks</p>\r\n<p>bryan</p>', '2010-07-22 09:27:54', 65, 329, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 2, NULL, '69.250.148.94'),
(78, '<p>Hey I&#39;m Ed and I just might be interested! You should e-mail me though, because i feel like that would be a more reliable form of communication.</p>\r\n<p>My email is <a href="mailto:Zebrajones01@Gmail.com">Zebrajones01@Gmail.com</a></p>\r\n<p>ask me some questions, I&#39;ll ask you some, we&#39;ll become the best of friends.</p>\r\n<p>Also, I can&#39;t help but promote my project, I dunno if you noticed but my friend Kenneth posted on the front page about a spoken word compilation, well, that&#39;s my spoken word compilation, haha, you should read about it and send me a spoken word peice!</p>\r\n<p>Anyways, thanks for reading, I hope to hear from you soon!</p>\r\n<p>-Ed</p>', '2010-07-22 13:19:54', 61, 330, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 2, NULL, '184.78.197.212'),
(79, '<p>hey! i&#39;m Christopher.</p>\r\n<p>me and my partner and a friend are looking at a house that is south of&nbsp;Seattle. It&#39;s about a twenty minute bus or about 30-40 minute bike ride&nbsp;from downtown. If you want to look at a map, it&#39;s at the north end of tukwila.</p>\r\n<p>we are hoping to be very active in the community, both downtown and in the south seattle area. we&#39;re already started up a food not bombs chapter and are hoping to do a lot more once we move into this house. we&#39;re&nbsp;going to garden, provide help for homeless and poor, live sustainably, host shows in the basement, host food not bombs cooking, give travelers a place to stay as they pass through (there&#39;s a shed in the yard that&#39;d be great for that). yes we&#39;ve even talked about getting chickens. everyone at the house practices vegetarianism (two are vegan) and freeganism (great dumpsters nearby). we&#39;ll have a kitten and may be getting a dog sometime soon.</p>\r\n<p>"i think revolutionary rhetoric is much less important than the way you create community" this is an awesome quote. i, personally, would very much agree and think the other housemates would as well, and that&#39;s what we want to do with this house.</p>\r\n<p>anyways, i&#39;m overseas and getting further and further from internet accessability and computers in general, so i&#39;ll give you my e-mail and my partner&#39;s, her name is Bethany.</p>\r\n<p>mine is: <a href="mailto:christopherchambers@live.com" target="_blank">christopherchambers@live.com</a></p>\r\n<p>hers is: <a href="mailto:iliketoycars@yahoo.com" target="_blank">iliketoycars@yahoo.com</a></p>\r\n<p>i already linked her to your&nbsp;post and she was interested, but because i&#39;m so far we haven&#39;t communicated super well. email her and talk to her about all the figures and stuff, she knows more than me. we&#39;d be very interested in creating community with you!</p>\r\n<p>hope to hear from you soon!</p>\r\n<p>love</p>\r\n<p>christopher</p>', '2010-07-22 13:56:44', 62, 334, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 2, NULL, '83.236.129.34'),
(80, '<p>My friend Derek and I are really fiending for one, it would help us immensely in our musical endeavors, however, we&#39;re short of $$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$</p>\r\n<p>and loop machines cost $$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$$</p>\r\n<p>So like, if you really h8 your loop machine and find yourself thinking</p>\r\n<p>"Man, I would sell this for a very small ammount of $$$$$$$" (regarding your loop machcine)</p>\r\n<p>We&#39;re the guys to talk to =)</p>\r\n<p>Lemme know if you&#39;ve got one, my email is <a href="mailto:Zebrajones01@gmail.com">Zebrajones01@gmail.com</a></p>\r\n<p>and my phone number is (425)213-9260</p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>-Ed</p>', '2010-07-27 12:13:43', 66, 330, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '184.78.197.212'),
(81, '<p>we&#39;re two guys who are 27 and live in wallingford/greenlake. Our two girl rommates moved out and we&#39;re also moving out but need someone to sublet while we get our shit together for another month or two.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hoping to find someone who&#39;s cool, responsible etc, all the usual stuff&nbsp;more clean than dirty, . House is on stone way and n. 50th. We have a nice garden and yard, music space, and generally a pretty sweet little house. drop me a line at mwwilkes [at] gmail.com if interested and I&#39;ll tell you all you want to know. thanks!</p>', '2010-07-28 13:13:06', 67, 335, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '67.161.92.236'),
(82, '<p>Yo &ndash; i&#39;m looking for a ride to philadelphia. I&#39;ve got shit to do in town until Aug 15th, but I&#39;d like to leave soon after.&nbsp; I&#39;m trying to get up there for a couple weeksto help a friend make a movie.&nbsp; I&#39;m Jonah, 24, male, amiable, agreeable, and i am sure that we would become fast friends.&nbsp; And i would be totally happy to split gas, driving time, share conversation, snacks, etc.&nbsp; Thanks!</p>', '2010-08-01 12:46:29', 68, 216, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:6:"JonahB";s:2:"at";i:1280667059;}}', '24.35.120.224'),
(83, '<div class="content">Looking for people interested in playing in a band&hellip;</div>\r\n<div class="content">I&#39;ve been working on this music for a long time but am</div>\r\n<div class="content">trying to get people involved who would want to be in a band!</div>\r\n<div class="content">The music I have written thus far is loosely influenced by Godspeed you  black emperor, earth, my bloody valentine, city of caterpillar,  Harvey  milk, other drone, minimalist type shit, as well as doomy stuff.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class="content">if this sounds fun to anyone email me, <a href="mailto:justgallego@gmail.com" target="_blank">justgallego@gmail.com</a></div>\r\n<div class="content">thanks<img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /><img title="Cool" src="/wp-content/forum-smileys/sf-cool.gif" alt="Cool" /></div>', '2010-08-08 22:53:01', 69, 23, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, 'a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:2:"by";s:9:"justin...";s:2:"at";i:1281308118;}}', '97.113.70.8'),
(84, '<p>Hey everyone! &nbsp;I&#39;m looking for a place to live! &nbsp;Maybe you have a room opening up in your exciting, fun, artistic, inspiring house? &nbsp;I&#39;m a musician (mostly violin and piano, with a hint of writer, and other extraneous human stuff) and i would really love to be involved in a house that was putting on shows, readings, and community events like this. &nbsp;I do need to be able to play and record music in my room (at reasonable volumes, at reasonable times of day of course), and if there&#39;s space for band practices this is a big plus. &nbsp;A bit more about me: i&#39;m 24, male, have lived in seattle and oly for 5ish years, i&#39;m all about riding bikes and swimming and summertime adventures and dancing, and sci-fi, fantasy, anime, i volunteer/dj for hollow earth radio, i&#39;m pretty rad. &nbsp;My name&#39;s jonah. &nbsp;Ask about me. &nbsp;Thanks!</p>', '2010-08-22 12:32:23', 70, 216, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '75.145.28.178'),
(85, '<p>We are coming to Seattle in a weeks time (4th&nbsp;September) with the intention of filming acoustic/stripped back songs with unsigned/smaller bands and artist in interesting locations around the city. It will feature as a special on our website&nbsp;<a href="http://www.manchesterscenewipe.co.uk/" target="_blank" target="_blank">http://www.manchesterscenewipe.co.uk</a>&nbsp;which has a great following here in the UK. It would be great exposure for bands over here.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If there are any bands out there who would suit being stripped back (i.e. no power/amps) or anyone who has any suggestions of cool up and coming bands</p>\r\n<p>then please get in contact with us at <a href="mailto:info@manchesterscenewipe.co.uk">info@manchesterscenewipe.co.uk</a></p>\r\n<p>We are also up for anyone meeting up with us for a pint and showing us some cool hangouts, house gigs, diy shows, gigs and the general underbelly of Seattles live music scene.</p>\r\n<p>Thanks</p>\r\n<p>toby &amp; Sam</p>', '2010-08-26 05:43:31', 71, 339, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '86.164.111.69'),
(86, '<p>got a handful of songs in the vein of woody guthrie, utah phillips with my own twist.</p>\r\n<p>sort of folk/country with punk ideas/ethics. would like to busk and play a lot of shows.</p>\r\n<p>any instrument would be great - i play an old spanish guitar w/ a pick and big strums and sing</p>\r\n<p>was thinking we could meet up in freeway park or anyother park. I have a space we can practice in the future.</p>\r\n<p>typically i have taken my folk songs and turned them into more punk rock songs for whatever band i was in at the time and im not opposed to doing that again. but lets get together and share some idea and see where we go.</p>\r\n<p>talk to you soon. <a href="mailto:traviswhensley@gmail.com">traviswhensley@gmail.com</a></p>', '2010-09-28 13:56:15', 72, 348, 1, '', '', 0, 0, 1, NULL, '184.78.237.200');
