(2024, 298, 'description', 'On the third Friday of every month the Temenos Project will gather to witness, celebrate, judge the 22-minute performances by last month’s winners. Afterwards, 6 artists will have 90 seconds to convince the audience to vote for them for next month’s two performance slots. The winners will split the grant ($150-300 each) and will have a month to create, refine, dig up a 22-minute performance of their own. On the third Friday of the next month the Temenos Project do it all again.\r\n\r\nMission:\r\n    The Temenos Project is a performative, philanthropic experiment exploring how to promote high-quality, community-focused arts here in Seattle. We are group of people who believe that artists play vital roles in community and that communities need to find ways to support their artists. This is our attempt to put those things together through a monthly performance series and grant. Think of it as a CSA for artists.\r\n\r\n    The Temenos Project brings amazing artists together with audiences dedicated to sustaining and celebrating a vibrant arts scene in Seattle. It is a space for performances of all stripes, where artists stand before their community(ies) weaving stories of possibility. Our communities are hungry for visions not only of how the world is, but of how the world might yet be. In order to build a better future we must first see it.'),
